626 
627 #ifndef HEAP_ALIGN_LOG
628 /* default tiny heap size: 16KB */
629 #define HEAP_ALIGN_LOG 14
630 #endif
631 #define CEILDIV(i, mod) (((i) + (mod) - 1)/(mod))
632 enum {
633  HEAP_ALIGN = (1UL << HEAP_ALIGN_LOG),
634  HEAP_ALIGN_MASK = (~(~0UL << HEAP_ALIGN_LOG)),
635  REQUIRED_SIZE_BY_MALLOC = (sizeof(size_t) * 5),
636  HEAP_SIZE = (HEAP_ALIGN - REQUIRED_SIZE_BY_MALLOC),
637  HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT = (unsigned int)((HEAP_SIZE - sizeof(struct heap_page_header))/sizeof(struct RVALUE)),
638  HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT = CEILDIV(CEILDIV(HEAP_SIZE, sizeof(struct RVALUE)), BITS_BITLENGTH),
639  HEAP_BITMAP_SIZE = ( BITS_SIZE * HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT),
640  HEAP_BITMAP_PLANES = USE_RGENGC ? 3 : 1 /* RGENGC: mark bits, rememberset bits and oldgen bits */
641 };
642 
643 struct heap_page {
644  struct heap_page_body *body;
645  struct heap_page *prev;
646  rb_heap_t *heap;
647  int total_slots;
648  int free_slots;
649  int final_slots;
650  struct {
651  unsigned int before_sweep : 1;
652  unsigned int has_remembered_objects : 1;
653  unsigned int has_uncollectible_shady_objects : 1;
654  } flags;
655 
656  struct heap_page *free_next;
657  RVALUE *start;
658  RVALUE *freelist;
659  struct heap_page *next;
660 
661 #if USE_RGENGC
662  bits_t wb_unprotected_bits[HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT];
663 #endif
664  /* the following three bitmaps are cleared at the beginning of full GC */
665  bits_t mark_bits[HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT];
666 #if USE_RGENGC
667  bits_t uncollectible_bits[HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT];
668  bits_t marking_bits[HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT];
669 #endif
670 };
671 
672 #define GET_PAGE_BODY(x) ((struct heap_page_body *)((bits_t)(x) & ~(HEAP_ALIGN_MASK)))
673 #define GET_PAGE_HEADER(x) (&GET_PAGE_BODY(x)->header)
674 #define GET_HEAP_PAGE(x) (GET_PAGE_HEADER(x)->page)
675 
676 #define NUM_IN_PAGE(p) (((bits_t)(p) & HEAP_ALIGN_MASK)/sizeof(RVALUE))
677 #define BITMAP_INDEX(p) (NUM_IN_PAGE(p) / BITS_BITLENGTH )
678 #define BITMAP_OFFSET(p) (NUM_IN_PAGE(p) & (BITS_BITLENGTH-1))
679 #define BITMAP_BIT(p) ((bits_t)1 << BITMAP_OFFSET(p))
680 
681 /* Bitmap Operations */
682 #define MARKED_IN_BITMAP(bits, p) ((bits)[BITMAP_INDEX(p)] & BITMAP_BIT(p))
683 #define MARK_IN_BITMAP(bits, p) ((bits)[BITMAP_INDEX(p)] = (bits)[BITMAP_INDEX(p)] | BITMAP_BIT(p))
684 #define CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(bits, p) ((bits)[BITMAP_INDEX(p)] = (bits)[BITMAP_INDEX(p)] & ~BITMAP_BIT(p))
685

692 #endif

871 
872 /*
873  * 1 - TSC (H/W Time Stamp Counter)
874  * 2 - getrusage
875  */
876 #ifndef TICK_TYPE
877 #define TICK_TYPE 1
878 #endif
879 
880 #if USE_TICK_T
881 
882 #if TICK_TYPE == 1
883 /* the following code is only for internal tuning. */
884 
885 /* Source code to use RDTSC is quoted and modified from
886  * http://www.mcs.anl.gov/~kazutomo/rdtsc.html
887  * written by Kazutomo Yoshii <kazutomo@mcs.anl.gov>
888  */
889 
890 #if defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__i386__)
891 typedef unsigned long long tick_t;
892 #define PRItick "llu"
893 static inline tick_t
894 tick(void)
895 {
896  unsigned long long int x;
897  __asm__ __volatile__ ("rdtsc" : "=A" (x));
898  return x;
899 }
900 
901 #elif defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__x86_64__)
902 typedef unsigned long long tick_t;
903 #define PRItick "llu"
904 
905 static __inline__ tick_t
906 tick(void)
907 {
908  unsigned long hi, lo;
909  __asm__ __volatile__ ("rdtsc" : "=a"(lo), "=d"(hi));
910  return ((unsigned long long)lo)|( ((unsigned long long)hi)<<32);
911 }
912 
913 #elif defined(_WIN32) && defined(_MSC_VER)
914 #include <intrin.h>
915 typedef unsigned __int64 tick_t;
916 #define PRItick "llu"
917 
918 static inline tick_t
919 tick(void)
920 {
921  return __rdtsc();
922 }
923 
924 #else /* use clock */
925 typedef clock_t tick_t;
926 #define PRItick "llu"
927 
928 static inline tick_t
929 tick(void)
930 {
931  return clock();
932 }
933 #endif /* TSC */
934 
935 #elif TICK_TYPE == 2
936 typedef double tick_t;
937 #define PRItick "4.9f"
938 
939 static inline tick_t
940 tick(void)
941 {
942  return getrusage_time();
943 }
944 #else /* TICK_TYPE */
945 #error "choose tick type"
946 #endif /* TICK_TYPE */
947 
948 #define MEASURE_LINE(expr) do { \
949  volatile tick_t start_time = tick(); \
950  volatile tick_t end_time; \
951  expr; \
952  end_time = tick(); \
953  fprintf(stderr, "0\t%"PRItick"\t%s\n", end_time - start_time, #expr); \
954 } while (0)
955 
956 #else /* USE_TICK_T */
957 #define MEASURE_LINE(expr) expr
958 #endif /* USE_TICK_T */
959 
960 #define FL_TEST2(x,f) ((RGENGC_CHECK_MODE && SPECIAL_CONST_P(x)) ? (rb_bug("FL_TEST2: SPECIAL_CONST (%p)", (void *)(x)), 0) : FL_TEST_RAW((x),(f)) != 0)
961 #define FL_SET2(x,f) do {if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE && SPECIAL_CONST_P(x)) rb_bug("FL_SET2: SPECIAL_CONST"); RBASIC(x)->flags |= (f);} while (0)
962 #define FL_UNSET2(x,f) do {if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE && SPECIAL_CONST_P(x)) rb_bug("FL_UNSET2: SPECIAL_CONST"); RBASIC(x)->flags &= ~(f);} while (0)
963 
964 #define RVALUE_MARK_BITMAP(obj) MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARK_BITS(obj), (obj))
965 #define RVALUE_PAGE_MARKED(page, obj) MARKED_IN_BITMAP((page)->mark_bits, (obj))
966 
967 #if USE_RGENGC
968 #define RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED_BITMAP(obj) MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_WB_UNPROTECTED_BITS(obj), (obj))
969 #define RVALUE_UNCOLLECTIBLE_BITMAP(obj) MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_UNCOLLECTIBLE_BITS(obj), (obj))
970 #define RVALUE_MARKING_BITMAP(obj) MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARKING_BITS(obj), (obj))
971 
972 #define RVALUE_PAGE_WB_UNPROTECTED(apge, obj) MARKED_IN_BITMAP((page)->wb_unprotected_bits, (obj))
973 #define RVALUE_PAGE_UNCOLLECTIBLE(page, obj) MARKED_IN_BITMAP((page)->uncollectible_bits, (obj))
974 #define RVALUE_PAGE_MARKING(page, obj) MARKED_IN_BITMAP((page)->marking_bits, (obj))

976 #define RVALUE_OLD_AGE 3
977 #define RVALUE_AGE_SHIFT 5 /* FL_PROMOTED0 bit */
978 
979 static int rgengc_remembered(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj);
980 static int rgengc_remember(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj);
981 static void rgengc_mark_and_rememberset_clear(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap);
982 static void rgengc_rememberset_mark(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap);

984 static inline int
985 RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE(VALUE flags)
986 {
987  return (int)((flags & (FL_PROMOTED0 | FL_PROMOTED1)) >> RVALUE_AGE_SHIFT);
988 }
989 
990 #endif /* USE_RGENGC */

992 
993 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE == 0
994 static inline VALUE
995 check_rvalue_consistency(const VALUE obj)
996 {
997  return obj;
998 }
999 #else
1000 static VALUE
1001 check_rvalue_consistency(const VALUE obj)
1002 {
1003  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
1004 
1005  if (SPECIAL_CONST_P(obj)) {
1006  rb_bug("check_rvalue_consistency: %p is a special const.", (void *)obj);
1007  }
1008  else if (!is_pointer_to_heap(objspace, (void *)obj)) {
1009  rb_bug("check_rvalue_consistency: %p is not a Ruby object.", (void *)obj);
1010  }
1011  else {
1012  const int wb_unprotected_bit = RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED_BITMAP(obj) != 0;
1013  const int uncollectible_bit = RVALUE_UNCOLLECTIBLE_BITMAP(obj) != 0;
1014  const int mark_bit = RVALUE_MARK_BITMAP(obj) != 0;
1015  const int marking_bit = RVALUE_MARKING_BITMAP(obj) != 0, remembered_bit = marking_bit;
1016  const int age = RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE(RBASIC(obj)->flags);
1017 
1018  if (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj) == T_NONE) rb_bug("check_rvalue_consistency: %s is T_NONE", obj_info(obj));
1019  if (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj) == T_ZOMBIE) rb_bug("check_rvalue_consistency: %s is T_ZOMBIE", obj_info(obj));
1020  obj_memsize_of((VALUE)obj, FALSE);
1021 
1022  /* check generation
1023  *
1024  * OLD == age == 3 && old-bitmap && mark-bit (except incremental marking)
1025  */
1026  if (age > 0 && wb_unprotected_bit) {
1027  rb_bug("check_rvalue_consistency: %s is not WB protected, but age is %d > 0.", obj_info(obj), age);
1028  }
1029 
1030  if (!is_marking(objspace) && uncollectible_bit && !mark_bit) {
1031  rb_bug("check_rvalue_consistency: %s is uncollectible, but is not marked while !gc.", obj_info(obj));
1032  }
1033 
1034  if (!is_full_marking(objspace)) {
1035  if (uncollectible_bit && age != RVALUE_OLD_AGE && !wb_unprotected_bit) {
1036  rb_bug("check_rvalue_consistency: %s is uncollectible, but not old (age: %d) and not WB unprotected.", obj_info(obj), age);
1037  }
1038  if (remembered_bit && age != RVALUE_OLD_AGE) {
1039  rb_bug("check_rvalue_consistency: %s is rememberd, but not old (age: %d).", obj_info(obj), age);
1040  }
1041  }
1042 
1043  /*
1044  * check coloring
1045  *
1046  * marking:false marking:true
1047  * marked:false white *invalid*
1048  * marked:true black grey
1049  */
1050  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace) && marking_bit) {
1051  if (!is_marking(objspace) && !mark_bit) rb_bug("check_rvalue_consistency: %s is marking, but not marked.", obj_info(obj));
1052  }
1053  }
1054  return obj;
1055 }
1056 #endif
1057 
1058 static inline int
1059 RVALUE_MARKED(VALUE obj)
1060 {
1061  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1062  return RVALUE_MARK_BITMAP(obj) != 0;
1063 }
1064 
1065 #if USE_RGENGC
1066 static inline int
1067 RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(VALUE obj)
1068 {
1069  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1070  return RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED_BITMAP(obj) != 0;
1071 }
1072 
1073 static inline int
1074 RVALUE_MARKING(VALUE obj)
1075 {
1076  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1077  return RVALUE_MARKING_BITMAP(obj) != 0;
1078 }
1079 
1080 static inline int
1081 RVALUE_REMEMBERED(VALUE obj)
1082 {
1083  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1084  return RVALUE_MARKING_BITMAP(obj) != 0;
1085 }
1086 
1087 static inline int
1088 RVALUE_UNCOLLECTIBLE(VALUE obj)

1091  return RVALUE_UNCOLLECTIBLE_BITMAP(obj) != 0;
1092 }

1094 static inline int
1095 RVALUE_OLD_P_RAW(VALUE obj)
1096 {
1097  const VALUE promoted = FL_PROMOTED0 | FL_PROMOTED1;
1098  return (RBASIC(obj)->flags & promoted) == promoted;
1099 }
1100 
1101 static inline int
1102 RVALUE_OLD_P(VALUE obj)
1103 {
1104  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1105  return RVALUE_OLD_P_RAW(obj);
1106 }
1107 
1108 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE || GC_DEBUG
1109 static inline int
1110 RVALUE_AGE(VALUE obj)
1111 {
1112  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1113  return RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE(RBASIC(obj)->flags);
1114 }
1115 #endif
1116 
1117 static inline void
1118 RVALUE_PAGE_OLD_UNCOLLECTIBLE_SET(rb_objspace_t *objspace, struct heap_page *page, VALUE obj)
1119 {
1120  MARK_IN_BITMAP(&page->uncollectible_bits[0], obj);
1121  objspace->rgengc.old_objects++;
1122 
1123 #if RGENGC_PROFILE >= 2
1124  objspace->profile.total_promoted_count++;
1125  objspace->profile.promoted_types[BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)]++;
1126 #endif
1127 }
1128 
1129 static inline void
1130 RVALUE_OLD_UNCOLLECTIBLE_SET(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
1131 {
1132  RVALUE_PAGE_OLD_UNCOLLECTIBLE_SET(objspace, GET_HEAP_PAGE(obj), obj);
1133 }
1134 
1135 static inline VALUE
1136 RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE_SET(VALUE flags, int age)
1137 {
1138  flags &= ~(FL_PROMOTED0 | FL_PROMOTED1);
1139  flags |= (age << RVALUE_AGE_SHIFT);
1140  return flags;
1141 }
1142 
1143 /* set age to age+1 */
1144 static inline void
1145 RVALUE_AGE_INC(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
1146 {
1147  VALUE flags = RBASIC(obj)->flags;
1148  int age = RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE(flags);
1149 
1150  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE && age == RVALUE_OLD_AGE) {
1151  rb_bug("RVALUE_AGE_INC: can not increment age of OLD object %s.", obj_info(obj));
1152  }
1153 
1154  age++;
1155  RBASIC(obj)->flags = RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE_SET(flags, age);
1156 
1157  if (age == RVALUE_OLD_AGE) {
1158  RVALUE_OLD_UNCOLLECTIBLE_SET(objspace, obj);
1159  }
1160  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1161 }
1162 
1163 /* set age to RVALUE_OLD_AGE */
1164 static inline void
1165 RVALUE_AGE_SET_OLD(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
1166 {
1167  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1168  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(!RVALUE_OLD_P(obj));
1169 
1170  RBASIC(obj)->flags = RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE_SET(RBASIC(obj)->flags, RVALUE_OLD_AGE);
1171  RVALUE_OLD_UNCOLLECTIBLE_SET(objspace, obj);
1172 
1173  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1174 }
1175 
1176 /* set age to RVALUE_OLD_AGE - 1 */
1177 static inline void
1178 RVALUE_AGE_SET_CANDIDATE(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
1179 {
1180  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1181  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(!RVALUE_OLD_P(obj));
1182 
1183  RBASIC(obj)->flags = RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE_SET(RBASIC(obj)->flags, RVALUE_OLD_AGE - 1);
1184 
1185  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1186 }
1187 
1188 static inline void
1189 RVALUE_DEMOTE_RAW(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
1190 {
1191  RBASIC(obj)->flags = RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE_SET(RBASIC(obj)->flags, 0);
1192  CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_UNCOLLECTIBLE_BITS(obj), obj);
1193 }
1194 
1195 static inline void
1196 RVALUE_DEMOTE(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
1197 {
1198  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1199  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(RVALUE_OLD_P(obj));
1200 
1201  if (!is_incremental_marking(objspace) && RVALUE_REMEMBERED(obj)) {
1202  CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARKING_BITS(obj), obj);
1203  }
1204 
1205  RVALUE_DEMOTE_RAW(objspace, obj);
1206 
1207  if (RVALUE_MARKED(obj)) {
1208  objspace->rgengc.old_objects--;
1209  }
1210 
1211  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1212 }
1213 
1214 static inline void
1215 RVALUE_AGE_RESET_RAW(VALUE obj)
1216 {
1217  RBASIC(obj)->flags = RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE_SET(RBASIC(obj)->flags, 0);
1218 }
1219 
1220 static inline void
1221 RVALUE_AGE_RESET(VALUE obj)
1222 {
1223  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1224  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(!RVALUE_OLD_P(obj));
1225  RVALUE_AGE_RESET_RAW(obj);
1226  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1227 }
1228 
1229 static inline int
1230 RVALUE_BLACK_P(VALUE obj)
1231 {
1232  return RVALUE_MARKED(obj) && !RVALUE_MARKING(obj);
1233 }
1234 
1235 #if 0
1236 static inline int
1237 RVALUE_GREY_P(VALUE obj)
1238 {
1239  return RVALUE_MARKED(obj) && RVALUE_MARKING(obj);
1240 }
1241 #endif
1242 
1243 static inline int
1244 RVALUE_WHITE_P(VALUE obj)
1245 {
1246  return RVALUE_MARKED(obj) == FALSE;
1247 }
1248 
1249 #endif /* USE_RGENGC */
1250 
1251 /*
1252  --------------------------- ObjectSpace -----------------------------
1253 */
1254 
1255 #if defined(ENABLE_VM_OBJSPACE) && ENABLE_VM_OBJSPACE
1256 rb_objspace_t *
1257 rb_objspace_alloc(void)
1258 {
1259  rb_objspace_t *objspace = calloc(1, sizeof(rb_objspace_t));
1260  malloc_limit = gc_params.malloc_limit_min;
1261 
1262  return objspace;
1263 }
1264 #endif
1265 
1266 #if defined(ENABLE_VM_OBJSPACE) && ENABLE_VM_OBJSPACE
1267 static void free_stack_chunks(mark_stack_t *);
1268 static void heap_page_free(rb_objspace_t *objspace, struct heap_page *page);
1269 
1270 void
1271 rb_objspace_free(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
1272 {
1273  if (is_lazy_sweeping(heap_eden))
1274  rb_bug("lazy sweeping underway when freeing object space");
1275 
1276  if (objspace->profile.records) {
1277  free(objspace->profile.records);
1278  objspace->profile.records = 0;
1279  }
1280 
1281  if (global_list) {
1282  struct gc_list *list, *next;
1283  for (list = global_list; list; list = next) {
1284  next = list->next;
1285  xfree(list);
1286  }
1287  }
1288  if (heap_pages_sorted) {
1289  size_t i;
1290  for (i = 0; i < heap_allocated_pages; ++i) {
1291  heap_page_free(objspace, heap_pages_sorted[i]);
1292  }
1293  free(heap_pages_sorted);
1294  heap_allocated_pages = 0;
1295  heap_pages_sorted_length = 0;
1296  heap_pages_lomem = 0;
1297  heap_pages_himem = 0;
1298 
1299  objspace->eden_heap.page_length = 0;
1300  objspace->eden_heap.total_slots = 0;
1301  objspace->eden_heap.pages = NULL;
1302  }
1303  free_stack_chunks(&objspace->mark_stack);
1304  free(objspace);
1305 }
1306 #endif
1307 
1308 static void
1309 heap_pages_expand_sorted(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
1310 {
1311  size_t next_length = heap_allocatable_pages;
1312  next_length += heap_eden->page_length;
1313  next_length += heap_tomb->page_length;
1314 
1315  if (next_length > heap_pages_sorted_length) {
1316  struct heap_page **sorted;
1317  size_t size = next_length * sizeof(struct heap_page *);
1318 
1319  gc_report(3, objspace, "heap_pages_expand_sorted: next_length: %d, size: %d\n", (int)next_length, (int)size);
1320 
1321  if (heap_pages_sorted_length > 0) {
1322  sorted = (struct heap_page **)realloc(heap_pages_sorted, size);
1323  if (sorted) heap_pages_sorted = sorted;
1324  }
1325  else {
1326  sorted = heap_pages_sorted = (struct heap_page **)malloc(size);
1327  }
1328 
1329  if (sorted == 0) {
1330  rb_memerror();
1331  }
1332 
1333  heap_pages_sorted_length = next_length;
1334  }
1335 }
1336 
1337 static inline void
1338 heap_page_add_freeobj(rb_objspace_t *objspace, struct heap_page *page, VALUE obj)
1339 {
1340  RVALUE *p = (RVALUE *)obj;
1341  p->as.free.flags = 0;
1342  p->as.free.next = page->freelist;
1343  page->freelist = p;
1344 
1345  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE && !is_pointer_to_heap(objspace, p)) {
1346  rb_bug("heap_page_add_freeobj: %p is not rvalue.", p);
1347  }
1348 
1349  gc_report(3, objspace, "heap_page_add_freeobj: add %p to freelist\n", (void *)obj);
1350 }
1351 
1352 static inline void
1353 heap_add_freepage(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap, struct heap_page *page)
1354 {
1355  if (page->freelist) {
1356  page->free_next = heap->free_pages;
1357  heap->free_pages = page;
1358  }
1359 }
1360 
1361 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
1362 static inline int
1363 heap_add_poolpage(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap, struct heap_page *page)
1364 {
1365  if (page->freelist) {
1366  page->free_next = heap->pooled_pages;
1367  heap->pooled_pages = page;
1368  objspace->rincgc.pooled_slots += page->free_slots;
1369  return TRUE;
1370  }
1371  else {
1372  return FALSE;
1373  }
1374 }
1375 #endif
1376 
1377 static void
1378 heap_unlink_page(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap, struct heap_page *page)
1379 {
1380  if (page->prev) page->prev->next = page->next;
1381  if (page->next) page->next->prev = page->prev;
1382  if (heap->pages == page) heap->pages = page->next;
1383  page->prev = NULL;
1384  page->next = NULL;
1385  page->heap = NULL;
1386  heap->page_length--;
1387  heap->total_slots -= page->total_slots;
1388 }
1389 
1390 static void
1391 heap_page_free(rb_objspace_t *objspace, struct heap_page *page)
1392 {
1393  heap_allocated_pages--;
1394  objspace->profile.total_freed_pages++;
1395  aligned_free(page->body);
1396  free(page);
1397 }
1398 
1399 static void
1400 heap_pages_free_unused_pages(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
1401 {
1402  size_t i, j;
1403 
1404  if (heap_tomb->pages && heap_pages_swept_slots > heap_pages_max_free_slots) {
1405  for (i = j = 1; j < heap_allocated_pages; i++) {
1406  struct heap_page *page = heap_pages_sorted[i];
1407 
1408  if (page->heap == heap_tomb && page->free_slots == page->total_slots) {
1409  if (heap_pages_swept_slots - page->total_slots > heap_pages_max_free_slots) {
1410  if (0) fprintf(stderr, "heap_pages_free_unused_pages: %d free page %p, heap_pages_swept_slots: %d, heap_pages_max_free_slots: %d\n",
1411  (int)i, page, (int)heap_pages_swept_slots, (int)heap_pages_max_free_slots);
1412  heap_pages_swept_slots -= page->total_slots;
1413  heap_unlink_page(objspace, heap_tomb, page);
1414  heap_page_free(objspace, page);
1415  continue;
1416  }
1417  else if (i == j) {
1418  return; /* no need to check rest pages */
1419  }
1420  }
1421  if (i != j) {
1422  heap_pages_sorted[j] = page;
1423  }
1424  j++;
1425  }
1426  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(j == heap_allocated_pages);
1427  }
1428 }
1429 
1430 static struct heap_page *
1431 heap_page_allocate(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
1432 {
1433  RVALUE *start, *end, *p;
1434  struct heap_page *page;
1435  struct heap_page_body *page_body = 0;
1436  size_t hi, lo, mid;
1437  int limit = HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT;
1438 
1439  /* assign heap_page body (contains heap_page_header and RVALUEs) */
1440  page_body = (struct heap_page_body *)aligned_malloc(HEAP_ALIGN, HEAP_SIZE);
1441  if (page_body == 0) {
1442  rb_memerror();
1443  }
1444 
1445  /* assign heap_page entry */
1446  page = (struct heap_page *)calloc(1, sizeof(struct heap_page));
1447  if (page == 0) {
1448  aligned_free(page_body);
1449  rb_memerror();
1450  }
1451 
1452  page->body = page_body;
1453 
1454  /* setup heap_pages_sorted */
1455  lo = 0;
1456  hi = heap_allocated_pages;
1457  while (lo < hi) {
1458  struct heap_page *mid_page;
1459 
1460  mid = (lo + hi) / 2;
1461  mid_page = heap_pages_sorted[mid];
1462  if (mid_page->body < page_body) {
1463  lo = mid + 1;
1464  }
1465  else if (mid_page->body > page_body) {
1466  hi = mid;
1467  }
1468  else {
1469  rb_bug("same heap page is allocated: %p at %"PRIuVALUE, (void *)page_body, (VALUE)mid);
1470  }
1471  }
1472  if (hi < heap_allocated_pages) {
1473  MEMMOVE(&heap_pages_sorted[hi+1], &heap_pages_sorted[hi], struct heap_page_header*, heap_allocated_pages - hi);
1474  }
1475 
1476  heap_pages_sorted[hi] = page;
1477 
1478  heap_allocated_pages++;
1479  objspace->profile.total_allocated_pages++;
1480 
1481  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(heap_allocated_pages <= heap_pages_sorted_length);
1482 
1483  /* adjust obj_limit (object number available in this page) */
1484  start = (RVALUE*)((VALUE)page_body + sizeof(struct heap_page_header));
1485  if ((VALUE)start % sizeof(RVALUE) != 0) {
1486  int delta = (int)(sizeof(RVALUE) - ((VALUE)start % sizeof(RVALUE)));
1487  start = (RVALUE*)((VALUE)start + delta);
1488  limit = (HEAP_SIZE - (int)((VALUE)start - (VALUE)page_body))/(int)sizeof(RVALUE);
1489  }
1490  end = start + limit;
1491 
1492  if (heap_pages_lomem == 0 || heap_pages_lomem > start) heap_pages_lomem = start;
1493  if (heap_pages_himem < end) heap_pages_himem = end;
1494 
1495  page->start = start;
1496  page->total_slots = limit;
1497  page_body->header.page = page;
1498 
1499  for (p = start; p != end; p++) {
1500  gc_report(3, objspace, "assign_heap_page: %p is added to freelist\n", p);
1501  heap_page_add_freeobj(objspace, page, (VALUE)p);
1502  }
1503  page->free_slots = limit;
1504 
1505  return page;
1506 }
1507 
1508 static struct heap_page *
1509 heap_page_resurrect(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
1510 {
1511  struct heap_page *page;
1512 
1513  if ((page = heap_tomb->pages) != NULL) {
1514  heap_unlink_page(objspace, heap_tomb, page);
1515  return page;
1516  }
1517  return NULL;
1518 }
1519 
1520 static struct heap_page *
1521 heap_page_create(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
1522 {
1523  struct heap_page *page = heap_page_resurrect(objspace);
1524  const char *method = "recycle";
1525  if (page == NULL) {
1526  page = heap_page_allocate(objspace);
1527  method = "allocate";
1528  }
1529  if (0) fprintf(stderr, "heap_page_create: %s - %p, heap_allocated_pages: %d, heap_allocated_pages: %d, tomb->page_length: %d\n",
1530  method, page, (int)heap_pages_sorted_length, (int)heap_allocated_pages, (int)heap_tomb->page_length);
1531  return page;
1532 }
1533 
1534 static void
1535 heap_add_page(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap, struct heap_page *page)
1536 {
1537  page->heap = heap;
1538  page->next = heap->pages;
1539  if (heap->pages) heap->pages->prev = page;
1540  heap->pages = page;
1541  heap->page_length++;
1542  heap->total_slots += page->total_slots;
1543 }
1544 
1545 static void
1546 heap_assign_page(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
1547 {
1548  struct heap_page *page = heap_page_create(objspace);
1549  heap_add_page(objspace, heap, page);
1550  heap_add_freepage(objspace, heap, page);
1551 }
1552 
1553 static void
1554 heap_add_pages(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap, size_t add)
1555 {
1556  size_t i;
1557 
1558  heap_allocatable_pages = add;
1559  heap_pages_expand_sorted(objspace);
1560  for (i = 0; i < add; i++) {
1561  heap_assign_page(objspace, heap);
1562  }
1563  heap_allocatable_pages = 0;
1564 }
1565 
1566 static size_t
1567 heap_extend_pages(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
1568 {
1569  size_t used = heap_allocated_pages - heap_tomb->page_length;
1570  size_t next_used_limit = (size_t)(used * gc_params.growth_factor);
1571 
1572  if (gc_params.growth_max_slots > 0) {
1573  size_t max_used_limit = (size_t)(used + gc_params.growth_max_slots/HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT);
1574  if (next_used_limit > max_used_limit) next_used_limit = max_used_limit;
1575  }
1576 
1577  return next_used_limit - used;
1578 }
1579 
1580 static void
1581 heap_set_increment(rb_objspace_t *objspace, size_t additional_pages)
1582 {
1583  size_t used = heap_eden->page_length;
1584  size_t next_used_limit = used + additional_pages;
1585 
1586  if (next_used_limit == heap_allocated_pages) next_used_limit++;
1587 
1588  heap_allocatable_pages = next_used_limit - used;
1589  heap_pages_expand_sorted(objspace);
1590 
1591  gc_report(1, objspace, "heap_set_increment: heap_allocatable_pages is %d\n", (int)heap_allocatable_pages);
1592 }
1593 
1594 static int
1595 heap_increment(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
1596 {
1597  if (heap_allocatable_pages > 0) {
1598  gc_report(1, objspace, "heap_increment: heap_pages_sorted_length: %d, heap_pages_inc: %d, heap->page_length: %d\n",
1599  (int)heap_pages_sorted_length, (int)heap_allocatable_pages, (int)heap->page_length);
1600  heap_allocatable_pages--;
1601  heap_assign_page(objspace, heap);
1602  return TRUE;
1603  }
1604  return FALSE;
1605 }
1606 
1607 static void
1608 heap_prepare(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
1609 {
1610  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(heap->free_pages == NULL);
1611 
1612 #if GC_ENABLE_LAZY_SWEEP
1613  if (is_lazy_sweeping(heap)) {
1614  gc_sweep_continue(objspace, heap);
1615  }
1616 #endif
1617 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
1618  else if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
1619  gc_marks_continue(objspace, heap);
1620  }
1621 #endif
1622 
1623  if (heap->free_pages == NULL &&
1624  (will_be_incremental_marking(objspace) || heap_increment(objspace, heap) == FALSE) &&
1625  gc_start(objspace, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, GPR_FLAG_NEWOBJ) == FALSE) {
1626  rb_memerror();
1627  }
1628 }
1629 
1630 static RVALUE *
1631 heap_get_freeobj_from_next_freepage(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
1632 {
1633  struct heap_page *page;
1634  RVALUE *p;
1635 
1636  while (UNLIKELY(heap->free_pages == NULL)) {
1637  heap_prepare(objspace, heap);
1638  }
1639  page = heap->free_pages;
1640  heap->free_pages = page->free_next;
1641  heap->using_page = page;
1642 
1643  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(page->free_slots != 0);
1644  p = page->freelist;
1645  page->freelist = NULL;
1646  page->free_slots = 0;
1647  return p;
1648 }
1649 
1650 static inline VALUE
1651 heap_get_freeobj(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
1652 {
1653  RVALUE *p = heap->freelist;
1654 
1655  while (1) {
1656  if (LIKELY(p != NULL)) {
1657  heap->freelist = p->as.free.next;
1658  return (VALUE)p;
1659  }
1660  else {
1661  p = heap_get_freeobj_from_next_freepage(objspace, heap);
1662  }
1663  }
1664 }

1666 void
1667 rb_objspace_set_event_hook(const rb_event_flag_t event)
1668 {
1669  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
1670  objspace->hook_events = event & RUBY_INTERNAL_EVENT_OBJSPACE_MASK;
1671 }
1672 
1673 static void
1674 gc_event_hook_body(rb_thread_t *th, rb_objspace_t *objspace, const rb_event_flag_t event, VALUE data)
1675 {
1676  EXEC_EVENT_HOOK(th, event, th->cfp->self, 0, 0, data);
1677 }
1678 
1679 #define gc_event_hook(objspace, event, data) do { \
1680  if (UNLIKELY((objspace)->hook_events & (event))) { \
1681  gc_event_hook_body(GET_THREAD(), (objspace), (event), (data)); \
1682  } \
1683 } while (0)
1684 
1685 static VALUE
1686 newobj_of(VALUE klass, VALUE flags, VALUE v1, VALUE v2, VALUE v3)
1687 {
1688  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
1689  VALUE obj;
1690 
1691 #if GC_DEBUG_STRESS_TO_CLASS
1692  if (UNLIKELY(stress_to_class)) {
1693  long i, cnt = RARRAY_LEN(stress_to_class);
1694  const VALUE *ptr = RARRAY_CONST_PTR(stress_to_class);
1695  for (i = 0; i < cnt; ++i) {
1696  if (klass == ptr[i]) rb_memerror();
1697  }
1698  }
1699 #endif
1700 
1701  if (UNLIKELY(during_gc || ruby_gc_stressful)) {
1702  if (during_gc) {
1703  dont_gc = 1;
1704  during_gc = 0;
1705  rb_bug("object allocation during garbage collection phase");
1706  }
1707 
1708  if (ruby_gc_stressful) {
1709  if (!garbage_collect(objspace, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, GPR_FLAG_NEWOBJ)) {
1710  rb_memerror();
1711  }
1712  }
1713  }
1714 
1715  obj = heap_get_freeobj(objspace, heap_eden);
1716 
1717  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE > 0) assert(BUILTIN_TYPE(obj) == T_NONE);
1718 
1719  /* OBJSETUP */
1720  RBASIC(obj)->flags = flags & ~FL_WB_PROTECTED;
1721  RBASIC_SET_CLASS_RAW(obj, klass);
1722  if (rb_safe_level() >= 3) FL_SET((obj), FL_TAINT);
1723  RANY(obj)->as.values.v1 = v1;
1724  RANY(obj)->as.values.v2 = v2;
1725  RANY(obj)->as.values.v3 = v3;
1726 
1727 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE
1728  assert(RVALUE_MARKED(obj) == FALSE);
1729  assert(RVALUE_MARKING(obj) == FALSE);
1730  assert(RVALUE_OLD_P(obj) == FALSE);
1731  assert(RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj) == FALSE);
1732 
1733  if (flags & FL_PROMOTED1) {
1734  if (RVALUE_AGE(obj) != 2) rb_bug("newobj: %s of age (%d) != 2.", obj_info(obj), RVALUE_AGE(obj));
1735  }
1736  else {
1737  if (RVALUE_AGE(obj) > 0) rb_bug("newobj: %s of age (%d) > 0.", obj_info(obj), RVALUE_AGE(obj));
1738  }
1739  if (rgengc_remembered(objspace, (VALUE)obj)) rb_bug("newobj: %s is remembered.", obj_info(obj));
1740 #endif
1741 
1742 #if USE_RGENGC
1743  if ((flags & FL_WB_PROTECTED) == 0) {
1744  MARK_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_WB_UNPROTECTED_BITS(obj), obj);
1745  }
1746 #endif
1747 
1748 #if RGENGC_PROFILE
1749  if (flags & FL_WB_PROTECTED) {
1750  objspace->profile.total_generated_normal_object_count++;
1751 #if RGENGC_PROFILE >= 2
1752  objspace->profile.generated_normal_object_count_types[BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)]++;
1753 #endif
1754  }
1755  else {
1756  objspace->profile.total_generated_shady_object_count++;
1757 #if RGENGC_PROFILE >= 2
1758  objspace->profile.generated_shady_object_count_types[BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)]++;
1759 #endif
1760  }
1761 #endif
1762 
1763 #if GC_DEBUG
1764  RANY(obj)->file = rb_sourcefile();
1765  RANY(obj)->line = rb_sourceline();
1766  assert(!SPECIAL_CONST_P(obj)); /* check alignment */
1767 #endif
1768 
1769  objspace->total_allocated_objects++;
1770  gc_event_hook(objspace, RUBY_INTERNAL_EVENT_NEWOBJ, obj);
1771  gc_report(5, objspace, "newobj: %s\n", obj_info(obj));
1772 
1773 #if RGENGC_OLD_NEWOBJ_CHECK > 0
1774  {
1775  static int newobj_cnt = RGENGC_OLD_NEWOBJ_CHECK;
1776 
1777  if (!is_incremental_marking(objspace) &&
1778  flags & FL_WB_PROTECTED && /* do not promote WB unprotected objects */
1779  ! RB_TYPE_P(obj, T_ARRAY)) { /* array.c assumes that allocated objects are new */
1780  if (--newobj_cnt == 0) {
1781  newobj_cnt = RGENGC_OLD_NEWOBJ_CHECK;
1782 
1783  gc_mark_set(objspace, obj);
1784  RVALUE_AGE_SET_OLD(objspace, obj);
1785 
1786  rb_gc_writebarrier_remember(obj);
1787  }
1788  }
1789  }
1790 #endif
1791  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
1792  return obj;
1793 }

1898 static inline int
1899 is_pointer_to_heap(rb_objspace_t *objspace, void *ptr)
1900 {
1901  register RVALUE *p = RANY(ptr);
1902  register struct heap_page *page;
1903  register size_t hi, lo, mid;
1904 
1905  if (p < heap_pages_lomem || p > heap_pages_himem) return FALSE;
1906  if ((VALUE)p % sizeof(RVALUE) != 0) return FALSE;
1907 
1908  /* check if p looks like a pointer using bsearch*/
1909  lo = 0;
1910  hi = heap_allocated_pages;
1911  while (lo < hi) {
1912  mid = (lo + hi) / 2;
1913  page = heap_pages_sorted[mid];
1914  if (page->start <= p) {
1915  if (p < page->start + page->total_slots) {
1916  return TRUE;
1917  }
1918  lo = mid + 1;
1919  }
1920  else {
1921  hi = mid;
1922  }
1923  }
1924  return FALSE;
1925 }

1951 make_zombie(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj, void (*dfree)(void *), void *data)

1968 static int
1969 obj_free(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
1970 {
1971  gc_event_hook(objspace, RUBY_INTERNAL_EVENT_FREEOBJ, obj);
1972 
1973  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)) {
1974  case T_NIL:
1975  case T_FIXNUM:
1976  case T_TRUE:
1977  case T_FALSE:
1978  rb_bug("obj_free() called for broken object");
1979  break;
1980  }
1981 
1982  if (FL_TEST(obj, FL_EXIVAR)) {
1983  rb_free_generic_ivar((VALUE)obj);
1984  FL_UNSET(obj, FL_EXIVAR);
1985  }
1986 
1987 #if USE_RGENGC
1988  if (RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj)) CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_WB_UNPROTECTED_BITS(obj), obj);
1989 
1990 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE
1991 #define CHECK(x) if (x(obj) != FALSE) rb_bug("obj_free: " #x "(%s) != FALSE", obj_info(obj))
1992  CHECK(RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED);
1993  CHECK(RVALUE_MARKED);
1994  CHECK(RVALUE_MARKING);
1995  CHECK(RVALUE_UNCOLLECTIBLE);
1996 #undef CHECK
1997 #endif
1998 #endif
1999 
2000  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)) {
2001  case T_OBJECT:
2002  if (!(RANY(obj)->as.basic.flags & ROBJECT_EMBED) &&
2003  RANY(obj)->as.object.as.heap.ivptr) {
2004  xfree(RANY(obj)->as.object.as.heap.ivptr);
2005  }
2006  break;
2007  case T_MODULE:
2008  case T_CLASS:
2009  rb_free_m_tbl(RCLASS_M_TBL(obj));
2010  if (RCLASS_IV_TBL(obj)) {
2011  st_free_table(RCLASS_IV_TBL(obj));
2012  }
2013  if (RCLASS_CONST_TBL(obj)) {
2014  rb_free_const_table(RCLASS_CONST_TBL(obj));
2015  }
2016  if (RCLASS_IV_INDEX_TBL(obj)) {
2017  st_free_table(RCLASS_IV_INDEX_TBL(obj));
2018  }
2019  if (RCLASS_EXT(obj)->subclasses) {
2020  if (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj) == T_MODULE) {
2021  rb_class_detach_module_subclasses(obj);
2022  }
2023  else {
2024  rb_class_detach_subclasses(obj);
2025  }
2026  RCLASS_EXT(obj)->subclasses = NULL;
2027  }
2028  rb_class_remove_from_module_subclasses(obj);
2029  rb_class_remove_from_super_subclasses(obj);
2030  if (RANY(obj)->as.klass.ptr)
2031  xfree(RANY(obj)->as.klass.ptr);
2032  RANY(obj)->as.klass.ptr = NULL;
2033  break;
2034  case T_STRING:
2035  rb_str_free(obj);
2036  break;
2037  case T_ARRAY:
2038  rb_ary_free(obj);
2039  break;
2040  case T_HASH:
2041  if (RANY(obj)->as.hash.ntbl) {
2042  st_free_table(RANY(obj)->as.hash.ntbl);
2043  }
2044  break;
2045  case T_REGEXP:
2046  if (RANY(obj)->as.regexp.ptr) {
2047  onig_free(RANY(obj)->as.regexp.ptr);
2048  }
2049  break;
2050  case T_DATA:
2051  if (DATA_PTR(obj)) {
2052  int free_immediately = FALSE;
2053  void (*dfree)(void *);
2054  void *data = DATA_PTR(obj);
2055 
2056  if (RTYPEDDATA_P(obj)) {
2057  free_immediately = (RANY(obj)->as.typeddata.type->flags & RUBY_TYPED_FREE_IMMEDIATELY) != 0;
2058  dfree = RANY(obj)->as.typeddata.type->function.dfree;
2059  if (0 && free_immediately == 0) {
2060  /* to expose non-free-immediate T_DATA */
2061  fprintf(stderr, "not immediate -> %s\n", RANY(obj)->as.typeddata.type->wrap_struct_name);
2062  }
2063  }
2064  else {
2065  dfree = RANY(obj)->as.data.dfree;
2066  }
2067 
2068  if (dfree) {
2069  if (dfree == RUBY_DEFAULT_FREE) {
2070  xfree(data);
2071  }
2072  else if (free_immediately) {
2073  (*dfree)(data);
2074  }
2075  else {
2076  make_zombie(objspace, obj, dfree, data);
2077  return 1;
2078  }
2079  }
2080  }
2081  break;
2082  case T_MATCH:
2083  if (RANY(obj)->as.match.rmatch) {
2084  struct rmatch *rm = RANY(obj)->as.match.rmatch;
2085  onig_region_free(&rm->regs, 0);
2086  if (rm->char_offset)
2087  xfree(rm->char_offset);
2088  xfree(rm);
2089  }
2090  break;
2091  case T_FILE:
2092  if (RANY(obj)->as.file.fptr) {
2093  make_io_zombie(objspace, obj);
2094  return 1;
2095  }
2096  break;
2097  case T_RATIONAL:
2098  case T_COMPLEX:
2099  break;
2100  case T_ICLASS:
2101  /* Basically , T_ICLASS shares table with the module */
2102  if (FL_TEST(obj, RICLASS_IS_ORIGIN)) {
2103  rb_free_m_tbl(RCLASS_M_TBL(obj));
2104  }
2105  if (RCLASS_EXT(obj)->subclasses) {
2106  rb_class_detach_subclasses(obj);
2107  RCLASS_EXT(obj)->subclasses = NULL;
2108  }
2109  rb_class_remove_from_module_subclasses(obj);
2110  rb_class_remove_from_super_subclasses(obj);
2111  xfree(RANY(obj)->as.klass.ptr);
2112  RANY(obj)->as.klass.ptr = NULL;
2113  break;
2114 
2115  case T_FLOAT:
2116  break;
2117 
2118  case T_BIGNUM:
2119  if (!(RBASIC(obj)->flags & BIGNUM_EMBED_FLAG) && BIGNUM_DIGITS(obj)) {
2120  xfree(BIGNUM_DIGITS(obj));
2121  }
2122  break;
2123 
2124  case T_NODE:
2125  rb_gc_free_node(obj);
2126  break; /* no need to free iv_tbl */
2127 
2128  case T_STRUCT:
2129  if ((RBASIC(obj)->flags & RSTRUCT_EMBED_LEN_MASK) == 0 &&
2130  RANY(obj)->as.rstruct.as.heap.ptr) {
2131  xfree((void *)RANY(obj)->as.rstruct.as.heap.ptr);
2132  }
2133  break;
2134 
2135  case T_SYMBOL:
2136  {
2137  rb_gc_free_dsymbol(obj);
2138  }
2139  break;
2140 
2141  case T_IMEMO:
2142  {
2143  if (imemo_type(obj) == imemo_ment) {
2144  rb_free_method_entry(&RANY(obj)->as.imemo.ment);
2145  }
2146  }
2147  break;
2148 
2149  default:
2150  rb_bug("gc_sweep(): unknown data type 0x%x(%p) 0x%"PRIxVALUE,
2151  BUILTIN_TYPE(obj), (void*)obj, RBASIC(obj)->flags);
2152  }
2153 
2154  if (FL_TEST(obj, FL_FINALIZE)) {
2155  make_zombie(objspace, obj, 0, 0);
2156  return 1;
2157  }
2158  else {
2159  return 0;
2160  }
2161 }
2162 
2163 void
2164 Init_heap(void)
2165 {
2166  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
2167 
2168  gc_stress_set(objspace, ruby_initial_gc_stress);
2169 
2170 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
2171  objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit = gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_min;
2172 #endif
2173 
2174  heap_add_pages(objspace, heap_eden, gc_params.heap_init_slots / HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT);
2175  init_mark_stack(&objspace->mark_stack);
2176 
2177 #ifdef USE_SIGALTSTACK
2178  {
2179  /* altstack of another threads are allocated in another place */
2180  rb_thread_t *th = GET_THREAD();
2181  void *tmp = th->altstack;
2182  th->altstack = malloc(rb_sigaltstack_size());
2183  free(tmp); /* free previously allocated area */
2184  }
2185 #endif
2186 
2187  objspace->profile.invoke_time = getrusage_time();
2188  finalizer_table = st_init_numtable();
2189 }
2190 
2191 typedef int each_obj_callback(void *, void *, size_t, void *);
2192 
2193 struct each_obj_args {
2194  each_obj_callback *callback;
2195  void *data;
2196 };
2197 
2198 static VALUE
2199 objspace_each_objects(VALUE arg)
2200 {
2201  size_t i;
2202  struct heap_page_body *last_body = 0;
2203  struct heap_page *page;
2204  RVALUE *pstart, *pend;
2205  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
2206  struct each_obj_args *args = (struct each_obj_args *)arg;
2207 
2208  i = 0;
2209  while (i < heap_allocated_pages) {
2210  while (0 < i && last_body < heap_pages_sorted[i-1]->body) i--;
2211  while (i < heap_allocated_pages && heap_pages_sorted[i]->body <= last_body) i++;
2212  if (heap_allocated_pages <= i) break;
2213 
2214  page = heap_pages_sorted[i];
2215  last_body = page->body;
2216 
2217  pstart = page->start;
2218  pend = pstart + page->total_slots;
2219 
2220  if ((*args->callback)(pstart, pend, sizeof(RVALUE), args->data)) {
2221  break;
2222  }
2223  }
2224 
2225  return Qnil;
2226 }
2227 
2228 static VALUE
2229 incremental_enable(void)
2230 {
2231  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
2232 
2233  objspace->flags.dont_incremental = FALSE;
2234  return Qnil;
2235 }
2236 
2237 /*
2238  * rb_objspace_each_objects() is special C API to walk through
2239  * Ruby object space. This C API is too difficult to use it.
2240  * To be frank, you should not use it. Or you need to read the
2241  * source code of this function and understand what this function does.
2242  *
2243  * 'callback' will be called several times (the number of heap page,
2244  * at current implementation) with:
2245  * vstart: a pointer to the first living object of the heap_page.
2246  * vend: a pointer to next to the valid heap_page area.
2247  * stride: a distance to next VALUE.
2248  *
2249  * If callback() returns non-zero, the iteration will be stopped.
2250  *
2251  * This is a sample callback code to iterate liveness objects:
2252  *
2253  * int
2254  * sample_callback(void *vstart, void *vend, int stride, void *data) {
2255  * VALUE v = (VALUE)vstart;
2256  * for (; v != (VALUE)vend; v += stride) {
2257  * if (RBASIC(v)->flags) { // liveness check
2258  * // do something with live object 'v'
2259  * }
2260  * return 0; // continue to iteration
2261  * }
2262  *
2263  * Note: 'vstart' is not a top of heap_page. This point the first
2264  * living object to grasp at least one object to avoid GC issue.
2265  * This means that you can not walk through all Ruby object page
2266  * including freed object page.
2267  *
2268  * Note: On this implementation, 'stride' is same as sizeof(RVALUE).
2269  * However, there are possibilities to pass variable values with
2270  * 'stride' with some reasons. You must use stride instead of
2271  * use some constant value in the iteration.
2272  */
2273 void
2274 rb_objspace_each_objects(each_obj_callback *callback, void *data)
2275 {
2276  struct each_obj_args args;
2277  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
2278  int prev_dont_incremental = objspace->flags.dont_incremental;
2279 
2280  gc_rest(objspace);
2281  objspace->flags.dont_incremental = TRUE;
2282 
2283  args.callback = callback;
2284  args.data = data;
2285 
2286  if (prev_dont_incremental) {
2287  objspace_each_objects((VALUE)&args);
2288  }
2289  else {
2290  rb_ensure(objspace_each_objects, (VALUE)&args, incremental_enable, Qnil);
2291  }
2292 }
2293 
2294 void
2295 rb_objspace_each_objects_without_setup(each_obj_callback *callback, void *data)
2296 {
2297  struct each_obj_args args;
2298  args.callback = callback;
2299  args.data = data;
2300 
2301  objspace_each_objects((VALUE)&args);
2302 }
2303 
2304 struct os_each_struct {
2305  size_t num;
2306  VALUE of;
2307 };
2308 
2309 static int
2310 internal_object_p(VALUE obj)
2311 {
2312  RVALUE *p = (RVALUE *)obj;
2313 
2314  if (p->as.basic.flags) {
2315  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(p)) {
2316  case T_NONE:
2317  case T_IMEMO:
2318  case T_ICLASS:
2319  case T_NODE:
2320  case T_ZOMBIE:
2321  break;
2322  case T_CLASS:
2323  if (FL_TEST(p, FL_SINGLETON))
2324  break;
2325  default:
2326  if (!p->as.basic.klass) break;
2327  return 0;
2328  }
2329  }
2330  return 1;
2331 }
2332 
2333 int
2334 rb_objspace_internal_object_p(VALUE obj)
2335 {
2336  return internal_object_p(obj);
2337 }
2338 
2339 static int
2340 os_obj_of_i(void *vstart, void *vend, size_t stride, void *data)
2341 {
2342  struct os_each_struct *oes = (struct os_each_struct *)data;
2343  RVALUE *p = (RVALUE *)vstart, *pend = (RVALUE *)vend;
2344 
2345  for (; p != pend; p++) {
2346  volatile VALUE v = (VALUE)p;
2347  if (!internal_object_p(v)) {
2348  if (!oes->of || rb_obj_is_kind_of(v, oes->of)) {
2349  rb_yield(v);
2350  oes->num++;
2351  }
2352  }
2353  }
2354 
2355  return 0;
2356 }
2357 
2358 static VALUE
2359 os_obj_of(VALUE of)
2360 {
2361  struct os_each_struct oes;
2362 
2363  oes.num = 0;
2364  oes.of = of;
2365  rb_objspace_each_objects(os_obj_of_i, &oes);
2366  return SIZET2NUM(oes.num);
2367 }
2368 
2369 /*
2370  * call-seq:
2371  * ObjectSpace.each_object([module]) {|obj| ... } -> fixnum
2372  * ObjectSpace.each_object([module]) -> an_enumerator
2373  *
2374  * Calls the block once for each living, nonimmediate object in this
2375  * Ruby process. If <i>module</i> is specified, calls the block
2376  * for only those classes or modules that match (or are a subclass of)
2377  * <i>module</i>. Returns the number of objects found. Immediate
2378  * objects (<code>Fixnum</code>s, <code>Symbol</code>s
2379  * <code>true</code>, <code>false</code>, and <code>nil</code>) are
2380  * never returned. In the example below, <code>each_object</code>
2381  * returns both the numbers we defined and several constants defined in
2382  * the <code>Math</code> module.
2383  *
2384  * If no block is given, an enumerator is returned instead.
2385  *
2386  * a = 102.7
2387  * b = 95 # Won't be returned
2388  * c = 12345678987654321
2389  * count = ObjectSpace.each_object(Numeric) {|x| p x }
2390  * puts "Total count: #{count}"
2391  *
2392  * <em>produces:</em>
2393  *
2394  * 12345678987654321
2395  * 102.7
2396  * 2.71828182845905
2397  * 3.14159265358979
2398  * 2.22044604925031e-16
2399  * 1.7976931348623157e+308
2400  * 2.2250738585072e-308
2401  * Total count: 7
2402  *
2403  */
2404 
2405 static VALUE
2406 os_each_obj(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE os)
2407 {
2408  VALUE of;
2409 
2410  if (argc == 0) {
2411  of = 0;
2412  }
2413  else {
2414  rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "01", &of);
2415  }
2416  RETURN_ENUMERATOR(os, 1, &of);
2417  return os_obj_of(of);
2418 }
2419 
2420 /*
2421  * call-seq:
2422  * ObjectSpace.undefine_finalizer(obj)
2423  *
2424  * Removes all finalizers for <i>obj</i>.
2425  *
2426  */
2427 
2428 static VALUE
2429 undefine_final(VALUE os, VALUE obj)
2430 {
2431  return rb_undefine_finalizer(obj);
2432 }
2433 
2434 VALUE
2435 rb_undefine_finalizer(VALUE obj)
2436 {
2437  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
2438  st_data_t data = obj;
2439  rb_check_frozen(obj);
2440  st_delete(finalizer_table, &data, 0);
2441  FL_UNSET(obj, FL_FINALIZE);
2442  return obj;
2443 }
2444 
2445 static void
2446 should_be_callable(VALUE block)
2447 {
2448  if (!rb_obj_respond_to(block, rb_intern("call"), TRUE)) {
2449  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "wrong type argument %"PRIsVALUE" (should be callable)",
2450  rb_obj_class(block));
2451  }
2452 }
2453 static void
2454 should_be_finalizable(VALUE obj)
2455 {
2456  if (!FL_ABLE(obj)) {
2457  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "cannot define finalizer for %s",
2458  rb_obj_classname(obj));
2459  }
2460  rb_check_frozen(obj);
2461 }
2462 
2463 /*
2464  * call-seq:
2465  * ObjectSpace.define_finalizer(obj, aProc=proc())
2466  *
2467  * Adds <i>aProc</i> as a finalizer, to be called after <i>obj</i>
2468  * was destroyed.
2469  *
2470  */
2471 
2472 static VALUE
2473 define_final(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE os)
2474 {
2475  VALUE obj, block;
2476 
2477  rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "11", &obj, &block);
2478  should_be_finalizable(obj);
2479  if (argc == 1) {
2480  block = rb_block_proc();
2481  }
2482  else {
2483  should_be_callable(block);
2484  }
2485 
2486  return define_final0(obj, block);
2487 }
2488 
2489 static VALUE
2490 define_final0(VALUE obj, VALUE block)
2491 {
2492  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
2493  VALUE table;
2494  st_data_t data;
2495 
2496  RBASIC(obj)->flags |= FL_FINALIZE;
2497 
2498  block = rb_ary_new3(2, INT2FIX(rb_safe_level()), block);
2499  OBJ_FREEZE(block);
2500 
2501  if (st_lookup(finalizer_table, obj, &data)) {
2502  table = (VALUE)data;
2503 
2504  /* avoid duplicate block, table is usually small */
2505  {
2506  const VALUE *ptr = RARRAY_CONST_PTR(table);
2507  long len = RARRAY_LEN(table);
2508  long i;
2509 
2510  for (i = 0; i < len; i++, ptr++) {
2511  if (rb_funcall(*ptr, idEq, 1, block)) {
2512  return *ptr;
2513  }
2514  }
2515  }
2516 
2517  rb_ary_push(table, block);
2518  }
2519  else {
2520  table = rb_ary_new3(1, block);
2521  RBASIC_CLEAR_CLASS(table);
2522  st_add_direct(finalizer_table, obj, table);
2523  }
2524  return block;
2525 }
2526 
2527 VALUE
2528 rb_define_finalizer(VALUE obj, VALUE block)
2529 {
2530  should_be_finalizable(obj);
2531  should_be_callable(block);
2532  return define_final0(obj, block);
2533 }
2534 
2535 void
2536 rb_gc_copy_finalizer(VALUE dest, VALUE obj)
2537 {
2538  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
2539  VALUE table;
2540  st_data_t data;
2541 
2542  if (!FL_TEST(obj, FL_FINALIZE)) return;
2543  if (st_lookup(finalizer_table, obj, &data)) {
2544  table = (VALUE)data;
2545  st_insert(finalizer_table, dest, table);
2546  }
2547  FL_SET(dest, FL_FINALIZE);
2548 }
2549 
2550 static VALUE
2551 run_single_final(VALUE arg)
2552 {
2553  VALUE *args = (VALUE *)arg;
2554  rb_eval_cmd(args[0], args[1], (int)args[2]);
2555  return Qnil;
2556 }
2557 
2558 static void
2559 run_finalizer(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj, VALUE table)
2560 {
2561  long i;
2562  int status;
2563  VALUE args[3];
2564  VALUE objid = nonspecial_obj_id(obj);
2565 
2566  if (RARRAY_LEN(table) > 0) {
2567  args[1] = rb_obj_freeze(rb_ary_new3(1, objid));
2568  }
2569  else {
2570  args[1] = 0;
2571  }
2572 
2573  args[2] = (VALUE)rb_safe_level();
2574  for (i=0; i<RARRAY_LEN(table); i++) {
2575  VALUE final = RARRAY_AREF(table, i);
2576  args[0] = RARRAY_AREF(final, 1);
2577  args[2] = FIX2INT(RARRAY_AREF(final, 0));
2578  status = 0;
2579  rb_protect(run_single_final, (VALUE)args, &status);
2580  if (status)
2581  rb_set_errinfo(Qnil);
2582  }
2583 }
2584 
2585 static void
2586 run_final(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE zombie)
2587 {
2588  st_data_t key, table;
2589 
2590  if (RZOMBIE(zombie)->dfree) {
2591  RZOMBIE(zombie)->dfree(RZOMBIE(zombie)->data);
2592  }
2593 
2594  key = (st_data_t)zombie;
2595  if (st_delete(finalizer_table, &key, &table)) {
2596  run_finalizer(objspace, zombie, (VALUE)table);
2597  }
2598 }
2599 
2600 static void
2601 finalize_list(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE zombie)
2602 {
2603  while (zombie) {
2604  VALUE next_zombie = RZOMBIE(zombie)->next;
2605  struct heap_page *page = GET_HEAP_PAGE(zombie);
2606 
2607  run_final(objspace, zombie);
2608 
2609  RZOMBIE(zombie)->basic.flags = 0;
2610  heap_pages_final_slots--;
2611  page->final_slots--;
2612  page->free_slots++;
2613  heap_page_add_freeobj(objspace, GET_HEAP_PAGE(zombie), zombie);
2614 
2615  heap_pages_swept_slots++;
2616  objspace->profile.total_freed_objects++;
2617 
2618  zombie = next_zombie;
2619  }
2620 }
2621 
2622 static void
2623 finalize_deferred(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
2624 {
2625  VALUE zombie;
2626 
2627  while ((zombie = (VALUE)ATOMIC_PTR_EXCHANGE(heap_pages_deferred_final, 0)) != 0) {
2628  finalize_list(objspace, zombie);
2629  }
2630 }
2631 
2632 static void
2633 gc_finalize_deferred(void *dmy)
2634 {
2635  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
2636  if (ATOMIC_EXCHANGE(finalizing, 1)) return;
2637  finalize_deferred(objspace);
2638  ATOMIC_SET(finalizing, 0);
2639 }
2640 
2641 /* TODO: to keep compatibility, maybe unused. */
2642 void
2643 rb_gc_finalize_deferred(void)
2644 {
2645  gc_finalize_deferred(0);
2646 }
2647 
2648 static void
2649 gc_finalize_deferred_register(void)
2650 {
2651  if (rb_postponed_job_register_one(0, gc_finalize_deferred, 0) == 0) {
2652  rb_bug("gc_finalize_deferred_register: can't register finalizer.");
2653  }
2654 }
2655 
2656 struct force_finalize_list {
2657  VALUE obj;
2658  VALUE table;
2659  struct force_finalize_list *next;
2660 };
2661 
2662 static int
2663 force_chain_object(st_data_t key, st_data_t val, st_data_t arg)
2664 {
2665  struct force_finalize_list **prev = (struct force_finalize_list **)arg;
2666  struct force_finalize_list *curr = ALLOC(struct force_finalize_list);
2667  curr->obj = key;
2668  curr->table = val;
2669  curr->next = *prev;
2670  *prev = curr;
2671  return ST_CONTINUE;
2672 }
2673 
2674 void
2675 rb_gc_call_finalizer_at_exit(void)
2676 {
2677 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 2
2678  gc_verify_internal_consistency(Qnil);
2679 #endif
2680  rb_objspace_call_finalizer(&rb_objspace);
2681 }
2682 
2683 static void
2684 rb_objspace_call_finalizer(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
2685 {
2686  RVALUE *p, *pend;
2687  size_t i;
2688 
2689  gc_rest(objspace);
2690 
2691  if (ATOMIC_EXCHANGE(finalizing, 1)) return;
2692 
2693  /* run finalizers */
2694  finalize_deferred(objspace);
2695  assert(heap_pages_deferred_final == 0);
2696 
2697  gc_rest(objspace);
2698  /* prohibit incremental GC */
2699  objspace->flags.dont_incremental = 1;
2700 
2701  /* force to run finalizer */
2702  while (finalizer_table->num_entries) {
2703  struct force_finalize_list *list = 0;
2704  st_foreach(finalizer_table, force_chain_object, (st_data_t)&list);
2705  while (list) {
2706  struct force_finalize_list *curr = list;
2707  st_data_t obj = (st_data_t)curr->obj;
2708  run_finalizer(objspace, curr->obj, curr->table);
2709  st_delete(finalizer_table, &obj, 0);
2710  list = curr->next;
2711  xfree(curr);
2712  }
2713  }
2714 
2715  /* prohibit GC because force T_DATA finalizers can break an object graph consistency */
2716  dont_gc = 1;
2717 
2718  /* running data/file finalizers are part of garbage collection */
2719  gc_enter(objspace, "rb_objspace_call_finalizer");
2720 
2721  /* run data/file object's finalizers */
2722  for (i = 0; i < heap_allocated_pages; i++) {
2723  p = heap_pages_sorted[i]->start; pend = p + heap_pages_sorted[i]->total_slots;
2724  while (p < pend) {
2725  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(p)) {
2726  case T_DATA:
2727  if (!DATA_PTR(p) || !RANY(p)->as.data.dfree) break;
2728  if (rb_obj_is_thread((VALUE)p)) break;
2729  if (rb_obj_is_mutex((VALUE)p)) break;
2730  if (rb_obj_is_fiber((VALUE)p)) break;
2731  p->as.free.flags = 0;
2732  if (RTYPEDDATA_P(p)) {
2733  RDATA(p)->dfree = RANY(p)->as.typeddata.type->function.dfree;
2734  }
2735  if (RANY(p)->as.data.dfree == (RUBY_DATA_FUNC)-1) {
2736  xfree(DATA_PTR(p));
2737  }
2738  else if (RANY(p)->as.data.dfree) {
2739  make_zombie(objspace, (VALUE)p, RANY(p)->as.data.dfree, RANY(p)->as.data.data);
2740  }
2741  break;
2742  case T_FILE:
2743  if (RANY(p)->as.file.fptr) {
2744  make_io_zombie(objspace, (VALUE)p);
2745  }
2746  break;
2747  }
2748  p++;
2749  }
2750  }
2751 
2752  gc_exit(objspace, "rb_objspace_call_finalizer");
2753 
2754  if (heap_pages_deferred_final) {
2755  finalize_list(objspace, heap_pages_deferred_final);
2756  }
2757 
2758  st_free_table(finalizer_table);
2759  finalizer_table = 0;
2760  ATOMIC_SET(finalizing, 0);
2761 }
2762 
2763 static inline int
2764 is_id_value(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE ptr)
2765 {
2766  if (!is_pointer_to_heap(objspace, (void *)ptr)) return FALSE;
2767  if (BUILTIN_TYPE(ptr) > T_FIXNUM) return FALSE;
2768  if (BUILTIN_TYPE(ptr) == T_ICLASS) return FALSE;
2769  return TRUE;
2770 }
2771 
2772 static inline int
2773 heap_is_swept_object(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap, VALUE ptr)
2774 {
2775  struct heap_page *page = GET_HEAP_PAGE(ptr);
2776  return page->flags.before_sweep ? FALSE : TRUE;
2777 }
2778 
2779 static inline int
2780 is_swept_object(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE ptr)
2781 {
2782  if (heap_is_swept_object(objspace, heap_eden, ptr)) {
2783  return TRUE;
2784  }
2785  else {
2786  return FALSE;
2787  }
2788 }
2789 
2790 /* garbage objects will be collected soon. */
2791 static inline int
2792 is_garbage_object(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE ptr)
2793 {
2794  if (!is_lazy_sweeping(heap_eden) ||
2795  is_swept_object(objspace, ptr) ||
2796  MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARK_BITS(ptr), ptr)) {
2797 
2798  return FALSE;
2799  }
2800  else {
2801  return TRUE;
2802  }
2803 }

2805 static inline int
2806 is_live_object(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE ptr)
2807 {
2808  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(ptr)) {
2809  case T_NONE:
2810  case T_ZOMBIE:
2811  return FALSE;
2812  }
2813 
2814  if (!is_garbage_object(objspace, ptr)) {
2815  return TRUE;
2816  }
2817  else {
2818  return FALSE;
2819  }
2820 }

2823 is_markable_object(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
2824 {
2825  if (rb_special_const_p(obj)) return FALSE; /* special const is not markable */
2826  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
2827  return TRUE;
2828 }

2838 rb_objspace_garbage_object_p(VALUE obj)

2843 
2844 /*
2845  * call-seq:
2846  * ObjectSpace._id2ref(object_id) -> an_object
2847  *
2848  * Converts an object id to a reference to the object. May not be
2849  * called on an object id passed as a parameter to a finalizer.
2850  *
2851  * s = "I am a string" #=> "I am a string"
2852  * r = ObjectSpace._id2ref(s.object_id) #=> "I am a string"
2853  * r == s #=> true
2854  *
2855  */
2856 
2857 static VALUE
2858 id2ref(VALUE obj, VALUE objid)
2859 {
2860 #if SIZEOF_LONG == SIZEOF_VOIDP
2861 #define NUM2PTR(x) NUM2ULONG(x)
2862 #elif SIZEOF_LONG_LONG == SIZEOF_VOIDP
2863 #define NUM2PTR(x) NUM2ULL(x)
2864 #endif
2865  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
2866  VALUE ptr;
2867  void *p0;
2868 
2869  ptr = NUM2PTR(objid);
2870  p0 = (void *)ptr;
2871 
2872  if (ptr == Qtrue) return Qtrue;
2873  if (ptr == Qfalse) return Qfalse;
2874  if (ptr == Qnil) return Qnil;
2875  if (FIXNUM_P(ptr)) return (VALUE)ptr;
2876  if (FLONUM_P(ptr)) return (VALUE)ptr;
2877  ptr = obj_id_to_ref(objid);
2878 
2879  if ((ptr % sizeof(RVALUE)) == (4 << 2)) {
2880  ID symid = ptr / sizeof(RVALUE);
2881  if (rb_id2str(symid) == 0)
2882  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "%p is not symbol id value", p0);
2883  return ID2SYM(symid);
2884  }
2885 
2886  if (!is_id_value(objspace, ptr)) {
2887  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "%p is not id value", p0);
2888  }
2889  if (!is_live_object(objspace, ptr)) {
2890  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "%p is recycled object", p0);
2891  }
2892  if (RBASIC(ptr)->klass == 0) {
2893  rb_raise(rb_eRangeError, "%p is internal object", p0);
2894  }
2895  return (VALUE)ptr;
2896 }
2897 
2898 /*
2899  * Document-method: __id__
2900  * Document-method: object_id
2901  *
2902  * call-seq:
2903  * obj.__id__ -> integer
2904  * obj.object_id -> integer
2905  *
2906  * Returns an integer identifier for +obj+.
2907  *
2908  * The same number will be returned on all calls to +object_id+ for a given
2909  * object, and no two active objects will share an id.
2910  *
2911  * Note: that some objects of builtin classes are reused for optimization.
2912  * This is the case for immediate values and frozen string literals.
2913  *
2914  * Immediate values are not passed by reference but are passed by value:
2915  * +nil+, +true+, +false+, Fixnums, Symbols, and some Floats.
2916  *
2917  * Object.new.object_id == Object.new.object_id # => false
2918  * (21 * 2).object_id == (21 * 2).object_id # => true
2919  * "hello".object_id == "hello".object_id # => false
2920  * "hi".freeze.object_id == "hi".freeze.object_id # => true
2921  */
2922 
2923 VALUE
2924 rb_obj_id(VALUE obj)
2925 {
2926  /*
2927  * 32-bit VALUE space
2928  * MSB ------------------------ LSB
2929  * false 00000000000000000000000000000000
2930  * true 00000000000000000000000000000010
2931  * nil 00000000000000000000000000000100
2932  * undef 00000000000000000000000000000110
2933  * symbol ssssssssssssssssssssssss00001110
2934  * object oooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo00 = 0 (mod sizeof(RVALUE))
2935  * fixnum fffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff1
2936  *
2937  * object_id space
2938  * LSB
2939  * false 00000000000000000000000000000000
2940  * true 00000000000000000000000000000010
2941  * nil 00000000000000000000000000000100
2942  * undef 00000000000000000000000000000110
2943  * symbol 000SSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSSS0 S...S % A = 4 (S...S = s...s * A + 4)
2944  * object oooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo0 o...o % A = 0
2945  * fixnum fffffffffffffffffffffffffffffff1 bignum if required
2946  *
2947  * where A = sizeof(RVALUE)/4
2948  *
2949  * sizeof(RVALUE) is
2950  * 20 if 32-bit, double is 4-byte aligned
2951  * 24 if 32-bit, double is 8-byte aligned
2952  * 40 if 64-bit
2953  */
2954  if (STATIC_SYM_P(obj)) {
2955  return (SYM2ID(obj) * sizeof(RVALUE) + (4 << 2)) | FIXNUM_FLAG;
2956  }
2957  else if (FLONUM_P(obj)) {
2958 #if SIZEOF_LONG == SIZEOF_VOIDP
2959  return LONG2NUM((SIGNED_VALUE)obj);
2960 #else
2961  return LL2NUM((SIGNED_VALUE)obj);
2962 #endif
2963  }
2964  else if (SPECIAL_CONST_P(obj)) {
2965  return LONG2NUM((SIGNED_VALUE)obj);
2966  }
2967  return nonspecial_obj_id(obj);
2968 }
2969 
2970 #include "regint.h"
2971 
2972 static size_t
2973 obj_memsize_of(VALUE obj, int use_all_types)
2974 {
2975  size_t size = 0;
2976 
2977  if (SPECIAL_CONST_P(obj)) {
2978  return 0;
2979  }
2980 
2981  if (FL_TEST(obj, FL_EXIVAR)) {
2982  size += rb_generic_ivar_memsize(obj);
2983  }
2984 
2985  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)) {
2986  case T_OBJECT:
2987  if (!(RBASIC(obj)->flags & ROBJECT_EMBED) &&
2988  ROBJECT(obj)->as.heap.ivptr) {
2989  size += ROBJECT(obj)->as.heap.numiv * sizeof(VALUE);
2990  }
2991  break;
2992  case T_MODULE:
2993  case T_CLASS:
2994  if (RCLASS_M_TBL(obj)) {
2995  size += st_memsize(RCLASS_M_TBL(obj));
2996  }
2997  if (RCLASS_EXT(obj)) {
2998  if (RCLASS_IV_TBL(obj)) {
2999  size += st_memsize(RCLASS_IV_TBL(obj));
3000  }
3001  if (RCLASS_IV_INDEX_TBL(obj)) {
3002  size += st_memsize(RCLASS_IV_INDEX_TBL(obj));
3003  }
3004  if (RCLASS(obj)->ptr->iv_tbl) {
3005  size += st_memsize(RCLASS(obj)->ptr->iv_tbl);
3006  }
3007  if (RCLASS(obj)->ptr->const_tbl) {
3008  size += st_memsize(RCLASS(obj)->ptr->const_tbl);
3009  }
3010  size += sizeof(rb_classext_t);
3011  }
3012  break;
3013  case T_ICLASS:
3014  if (FL_TEST(obj, RICLASS_IS_ORIGIN)) {
3015  if (RCLASS_M_TBL(obj)) {
3016  size += st_memsize(RCLASS_M_TBL(obj));
3017  }
3018  }
3019  break;
3020  case T_STRING:
3021  size += rb_str_memsize(obj);
3022  break;
3023  case T_ARRAY:
3024  size += rb_ary_memsize(obj);
3025  break;
3026  case T_HASH:
3027  if (RHASH(obj)->ntbl) {
3028  size += st_memsize(RHASH(obj)->ntbl);
3029  }
3030  break;
3031  case T_REGEXP:
3032  if (RREGEXP(obj)->ptr) {
3033  size += onig_memsize(RREGEXP(obj)->ptr);
3034  }
3035  break;
3036  case T_DATA:
3037  if (use_all_types) size += rb_objspace_data_type_memsize(obj);
3038  break;
3039  case T_MATCH:
3040  if (RMATCH(obj)->rmatch) {
3041  struct rmatch *rm = RMATCH(obj)->rmatch;
3042  size += onig_region_memsize(&rm->regs);
3043  size += sizeof(struct rmatch_offset) * rm->char_offset_num_allocated;
3044  size += sizeof(struct rmatch);
3045  }
3046  break;
3047  case T_FILE:
3048  if (RFILE(obj)->fptr) {
3049  size += rb_io_memsize(RFILE(obj)->fptr);
3050  }
3051  break;
3052  case T_RATIONAL:
3053  case T_COMPLEX:
3054  case T_IMEMO:
3055  break;
3056 
3057  case T_FLOAT:
3058  case T_SYMBOL:
3059  break;
3060 
3061  case T_BIGNUM:
3062  if (!(RBASIC(obj)->flags & BIGNUM_EMBED_FLAG) && BIGNUM_DIGITS(obj)) {
3063  size += BIGNUM_LEN(obj) * sizeof(BDIGIT);
3064  }
3065  break;
3066 
3067  case T_NODE:
3068  if (use_all_types) size += rb_node_memsize(obj);
3069  break;
3070 
3071  case T_STRUCT:
3072  if ((RBASIC(obj)->flags & RSTRUCT_EMBED_LEN_MASK) == 0 &&
3073  RSTRUCT(obj)->as.heap.ptr) {
3074  size += sizeof(VALUE) * RSTRUCT_LEN(obj);
3075  }
3076  break;
3077 
3078  case T_ZOMBIE:
3079  break;
3080 
3081  default:
3082  rb_bug("objspace/memsize_of(): unknown data type 0x%x(%p)",
3083  BUILTIN_TYPE(obj), (void*)obj);
3084  }
3085 
3086  return size + sizeof(RVALUE);
3087 }
3088 
3089 size_t
3090 rb_obj_memsize_of(VALUE obj)
3091 {
3092  return obj_memsize_of(obj, TRUE);
3093 }

3095 static int
3096 set_zero(st_data_t key, st_data_t val, st_data_t arg)
3097 {
3098  VALUE k = (VALUE)key;
3099  VALUE hash = (VALUE)arg;
3100  rb_hash_aset(hash, k, INT2FIX(0));
3101  return ST_CONTINUE;
3102 }
3103 
3104 /*
3105  * call-seq:
3106  * ObjectSpace.count_objects([result_hash]) -> hash
3107  *
3108  * Counts all objects grouped by type.
3109  *
3110  * It returns a hash, such as:
3111  * {
3112  * :TOTAL=>10000,
3113  * :FREE=>3011,
3114  * :T_OBJECT=>6,
3115  * :T_CLASS=>404,
3116  * # ...
3117  * }
3118  *
3119  * The contents of the returned hash are implementation specific.
3120  * It may be changed in future. The +:TOTAL+ key contains the count
3121  * of all currently allocated and previously freed objects.
3122  *
3123  * If the optional argument +result_hash+ is given,
3124  * it is overwritten and returned. This is intended to avoid probe effect.
3125  *
3126  * h = {}
3127  * ObjectSpace.count_objects(h)
3128  * puts h
3129  * # => { :TOTAL=>10000, :T_CLASS=>158280, :T_MODULE=>20672, :T_STRING=>527249 }
3130  *
3131  * This method is only expected to work on C Ruby.
3132  *
3133  */
3134 
3135 static VALUE
3136 count_objects(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE os)
3137 {
3138  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
3139  size_t counts[T_MASK+1];
3140  size_t freed = 0;
3141  size_t total = 0;
3142  size_t i;
3143  VALUE hash;
3144 
3145  if (rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "01", &hash) == 1) {
3146  if (!RB_TYPE_P(hash, T_HASH))
3147  rb_raise(rb_eTypeError, "non-hash given");
3148  }
3149 
3150  for (i = 0; i <= T_MASK; i++) {
3151  counts[i] = 0;
3152  }
3153 
3154  for (i = 0; i < heap_allocated_pages; i++) {
3155  struct heap_page *page = heap_pages_sorted[i];
3156  RVALUE *p, *pend;
3157 
3158  p = page->start; pend = p + page->total_slots;
3159  for (;p < pend; p++) {
3160  if (p->as.basic.flags) {
3161  counts[BUILTIN_TYPE(p)]++;
3162  }
3163  else {
3164  freed++;
3165  }
3166  }
3167  total += page->total_slots;
3168  }
3169 
3170  if (hash == Qnil) {
3171  hash = rb_hash_new();
3172  }
3173  else if (!RHASH_EMPTY_P(hash)) {
3174  st_foreach(RHASH_TBL_RAW(hash), set_zero, hash);
3175  }
3176  rb_hash_aset(hash, ID2SYM(rb_intern("TOTAL")), SIZET2NUM(total));
3177  rb_hash_aset(hash, ID2SYM(rb_intern("FREE")), SIZET2NUM(freed));
3178 
3179  for (i = 0; i <= T_MASK; i++) {
3180  VALUE type;
3181  switch (i) {
3182 #define COUNT_TYPE(t) case (t): type = ID2SYM(rb_intern(#t)); break;
3183  COUNT_TYPE(T_NONE);
3184  COUNT_TYPE(T_OBJECT);
3185  COUNT_TYPE(T_CLASS);
3186  COUNT_TYPE(T_MODULE);
3187  COUNT_TYPE(T_FLOAT);
3188  COUNT_TYPE(T_STRING);
3189  COUNT_TYPE(T_REGEXP);
3190  COUNT_TYPE(T_ARRAY);
3191  COUNT_TYPE(T_HASH);
3192  COUNT_TYPE(T_STRUCT);
3193  COUNT_TYPE(T_BIGNUM);
3194  COUNT_TYPE(T_FILE);
3195  COUNT_TYPE(T_DATA);
3196  COUNT_TYPE(T_MATCH);
3197  COUNT_TYPE(T_COMPLEX);
3198  COUNT_TYPE(T_RATIONAL);
3199  COUNT_TYPE(T_NIL);
3200  COUNT_TYPE(T_TRUE);
3201  COUNT_TYPE(T_FALSE);
3202  COUNT_TYPE(T_SYMBOL);
3203  COUNT_TYPE(T_FIXNUM);
3204  COUNT_TYPE(T_IMEMO);
3205  COUNT_TYPE(T_UNDEF);
3206  COUNT_TYPE(T_NODE);
3207  COUNT_TYPE(T_ICLASS);
3208  COUNT_TYPE(T_ZOMBIE);
3209 #undef COUNT_TYPE
3210  default: type = INT2NUM(i); break;
3211  }
3212  if (counts[i])
3213  rb_hash_aset(hash, type, SIZET2NUM(counts[i]));
3214  }
3215 
3216  return hash;
3217 }

3220  ------------------------ Garbage Collection ------------------------
3221 */

3225 static size_t
3226 objspace_available_slots(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
3227 {
3228  return heap_eden->total_slots + heap_tomb->total_slots;
3229 }

3231 static size_t
3232 objspace_live_slots(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
3233 {
3234  return (objspace->total_allocated_objects - objspace->profile.total_freed_objects) - heap_pages_final_slots;
3235 }
3236 
3237 static size_t
3238 objspace_free_slots(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
3239 {
3240  return objspace_available_slots(objspace) - objspace_live_slots(objspace) - heap_pages_final_slots;
3241 }
3242 
3243 static void
3244 gc_setup_mark_bits(struct heap_page *page)
3245 {
3246 #if USE_RGENGC
3247  /* copy oldgen bitmap to mark bitmap */
3248  memcpy(&page->mark_bits[0], &page->uncollectible_bits[0], HEAP_BITMAP_SIZE);
3249 #else
3250  /* clear mark bitmap */
3251  memset(&page->mark_bits[0], 0, HEAP_BITMAP_SIZE);
3252 #endif
3253 }
3254 
3255 /* TRUE : has empty slots */
3256 /* FALSE: no empty slots (or move to tomb heap because no live slots) */
3257 static inline void
3258 gc_page_sweep(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap, struct heap_page *sweep_page)
3259 {
3260  int i;
3261  int empty_slots = 0, freed_slots = 0, final_slots = 0;
3262  RVALUE *p, *pend,*offset;
3263  bits_t *bits, bitset;
3264 
3265  gc_report(2, objspace, "page_sweep: start.\n");
3266 
3267  sweep_page->flags.before_sweep = FALSE;
3268 
3269  p = sweep_page->start; pend = p + sweep_page->total_slots;
3270  offset = p - NUM_IN_PAGE(p);
3271  bits = sweep_page->mark_bits;
3272 
3273  /* create guard : fill 1 out-of-range */
3274  bits[BITMAP_INDEX(p)] |= BITMAP_BIT(p)-1;
3275  bits[BITMAP_INDEX(pend)] |= ~(BITMAP_BIT(pend) - 1);
3276 
3277  for (i=0; i < HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT; i++) {
3278  bitset = ~bits[i];
3279  if (bitset) {
3280  p = offset + i * BITS_BITLENGTH;
3281  do {
3282  if (bitset & 1) {
3283  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(p)) {
3284  default: { /* majority case */
3285  gc_report(2, objspace, "page_sweep: free %s\n", obj_info((VALUE)p));
3286 #if USE_RGENGC && RGENGC_CHECK_MODE
3287  if (!is_full_marking(objspace)) {
3288  if (RVALUE_OLD_P((VALUE)p)) rb_bug("page_sweep: %s - old while minor GC.", obj_info((VALUE)p));
3289  if (rgengc_remembered(objspace, (VALUE)p)) rb_bug("page_sweep: %s - remembered.", obj_info((VALUE)p));
3290  }
3291 #endif
3292  if (obj_free(objspace, (VALUE)p)) {
3293  final_slots++;
3294  }
3295  else {
3296  (void)VALGRIND_MAKE_MEM_UNDEFINED((void*)p, sizeof(RVALUE));
3297  heap_page_add_freeobj(objspace, sweep_page, (VALUE)p);
3298  gc_report(3, objspace, "page_sweep: %s is added to freelist\n", obj_info((VALUE)p));
3299  freed_slots++;
3300  }
3301  break;
3302  }
3303 
3304  /* minor cases */
3305  case T_ZOMBIE:
3306  /* already counted */
3307  break;
3308  case T_NONE:
3309  empty_slots++; /* already freed */
3310  break;
3311  }
3312  }
3313  p++;
3314  bitset >>= 1;
3315  } while (bitset);
3316  }
3317  }
3318 
3319  gc_setup_mark_bits(sweep_page);
3320 
3321 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
3322  if (gc_prof_enabled(objspace)) {
3323  gc_profile_record *record = gc_prof_record(objspace);
3324  record->removing_objects += final_slots + freed_slots;
3325  record->empty_objects += empty_slots;
3326  }
3327 #endif
3328  if (0) fprintf(stderr, "gc_page_sweep(%d): total_slots: %d, freed_slots: %d, empty_slots: %d, final_slots: %d\n",
3329  (int)rb_gc_count(),
3330  (int)sweep_page->total_slots,
3331  freed_slots, empty_slots, final_slots);
3332 
3333  heap_pages_swept_slots += sweep_page->free_slots = freed_slots + empty_slots;
3334  objspace->profile.total_freed_objects += freed_slots;
3335  heap_pages_final_slots += final_slots;
3336  sweep_page->final_slots += final_slots;
3337 
3338  if (heap_pages_deferred_final && !finalizing) {
3339  rb_thread_t *th = GET_THREAD();
3340  if (th) {
3341  gc_finalize_deferred_register();
3342  }
3343  }
3344 
3345  gc_report(2, objspace, "page_sweep: end.\n");
3346 }
3347 
3348 /* allocate additional minimum page to work */
3349 static void
3350 gc_heap_prepare_minimum_pages(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
3351 {
3352  if (!heap->free_pages && heap_increment(objspace, heap) == FALSE) {
3353  /* there is no free after page_sweep() */
3354  heap_set_increment(objspace, 1);
3355  if (!heap_increment(objspace, heap)) { /* can't allocate additional free objects */
3356  rb_memerror();
3357  }
3358  }
3359 }
3360 
3361 static void
3362 gc_stat_transition(rb_objspace_t *objspace, enum gc_stat stat)
3363 {
3364 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE
3365  enum gc_stat prev_stat = objspace->flags.stat;
3366  switch (prev_stat) {
3367  case gc_stat_none: assert(stat == gc_stat_marking); break;
3368  case gc_stat_marking: assert(stat == gc_stat_sweeping); break;
3369  case gc_stat_sweeping: assert(stat == gc_stat_none); break;
3370  }
3371 #endif
3372  objspace->flags.stat = stat;
3373 }
3374 
3375 static void
3376 gc_sweep_start_heap(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
3377 {
3378  heap->sweep_pages = heap->pages;
3379  heap->free_pages = NULL;
3380 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
3381  heap->pooled_pages = NULL;
3382  objspace->rincgc.pooled_slots = 0;
3383 #endif
3384  if (heap->using_page) {
3385  RVALUE **p = &heap->using_page->freelist;
3386  while (*p) {
3387  p = &(*p)->as.free.next;
3388  }
3389  *p = heap->freelist;
3390  heap->using_page = NULL;
3391  }
3392  heap->freelist = NULL;
3393 }
3394 
3395 #if defined(__GNUC__) && __GNUC__ == 4 && __GNUC_MINOR__ == 4
3396 __attribute__((noinline))
3397 #endif
3398 static void
3399 gc_sweep_start(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
3400 {
3401  rb_heap_t *heap;
3402  size_t total_limit_slot;
3403 
3404  gc_stat_transition(objspace, gc_stat_sweeping);
3405 
3406  /* sometimes heap_allocatable_pages is not 0 */
3407  heap_pages_swept_slots = heap_allocatable_pages * HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT;
3408  total_limit_slot = objspace_available_slots(objspace);
3409 
3410  heap_pages_min_free_slots = (size_t)(total_limit_slot * GC_HEAP_FREE_SLOTS_MIN_RATIO);
3411  if (heap_pages_min_free_slots < gc_params.heap_free_slots) {
3412  heap_pages_min_free_slots = gc_params.heap_free_slots;
3413  }
3414  heap_pages_max_free_slots = (size_t)(total_limit_slot * GC_HEAP_FREE_SLOTS_MAX_RATIO);
3415  if (heap_pages_max_free_slots < gc_params.heap_init_slots) {
3416  heap_pages_max_free_slots = gc_params.heap_init_slots;
3417  }
3418  if (0) fprintf(stderr, "heap_pages_min_free_slots: %d, heap_pages_max_free_slots: %d\n",
3419  (int)heap_pages_min_free_slots, (int)heap_pages_max_free_slots);
3420 
3421  heap = heap_eden;
3422  gc_sweep_start_heap(objspace, heap);
3423 }
3424 
3425 static void
3426 gc_sweep_finish(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
3427 {
3428  rb_heap_t *heap = heap_eden;
3429 
3430  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_sweep_finish: heap->total_slots: %d, heap->swept_slots: %d, min_free_slots: %d\n",
3431  (int)heap->total_slots, (int)heap_pages_swept_slots, (int)heap_pages_min_free_slots);
3432 
3433  gc_prof_set_heap_info(objspace);
3434 
3435  heap_pages_free_unused_pages(objspace);
3436 
3437  /* if heap_pages has unused pages, then assign them to increment */
3438  if (heap_allocatable_pages < heap_tomb->page_length) {
3439  heap_allocatable_pages = heap_tomb->page_length;
3440  }
3441 
3442  gc_event_hook(objspace, RUBY_INTERNAL_EVENT_GC_END_SWEEP, 0);
3443  gc_stat_transition(objspace, gc_stat_none);
3444 
3445 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 2
3446  gc_verify_internal_consistency(Qnil);
3447 #endif
3448 }
3449 
3450 static int
3451 gc_sweep_step(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
3452 {
3453  struct heap_page *sweep_page = heap->sweep_pages, *next;
3454  int unlink_limit = 3;
3455 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
3456  int need_pool = will_be_incremental_marking(objspace) ? TRUE : FALSE;
3457 
3458  gc_report(2, objspace, "gc_sweep_step (need_pool: %d)\n", need_pool);
3459 #else
3460  gc_report(2, objspace, "gc_sweep_step\n");
3461 #endif
3462 
3463  if (sweep_page == NULL) return FALSE;
3464 
3465 #if GC_ENABLE_LAZY_SWEEP
3466  gc_prof_sweep_timer_start(objspace);
3467 #endif
3468 
3469  while (sweep_page) {
3470  heap->sweep_pages = next = sweep_page->next;
3471  gc_page_sweep(objspace, heap, sweep_page);
3472 
3473  if (sweep_page->final_slots + sweep_page->free_slots == sweep_page->total_slots &&
3474  unlink_limit > 0) {
3475  unlink_limit--;
3476  /* there are no living objects -> move this page to tomb heap */
3477  heap_unlink_page(objspace, heap, sweep_page);
3478  heap_add_page(objspace, heap_tomb, sweep_page);
3479  }
3480  else if (sweep_page->free_slots > 0) {
3481 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
3482  if (need_pool) {
3483  if (heap_add_poolpage(objspace, heap, sweep_page)) {
3484  need_pool = FALSE;
3485  }
3486  }
3487  else {
3488  heap_add_freepage(objspace, heap, sweep_page);
3489  break;
3490  }
3491 #else
3492  heap_add_freepage(objspace, heap, sweep_page);
3493  break;
3494 #endif
3495  }
3496  else {
3497  sweep_page->free_next = NULL;
3498  }
3499 
3500  sweep_page = next;
3501  }
3502 
3503  if (heap->sweep_pages == NULL) {
3504  gc_sweep_finish(objspace);
3505  }
3506 
3507 #if GC_ENABLE_LAZY_SWEEP
3508  gc_prof_sweep_timer_stop(objspace);
3509 #endif
3510 
3511  return heap->free_pages != NULL;
3512 }
3513 
3514 static void
3515 gc_sweep_rest(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
3516 {
3517  rb_heap_t *heap = heap_eden; /* lazy sweep only for eden */
3518 
3519  while (has_sweeping_pages(heap)) {
3520  gc_sweep_step(objspace, heap);
3521  }
3522 }
3523 
3524 #if GC_ENABLE_LAZY_SWEEP
3525 static void
3526 gc_sweep_continue(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
3527 {
3528  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(dont_gc == FALSE);
3529 
3530  gc_enter(objspace, "sweep_continue");
3531 #if USE_RGENGC
3532  if (objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc == GPR_FLAG_NONE && heap_increment(objspace, heap)) {
3533  gc_report(3, objspace, "gc_sweep_continue: success heap_increment().\n");
3534  }
3535 #endif
3536  gc_sweep_step(objspace, heap);
3537  gc_exit(objspace, "sweep_continue");
3538 }
3539 #endif
3540 
3541 static void
3542 gc_sweep(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
3543 {
3544  const unsigned int immediate_sweep = objspace->flags.immediate_sweep;
3545 
3546  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_sweep: immediate: %d\n", immediate_sweep);
3547 
3548  if (immediate_sweep) {
3549 #if !GC_ENABLE_LAZY_SWEEP
3550  gc_prof_sweep_timer_start(objspace);
3551 #endif
3552  gc_sweep_start(objspace);
3553  gc_sweep_rest(objspace);
3554 #if !GC_ENABLE_LAZY_SWEEP
3555  gc_prof_sweep_timer_stop(objspace);
3556 #endif
3557  }
3558  else {
3559  struct heap_page *page;
3560  gc_sweep_start(objspace);
3561  page = heap_eden->sweep_pages;
3562  while (page) {
3563  page->flags.before_sweep = TRUE;
3564  page = page->next;
3565  }
3566  gc_sweep_step(objspace, heap_eden);
3567  }
3568 
3569  gc_heap_prepare_minimum_pages(objspace, heap_eden);
3570 }

3574 static stack_chunk_t *
3575 stack_chunk_alloc(void)
3576 {
3577  stack_chunk_t *res;
3578 
3579  res = malloc(sizeof(stack_chunk_t));
3580  if (!res)
3581  rb_memerror();
3582 
3583  return res;
3584 }
