3586 static inline int
3587 is_mark_stack_empty(mark_stack_t *stack)
3588 {
3589  return stack->chunk == NULL;
3590 }
3591 
3592 static size_t
3593 mark_stack_size(mark_stack_t *stack)
3594 {
3595  size_t size = stack->index;
3596  stack_chunk_t *chunk = stack->chunk ? stack->chunk->next : NULL;
3597 
3598  while (chunk) {
3599  size += stack->limit;
3600  chunk = chunk->next;
3601  }
3602  return size;
3603 }
3604 
3605 static void
3606 add_stack_chunk_cache(mark_stack_t *stack, stack_chunk_t *chunk)
3607 {
3608  chunk->next = stack->cache;
3609  stack->cache = chunk;
3610  stack->cache_size++;
3611 }
3612 
3613 static void
3614 shrink_stack_chunk_cache(mark_stack_t *stack)
3615 {
3616  stack_chunk_t *chunk;
3617 
3618  if (stack->unused_cache_size > (stack->cache_size/2)) {
3619  chunk = stack->cache;
3620  stack->cache = stack->cache->next;
3621  stack->cache_size--;
3622  free(chunk);
3623  }
3624  stack->unused_cache_size = stack->cache_size;
3625 }
3626 
3627 static void
3628 push_mark_stack_chunk(mark_stack_t *stack)
3629 {
3630  stack_chunk_t *next;
3631 
3632  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(stack->index == stack->limit);
3633 
3634  if (stack->cache_size > 0) {
3635  next = stack->cache;
3636  stack->cache = stack->cache->next;
3637  stack->cache_size--;
3638  if (stack->unused_cache_size > stack->cache_size)
3639  stack->unused_cache_size = stack->cache_size;
3640  }
3641  else {
3642  next = stack_chunk_alloc();
3643  }
3644  next->next = stack->chunk;
3645  stack->chunk = next;
3646  stack->index = 0;
3647 }
3648 
3649 static void
3650 pop_mark_stack_chunk(mark_stack_t *stack)
3651 {
3652  stack_chunk_t *prev;
3653 
3654  prev = stack->chunk->next;
3655  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(stack->index == 0);
3656  add_stack_chunk_cache(stack, stack->chunk);
3657  stack->chunk = prev;
3658  stack->index = stack->limit;
3659 }
3660 
3661 #if (defined(ENABLE_VM_OBJSPACE) && ENABLE_VM_OBJSPACE) || (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 4)
3662 static void
3663 free_stack_chunks(mark_stack_t *stack)
3664 {
3665  stack_chunk_t *chunk = stack->chunk;
3666  stack_chunk_t *next = NULL;
3667 
3668  while (chunk != NULL) {
3669  next = chunk->next;
3670  free(chunk);
3671  chunk = next;
3672  }
3673 }
3674 #endif
3675 
3676 static void
3677 push_mark_stack(mark_stack_t *stack, VALUE data)
3678 {
3679  if (stack->index == stack->limit) {
3680  push_mark_stack_chunk(stack);
3681  }
3682  stack->chunk->data[stack->index++] = data;
3683 }
3684 
3685 static int
3686 pop_mark_stack(mark_stack_t *stack, VALUE *data)
3687 {
3688  if (is_mark_stack_empty(stack)) {
3689  return FALSE;
3690  }
3691  if (stack->index == 1) {
3692  *data = stack->chunk->data[--stack->index];
3693  pop_mark_stack_chunk(stack);
3694  }
3695  else {
3696  *data = stack->chunk->data[--stack->index];
3697  }
3698  return TRUE;
3699 }
3700 
3701 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
3702 static int
3703 invalidate_mark_stack_chunk(stack_chunk_t *chunk, int limit, VALUE obj)
3704 {
3705  int i;
3706  for (i=0; i<limit; i++) {
3707  if (chunk->data[i] == obj) {
3708  chunk->data[i] = Qundef;
3709  return TRUE;
3710  }
3711  }
3712  return FALSE;
3713 }
3714 
3715 static void
3716 invalidate_mark_stack(mark_stack_t *stack, VALUE obj)
3717 {
3718  stack_chunk_t *chunk = stack->chunk;
3719  int limit = stack->index;
3720 
3721  while (chunk) {
3722  if (invalidate_mark_stack_chunk(chunk, limit, obj)) return;
3723  chunk = chunk->next;
3724  limit = stack->limit;
3725  }
3726  rb_bug("invalid_mark_stack: unreachable");
3727 }
3728 #endif
3729 
3730 static void
3731 init_mark_stack(mark_stack_t *stack)
3732 {
3733  int i;
3734 
3735  MEMZERO(stack, mark_stack_t, 1);
3736  stack->index = stack->limit = STACK_CHUNK_SIZE;
3737  stack->cache_size = 0;
3738 
3739  for (i=0; i < 4; i++) {
3740  add_stack_chunk_cache(stack, stack_chunk_alloc());
3741  }
3742  stack->unused_cache_size = stack->cache_size;
3743 }
3744 
3745 /* Marking */
3746 
3747 #ifdef __ia64
3748 #define SET_STACK_END (SET_MACHINE_STACK_END(&th->machine.stack_end), th->machine.register_stack_end = rb_ia64_bsp())
3749 #else
3750 #define SET_STACK_END SET_MACHINE_STACK_END(&th->machine.stack_end)
3751 #endif
3752 
3753 #define STACK_START (th->machine.stack_start)
3754 #define STACK_END (th->machine.stack_end)
3755 #define STACK_LEVEL_MAX (th->machine.stack_maxsize/sizeof(VALUE))
3756 
3757 #if STACK_GROW_DIRECTION < 0
3758 # define STACK_LENGTH (size_t)(STACK_START - STACK_END)
3759 #elif STACK_GROW_DIRECTION > 0
3760 # define STACK_LENGTH (size_t)(STACK_END - STACK_START + 1)
3761 #else
3762 # define STACK_LENGTH ((STACK_END < STACK_START) ? (size_t)(STACK_START - STACK_END) \
3763  : (size_t)(STACK_END - STACK_START + 1))
3764 #endif
3765 #if !STACK_GROW_DIRECTION
3766 int ruby_stack_grow_direction;
3767 int
3768 ruby_get_stack_grow_direction(volatile VALUE *addr)
3769 {
3770  VALUE *end;
3771  SET_MACHINE_STACK_END(&end);
3772 
3773  if (end > addr) return ruby_stack_grow_direction = 1;
3774  return ruby_stack_grow_direction = -1;
3775 }
3776 #endif
3777 
3778 size_t
3779 ruby_stack_length(VALUE **p)
3780 {
3781  rb_thread_t *th = GET_THREAD();
3782  SET_STACK_END;
3783  if (p) *p = STACK_UPPER(STACK_END, STACK_START, STACK_END);
3784  return STACK_LENGTH;
3785 }
3786 
3787 #if !(defined(POSIX_SIGNAL) && defined(SIGSEGV) && defined(HAVE_SIGALTSTACK))
3788 static int
3789 stack_check(int water_mark)
3790 {
3791  int ret;
3792  rb_thread_t *th = GET_THREAD();
3793  SET_STACK_END;
3794  ret = STACK_LENGTH > STACK_LEVEL_MAX - water_mark;
3795 #ifdef __ia64
3796  if (!ret) {
3797  ret = (VALUE*)rb_ia64_bsp() - th->machine.register_stack_start >
3798  th->machine.register_stack_maxsize/sizeof(VALUE) - water_mark;
3799  }
3800 #endif
3801  return ret;
3802 }
3803 #endif
3804 
3805 #define STACKFRAME_FOR_CALL_CFUNC 512
3806 
3807 int
3808 ruby_stack_check(void)
3809 {
3810 #if defined(POSIX_SIGNAL) && defined(SIGSEGV) && defined(HAVE_SIGALTSTACK)
3811  return 0;
3812 #else
3813  return stack_check(STACKFRAME_FOR_CALL_CFUNC);
3814 #endif
3815 }

3817 ATTRIBUTE_NO_ADDRESS_SAFETY_ANALYSIS
3818 static void
3819 mark_locations_array(rb_objspace_t *objspace, register const VALUE *x, register long n)
3820 {
3821  VALUE v;
3822  while (n--) {
3823  v = *x;
3824  gc_mark_maybe(objspace, v);
3825  x++;
3826  }
3827 }

3829 static void
3830 gc_mark_locations(rb_objspace_t *objspace, const VALUE *start, const VALUE *end)
3831 {
3832  long n;
3833 
3834  if (end <= start) return;
3835  n = end - start;
3836  mark_locations_array(objspace, start, n);
3837 }

3917 static void
3918 mark_method_entry(rb_objspace_t *objspace, const rb_method_entry_t *me)
3919 {
3920  const rb_method_definition_t *def = me->def;
3921 
3922  gc_mark(objspace, me->klass);
3923 
3924  switch (def->type) {
3925  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_ISEQ:
3926  gc_mark(objspace, def->body.iseq.iseqptr->self);
3927  gc_mark(objspace, (VALUE)def->body.iseq.cref);
3928  break;
3929  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_ATTRSET:
3930  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_IVAR:
3931  gc_mark(objspace, def->body.attr.location);
3932  break;
3933  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_BMETHOD:
3934  gc_mark(objspace, def->body.proc);
3935  break;
3936  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_ALIAS:
3937  gc_mark(objspace, (VALUE)def->body.alias.original_me);
3938  return;
3939  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_REFINED:
3940  gc_mark(objspace, (VALUE)def->body.refined.orig_me);
3941  break;
3942  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_CFUNC:
3943  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_ZSUPER:
3944  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_MISSING:
3945  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_OPTIMIZED:
3946  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_UNDEF:
3947  case VM_METHOD_TYPE_NOTIMPLEMENTED:
3948  break;
3949  }
3950 }
3951 
3952 static int
3953 mark_method_entry_i(st_data_t key, st_data_t value, st_data_t data)
3954 {
3955  VALUE me = (VALUE)value;
3956  rb_objspace_t *objspace = (rb_objspace_t *)data;
3957 
3958  gc_mark(objspace, me);
3959  return ST_CONTINUE;
3960 }

3988 #if STACK_GROW_DIRECTION < 0
3989 #define GET_STACK_BOUNDS(start, end, appendix) ((start) = STACK_END, (end) = STACK_START)
3990 #elif STACK_GROW_DIRECTION > 0
3991 #define GET_STACK_BOUNDS(start, end, appendix) ((start) = STACK_START, (end) = STACK_END+(appendix))
3992 #else
3993 #define GET_STACK_BOUNDS(start, end, appendix) \
3994  ((STACK_END < STACK_START) ? \
3995  ((start) = STACK_END, (end) = STACK_START) : ((start) = STACK_START, (end) = STACK_END+(appendix)))
3996 #endif

3998 static void
3999 mark_current_machine_context(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_thread_t *th)
4000 {
4001  union {
4002  rb_jmp_buf j;
4003  VALUE v[sizeof(rb_jmp_buf) / sizeof(VALUE)];
4004  } save_regs_gc_mark;
4005  VALUE *stack_start, *stack_end;
4006 
4007  FLUSH_REGISTER_WINDOWS;
4008  /* This assumes that all registers are saved into the jmp_buf (and stack) */
4009  rb_setjmp(save_regs_gc_mark.j);
4010 
4011  /* SET_STACK_END must be called in this function because
4012  * the stack frame of this function may contain
4013  * callee save registers and they should be marked. */
4014  SET_STACK_END;
4015  GET_STACK_BOUNDS(stack_start, stack_end, 1);
4016 
4017  mark_locations_array(objspace, save_regs_gc_mark.v, numberof(save_regs_gc_mark.v));
4018 
4019  rb_gc_mark_locations(stack_start, stack_end);
4020 #ifdef __ia64
4021  rb_gc_mark_locations(th->machine.register_stack_start, th->machine.register_stack_end);
4022 #endif
4023 #if defined(__mc68000__)
4024  rb_gc_mark_locations((VALUE*)((char*)stack_start + 2),
4025  (VALUE*)((char*)stack_end - 2));
4026 #endif
4027 }
4028 
4029 void
4030 rb_gc_mark_machine_stack(rb_thread_t *th)
4031 {
4032  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
4033  VALUE *stack_start, *stack_end;
4034 
4035  GET_STACK_BOUNDS(stack_start, stack_end, 0);
4036  rb_gc_mark_locations(stack_start, stack_end);
4037 #ifdef __ia64
4038  rb_gc_mark_locations(th->machine.register_stack_start, th->machine.register_stack_end);
4039 #endif
4040 #if defined(__mc68000__)
4041  rb_gc_mark_locations((VALUE*)((char*)stack_start + 2),
4042  (VALUE*)((char*)stack_end - 2));
4043 #endif
4044 }

4052 static void
4053 gc_mark_maybe(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
4054 {
4055  (void)VALGRIND_MAKE_MEM_DEFINED(&obj, sizeof(obj));
4056  if (is_pointer_to_heap(objspace, (void *)obj)) {
4057  int type = BUILTIN_TYPE(obj);
4058  if (type != T_ZOMBIE && type != T_NONE) {
4059  gc_mark_ptr(objspace, obj);
4060  }
4061  }
4062 }

4070 static inline int
4071 gc_mark_set(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
4072 {
4073  if (RVALUE_MARKED(obj)) return 0;
4074  MARK_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARK_BITS(obj), obj);
4075  return 1;
4076 }
4077 
4078 #if USE_RGENGC
4079 static int
4080 gc_remember_unprotected(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
4081 {
4082  struct heap_page *page = GET_HEAP_PAGE(obj);
4083  bits_t *uncollectible_bits = &page->uncollectible_bits[0];
4084 
4085  if (!MARKED_IN_BITMAP(uncollectible_bits, obj)) {
4086  page->flags.has_uncollectible_shady_objects = TRUE;
4087  MARK_IN_BITMAP(uncollectible_bits, obj);
4088  objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects++;
4089 
4090 #if RGENGC_PROFILE > 0
4091  objspace->profile.total_remembered_shady_object_count++;
4092 #if RGENGC_PROFILE >= 2
4093  objspace->profile.remembered_shady_object_count_types[BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)]++;
4094 #endif
4095 #endif
4096  return TRUE;
4097  }
4098  else {
4099  return FALSE;
4100  }
4101 }
4102 #endif
4103 
4104 static void
4105 rgengc_check_relation(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
4106 {
4107 #if USE_RGENGC
4108  const VALUE old_parent = objspace->rgengc.parent_object;
4109 
4110  if (old_parent) { /* parent object is old */
4111  if (RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj)) {
4112  if (gc_remember_unprotected(objspace, obj)) {
4113  gc_report(2, objspace, "relation: (O->S) %s -> %s\n", obj_info(old_parent), obj_info(obj));
4114  }
4115  }
4116  else {
4117  if (!RVALUE_OLD_P(obj)) {
4118  if (RVALUE_MARKED(obj)) {
4119  /* An object pointed from an OLD object should be OLD. */
4120  gc_report(2, objspace, "relation: (O->unmarked Y) %s -> %s\n", obj_info(old_parent), obj_info(obj));
4121  RVALUE_AGE_SET_OLD(objspace, obj);
4122  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
4123  if (!RVALUE_MARKING(obj)) {
4124  gc_grey(objspace, obj);
4125  }
4126  }
4127  else {
4128  rgengc_remember(objspace, obj);
4129  }
4130  }
4131  else {
4132  gc_report(2, objspace, "relation: (O->Y) %s -> %s\n", obj_info(old_parent), obj_info(obj));
4133  RVALUE_AGE_SET_CANDIDATE(objspace, obj);
4134  }
4135  }
4136  }
4137  }
4138 
4139  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(old_parent == objspace->rgengc.parent_object);
4140 #endif
4141 }
4142 
4143 static void
4144 gc_grey(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
4145 {
4146 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE
4147  if (RVALUE_MARKED(obj) == FALSE) rb_bug("gc_grey: %s is not marked.", obj_info(obj));
4148  if (RVALUE_MARKING(obj) == TRUE) rb_bug("gc_grey: %s is marking/remembered.", obj_info(obj));
4149 #endif
4150 
4151 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
4152  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
4153  MARK_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARKING_BITS(obj), obj);
4154  }
4155 #endif
4156 
4157  push_mark_stack(&objspace->mark_stack, obj);
4158 }
4159 
4160 static void
4161 gc_aging(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
4162 {
4163 #if USE_RGENGC
4164  struct heap_page *page = GET_HEAP_PAGE(obj);
4165 
4166 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE
4167  assert(RVALUE_MARKING(obj) == FALSE);
4168 #endif
4169 
4170  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
4171 
4172  if (!RVALUE_PAGE_WB_UNPROTECTED(page, obj)) {
4173  if (!RVALUE_OLD_P(obj)) {
4174  gc_report(3, objspace, "gc_aging: YOUNG: %s\n", obj_info(obj));
4175  RVALUE_AGE_INC(objspace, obj);
4176  }
4177  else if (is_full_marking(objspace)) {
4178  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(RVALUE_PAGE_UNCOLLECTIBLE(page, obj) == FALSE);
4179  RVALUE_PAGE_OLD_UNCOLLECTIBLE_SET(objspace, page, obj);
4180  }
4181  }
4182  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
4183 #endif /* USE_RGENGC */
4184 
4185  objspace->marked_slots++;
4186 }
4187 
4188 static void
4189 gc_mark_ptr(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
4190 {
4191  if (LIKELY(objspace->mark_func_data == NULL)) {
4192  rgengc_check_relation(objspace, obj);
4193  if (!gc_mark_set(objspace, obj)) return; /* already marked */
4194  gc_aging(objspace, obj);
4195  gc_grey(objspace, obj);
4196  }
4197  else {
4198  objspace->mark_func_data->mark_func(obj, objspace->mark_func_data->data);
4199  }
4200 }
4201 
4202 static void
4203 gc_mark(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
4204 {
4205  if (!is_markable_object(objspace, obj)) return;
4206  gc_mark_ptr(objspace, obj);
4207 }

4210 rb_gc_mark(VALUE ptr)

4213 }

4216  * This function is only for GC_END_MARK timing.
4217  */
4218

4220 rb_objspace_marked_object_p(VALUE obj)
4221 {

4223 }

4225 static inline void
4226 gc_mark_set_parent(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)

4228 #if USE_RGENGC
4229  if (RVALUE_OLD_P(obj)) {
4230  objspace->rgengc.parent_object = obj;

4232  else {
4233  objspace->rgengc.parent_object = Qfalse;

4238 static void
4239 gc_mark_children(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
4240 {
4241  register RVALUE *any = RANY(obj);
4242  gc_mark_set_parent(objspace, obj);
4243 
4244  if (FL_TEST(obj, FL_EXIVAR)) {
4245  rb_mark_generic_ivar(obj);
4246  }
4247 
4248  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)) {
4249  case T_NIL:
4250  case T_FIXNUM:
4251  rb_bug("rb_gc_mark() called for broken object");
4252  break;
4253 
4254  case T_NODE:
4255  obj = rb_gc_mark_node(&any->as.node);
4256  if (obj) gc_mark(objspace, obj);
4257  return; /* no need to mark class. */
4258 
4259  case T_IMEMO:
4260  switch (imemo_type(obj)) {
4261  case imemo_cref:
4262  gc_mark(objspace, RANY(obj)->as.imemo.cref.klass);
4263  gc_mark(objspace, (VALUE)RANY(obj)->as.imemo.cref.next);
4264  gc_mark(objspace, RANY(obj)->as.imemo.cref.refinements);
4265  return;
4266  case imemo_svar:
4267  gc_mark(objspace, RANY(obj)->as.imemo.svar.cref_or_me);
4268  gc_mark(objspace, RANY(obj)->as.imemo.svar.lastline);
4269  gc_mark(objspace, RANY(obj)->as.imemo.svar.backref);
4270  gc_mark(objspace, RANY(obj)->as.imemo.svar.others);
4271  return;
4272  case imemo_throw_data:
4273  gc_mark(objspace, RANY(obj)->as.imemo.throw_data.throw_obj);
4274  return;
4275  case imemo_ifunc:
4276  gc_mark_maybe(objspace, (VALUE)RANY(obj)->as.imemo.ifunc.data);
4277  return;
4278  case imemo_memo:
4279  gc_mark(objspace, RANY(obj)->as.imemo.memo.v1);
4280  gc_mark(objspace, RANY(obj)->as.imemo.memo.v2);
4281  gc_mark_maybe(objspace, RANY(obj)->as.imemo.memo.u3.value);
4282  return;
4283  case imemo_ment:
4284  mark_method_entry(objspace, &RANY(obj)->as.imemo.ment);
4285  return;
4286  default:
4287  rb_bug("T_IMEMO: unreachable");
4288  }
4289  }
4290 
4291  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.basic.klass);
4292 
4293  switch (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)) {
4294  case T_CLASS:
4295  case T_MODULE:
4296  mark_m_tbl(objspace, RCLASS_M_TBL(obj));
4297  if (!RCLASS_EXT(obj)) break;
4298  mark_tbl(objspace, RCLASS_IV_TBL(obj));
4299  mark_const_tbl(objspace, RCLASS_CONST_TBL(obj));
4300  gc_mark(objspace, RCLASS_SUPER((VALUE)obj));
4301  break;
4302 
4303  case T_ICLASS:
4304  if (FL_TEST(obj, RICLASS_IS_ORIGIN)) {
4305  mark_m_tbl(objspace, RCLASS_M_TBL(obj));
4306  }
4307  if (!RCLASS_EXT(obj)) break;
4308  gc_mark(objspace, RCLASS_SUPER((VALUE)obj));
4309  break;
4310 
4311  case T_ARRAY:
4312  if (FL_TEST(obj, ELTS_SHARED)) {
4313  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.array.as.heap.aux.shared);
4314  }
4315  else {
4316  long i, len = RARRAY_LEN(obj);
4317  const VALUE *ptr = RARRAY_CONST_PTR(obj);
4318  for (i=0; i < len; i++) {
4319  gc_mark(objspace, *ptr++);
4320  }
4321  }
4322  break;
4323 
4324  case T_HASH:
4325  mark_hash(objspace, any->as.hash.ntbl);
4326  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.hash.ifnone);
4327  break;
4328 
4329  case T_STRING:
4330  if (STR_SHARED_P(obj)) {
4331  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.string.as.heap.aux.shared);
4332  }
4333  break;
4334 
4335  case T_DATA:
4336  {
4337  void *const ptr = DATA_PTR(obj);
4338  if (ptr) {
4339  RUBY_DATA_FUNC mark_func = RTYPEDDATA_P(obj) ?
4340  any->as.typeddata.type->function.dmark :
4341  any->as.data.dmark;
4342  if (mark_func) (*mark_func)(ptr);
4343  }
4344  }
4345  break;
4346 
4347  case T_OBJECT:
4348  {
4349  long i, len = ROBJECT_NUMIV(obj);
4350  VALUE *ptr = ROBJECT_IVPTR(obj);
4351  for (i = 0; i < len; i++) {
4352  gc_mark(objspace, *ptr++);
4353  }
4354  }
4355  break;
4356 
4357  case T_FILE:
4358  if (any->as.file.fptr) {
4359  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.file.fptr->pathv);
4360  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.file.fptr->tied_io_for_writing);
4361  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.file.fptr->writeconv_asciicompat);
4362  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.file.fptr->writeconv_pre_ecopts);
4363  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.file.fptr->encs.ecopts);
4364  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.file.fptr->write_lock);
4365  }
4366  break;
4367 
4368  case T_REGEXP:
4369  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.regexp.src);
4370  break;
4371 
4372  case T_FLOAT:
4373  case T_BIGNUM:
4374  case T_SYMBOL:
4375  break;
4376 
4377  case T_MATCH:
4378  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.match.regexp);
4379  if (any->as.match.str) {
4380  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.match.str);
4381  }
4382  break;
4383 
4384  case T_RATIONAL:
4385  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.rational.num);
4386  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.rational.den);
4387  break;
4388 
4389  case T_COMPLEX:
4390  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.complex.real);
4391  gc_mark(objspace, any->as.complex.imag);
4392  break;
4393 
4394  case T_STRUCT:
4395  {
4396  long len = RSTRUCT_LEN(obj);
4397  const VALUE *ptr = RSTRUCT_CONST_PTR(obj);
4398 
4399  while (len--) {
4400  gc_mark(objspace, *ptr++);
4401  }
4402  }
4403  break;
4404 
4405  default:
4406 #if GC_DEBUG
4407  rb_gcdebug_print_obj_condition((VALUE)obj);
4408 #endif
4409  if (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj) == T_NONE) rb_bug("rb_gc_mark(): %p is T_NONE", (void *)obj);
4410  if (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj) == T_ZOMBIE) rb_bug("rb_gc_mark(): %p is T_ZOMBIE", (void *)obj);
4411  rb_bug("rb_gc_mark(): unknown data type 0x%x(%p) %s",
4412  BUILTIN_TYPE(obj), any,
4413  is_pointer_to_heap(objspace, any) ? "corrupted object" : "non object");
4414  }
4415 }
4416 
4421 static inline int
4422 gc_mark_stacked_objects(rb_objspace_t *objspace, int incremental, size_t count)
4423 {
4424  mark_stack_t *mstack = &objspace->mark_stack;
4425  VALUE obj;
4426 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
4427  size_t marked_slots_at_the_beggining = objspace->marked_slots;
4428  size_t popped_count = 0;
4429 #endif
4430 
4431  while (pop_mark_stack(mstack, &obj)) {
4432  if (obj == Qundef) continue; /* skip */
4433 
4434  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE && !RVALUE_MARKED(obj)) {
4435  rb_bug("gc_mark_stacked_objects: %s is not marked.", obj_info(obj));
4436  }
4437  gc_mark_children(objspace, obj);
4438 
4439 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
4440  if (incremental) {
4441  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE && !RVALUE_MARKING(obj)) {
4442  rb_bug("gc_mark_stacked_objects: incremental, but marking bit is 0");
4443  }
4444  CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARKING_BITS(obj), obj);
4445  popped_count++;
4446 
4447  if (popped_count + (objspace->marked_slots - marked_slots_at_the_beggining) > count) {
4448  break;
4449  }
4450  }
4451  else {
4452  /* just ignore marking bits */
4453  }
4454 #endif
4455  }
4456 
4457  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 3) gc_verify_internal_consistency(Qnil);
4458 
4459  if (is_mark_stack_empty(mstack)) {
4460  shrink_stack_chunk_cache(mstack);
4461  return TRUE;
4462  }
4463  else {
4464  return FALSE;
4465  }
4466 }
4467 
4468 static int
4469 gc_mark_stacked_objects_incremental(rb_objspace_t *objspace, size_t count)
4470 {
4471  return gc_mark_stacked_objects(objspace, TRUE, count);
4472 }
4473 
4474 static int
4475 gc_mark_stacked_objects_all(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
4476 {
4477  return gc_mark_stacked_objects(objspace, FALSE, 0);
4478 }

4480 #if PRINT_ROOT_TICKS
4481 #define MAX_TICKS 0x100
4482 static tick_t mark_ticks[MAX_TICKS];
4483 static const char *mark_ticks_categories[MAX_TICKS];
4484 
4485 static void
4486 show_mark_ticks(void)
4487 {
4488  int i;
4489  fprintf(stderr, "mark ticks result:\n");
4490  for (i=0; i<MAX_TICKS; i++) {
4491  const char *category = mark_ticks_categories[i];
4492  if (category) {
4493  fprintf(stderr, "%s\t%8lu\n", category, (unsigned long)mark_ticks[i]);
4494  }
4495  else {
4496  break;
4497  }
4498  }
4499 }
4500 
4501 #endif /* PRITNT_ROOT_TICKS */
4502 
4503 static void
4504 gc_mark_roots(rb_objspace_t *objspace, const char **categoryp)
4505 {
4506  struct gc_list *list;
4507  rb_thread_t *th = GET_THREAD();
4508 
4509 #if PRINT_ROOT_TICKS
4510  tick_t start_tick = tick();
4511  int tick_count = 0;
4512  const char *prev_category = 0;
4513 
4514  if (mark_ticks_categories[0] == 0) {
4515  atexit(show_mark_ticks);
4516  }
4517 #endif
4518 
4519  if (categoryp) *categoryp = "xxx";
4520 
4521 #if USE_RGENGC
4522  objspace->rgengc.parent_object = Qfalse;
4523 #endif
4524 
4525 #if PRINT_ROOT_TICKS
4526 #define MARK_CHECKPOINT_PRINT_TICK(category) do { \
4527  if (prev_category) { \
4528  tick_t t = tick(); \
4529  mark_ticks[tick_count] = t - start_tick; \
4530  mark_ticks_categories[tick_count] = prev_category; \
4531  tick_count++; \
4532  } \
4533  prev_category = category; \
4534  start_tick = tick(); \
4535 } while (0)
4536 #else /* PRITNT_ROOT_TICKS */
4537 #define MARK_CHECKPOINT_PRINT_TICK(category)
4538 #endif
4539 
4540 #define MARK_CHECKPOINT(category) do { \
4541  if (categoryp) *categoryp = category; \
4542  MARK_CHECKPOINT_PRINT_TICK(category); \
4543 } while (0)
4544 
4545  MARK_CHECKPOINT("vm");
4546  SET_STACK_END;
4547  rb_vm_mark(th->vm);
4548  if (th->vm->self) gc_mark_set(objspace, th->vm->self);
4549 
4550  MARK_CHECKPOINT("finalizers");
4551  mark_tbl(objspace, finalizer_table);
4552 
4553  MARK_CHECKPOINT("machine_context");
4554  mark_current_machine_context(objspace, th);
4555 
4556  MARK_CHECKPOINT("encodings");
4557  rb_gc_mark_encodings();
4558 
4559  /* mark protected global variables */
4560  MARK_CHECKPOINT("global_list");
4561  for (list = global_list; list; list = list->next) {
4562  rb_gc_mark_maybe(*list->varptr);
4563  }
4564 
4565  MARK_CHECKPOINT("end_proc");
4566  rb_mark_end_proc();
4567 
4568  MARK_CHECKPOINT("global_tbl");
4569  rb_gc_mark_global_tbl();
4570 
4571  if (stress_to_class) rb_gc_mark(stress_to_class);
4572 
4573  MARK_CHECKPOINT("finish");
4574 #undef MARK_CHECKPOINT
4575 }

4577 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 4
4578 
4579 #define MAKE_ROOTSIG(obj) (((VALUE)(obj) << 1) | 0x01)
4580 #define IS_ROOTSIG(obj) ((VALUE)(obj) & 0x01)
4581 #define GET_ROOTSIG(obj) ((const char *)((VALUE)(obj) >> 1))

4583 struct reflist {
4584  VALUE *list;
4585  int pos;
4586  int size;
4587 };
4588 
4589 static struct reflist *
4590 reflist_create(VALUE obj)
4591 {
4592  struct reflist *refs = xmalloc(sizeof(struct reflist));
4593  refs->size = 1;
4594  refs->list = ALLOC_N(VALUE, refs->size);
4595  refs->list[0] = obj;
4596  refs->pos = 1;
4597  return refs;
4598 }
4599 
4600 static void
4601 reflist_destruct(struct reflist *refs)
4602 {
4603  xfree(refs->list);
4604  xfree(refs);
4605 }
4606 
4607 static void
4608 reflist_add(struct reflist *refs, VALUE obj)
4609 {
4610  if (refs->pos == refs->size) {
4611  refs->size *= 2;
4612  SIZED_REALLOC_N(refs->list, VALUE, refs->size, refs->size/2);
4613  }
4614 
4615  refs->list[refs->pos++] = obj;
4616 }
4617 
4618 static void
4619 reflist_dump(struct reflist *refs)
4620 {
4621  int i;
4622  for (i=0; i<refs->pos; i++) {
4623  VALUE obj = refs->list[i];
4624  if (IS_ROOTSIG(obj)) { /* root */
4625  fprintf(stderr, "<root@%s>", GET_ROOTSIG(obj));
4626  }
4627  else {
4628  fprintf(stderr, "<%s>", obj_info(obj));
4629  }
4630  if (i+1 < refs->pos) fprintf(stderr, ", ");
4631  }
4632 }
4633 
4634 static int
4635 reflist_refered_from_machine_context(struct reflist *refs)
4636 {
4637  int i;
4638  for (i=0; i<refs->pos; i++) {
4639  VALUE obj = refs->list[i];
4640  if (IS_ROOTSIG(obj) && strcmp(GET_ROOTSIG(obj), "machine_context") == 0) return 1;
4641  }
4642  return 0;
4643 }
4644 
4645 struct allrefs {
4646  rb_objspace_t *objspace;
4647  /* a -> obj1
4648  * b -> obj1
4649  * c -> obj1
4650  * c -> obj2
4651  * d -> obj3
4652  * #=> {obj1 => [a, b, c], obj2 => [c, d]}
4653  */
4654  struct st_table *references;
4655  const char *category;
4656  VALUE root_obj;
4657  mark_stack_t mark_stack;
4658 };
4659 
4660 static int
4661 allrefs_add(struct allrefs *data, VALUE obj)
4662 {
4663  struct reflist *refs;
4664 
4665  if (st_lookup(data->references, obj, (st_data_t *)&refs)) {
4666  reflist_add(refs, data->root_obj);
4667  return 0;
4668  }
4669  else {
4670  refs = reflist_create(data->root_obj);
4671  st_insert(data->references, obj, (st_data_t)refs);
4672  return 1;
4673  }
4674 }
4675 
4676 static void
4677 allrefs_i(VALUE obj, void *ptr)
4678 {
4679  struct allrefs *data = (struct allrefs *)ptr;
4680 
4681  if (allrefs_add(data, obj)) {
4682  push_mark_stack(&data->mark_stack, obj);
4683  }
4684 }
4685 
4686 static void
4687 allrefs_roots_i(VALUE obj, void *ptr)
4688 {
4689  struct allrefs *data = (struct allrefs *)ptr;
4690  if (strlen(data->category) == 0) rb_bug("!!!");
4691  data->root_obj = MAKE_ROOTSIG(data->category);
4692 
4693  if (allrefs_add(data, obj)) {
4694  push_mark_stack(&data->mark_stack, obj);
4695  }
4696 }
4697 
4698 static st_table *
4699 objspace_allrefs(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
4700 {
4701  struct allrefs data;
4702  struct mark_func_data_struct mfd;
4703  VALUE obj;
4704  int prev_dont_gc = dont_gc;
4705  dont_gc = TRUE;
4706 
4707  data.objspace = objspace;
4708  data.references = st_init_numtable();
4709  init_mark_stack(&data.mark_stack);
4710 
4711  mfd.mark_func = allrefs_roots_i;
4712  mfd.data = &data;
4713 
4714  /* traverse root objects */
4715  PUSH_MARK_FUNC_DATA(&mfd);
4716  objspace->mark_func_data = &mfd;
4717  gc_mark_roots(objspace, &data.category);
4718  POP_MARK_FUNC_DATA();
4719 
4720  /* traverse rest objects reachable from root objects */
4721  while (pop_mark_stack(&data.mark_stack, &obj)) {
4722  rb_objspace_reachable_objects_from(data.root_obj = obj, allrefs_i, &data);
4723  }
4724  free_stack_chunks(&data.mark_stack);
4725 
4726  dont_gc = prev_dont_gc;
4727  return data.references;
4728 }
4729 
4730 static int
4731 objspace_allrefs_destruct_i(st_data_t key, st_data_t value, void *ptr)
4732 {
4733  struct reflist *refs = (struct reflist *)value;
4734  reflist_destruct(refs);
4735  return ST_CONTINUE;
4736 }
4737 
4738 static void
4739 objspace_allrefs_destruct(struct st_table *refs)
4740 {
4741  st_foreach(refs, objspace_allrefs_destruct_i, 0);
4742  st_free_table(refs);
4743 }

4758 allrefs_dump(rb_objspace_t *objspace)

4765 static int
4766 gc_check_after_marks_i(st_data_t k, st_data_t v, void *ptr)
4767 {
4768  VALUE obj = k;
4769  struct reflist *refs = (struct reflist *)v;
4770  rb_objspace_t *objspace = (rb_objspace_t *)ptr;
4771 
4772  /* object should be marked or oldgen */
4773  if (!MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARK_BITS(obj), obj)) {
4774  fprintf(stderr, "gc_check_after_marks_i: %s is not marked and not oldgen.\n", obj_info(obj));
4775  fprintf(stderr, "gc_check_after_marks_i: %p is referred from ", (void *)obj);
4776  reflist_dump(refs);
4777 
4778  if (reflist_refered_from_machine_context(refs)) {
4779  fprintf(stderr, " (marked from machine stack).\n");
4780  /* marked from machine context can be false positive */
4781  }
4782  else {
4783  objspace->rgengc.error_count++;
4784  fprintf(stderr, "\n");
4785  }
4786  }
4787  return ST_CONTINUE;
4788 }

4790 static void
4791 gc_marks_check(rb_objspace_t *objspace, int (*checker_func)(ANYARGS), const char *checker_name)
4792 {
4793  size_t saved_malloc_increase = objspace->malloc_params.increase;
4794 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
4795  size_t saved_oldmalloc_increase = objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase;
4796 #endif
4797  VALUE already_disabled = rb_gc_disable();
4798 
4799  objspace->rgengc.allrefs_table = objspace_allrefs(objspace);
4800 
4801  if (checker_func) {
4802  st_foreach(objspace->rgengc.allrefs_table, checker_func, (st_data_t)objspace);
4803  }
4804 
4805  if (objspace->rgengc.error_count > 0) {
4806 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 5
4807  allrefs_dump(objspace);
4808 #endif
4809  if (checker_name) rb_bug("%s: GC has problem.", checker_name);
4810  }
4811 
4812  objspace_allrefs_destruct(objspace->rgengc.allrefs_table);
4813  objspace->rgengc.allrefs_table = 0;
4814 
4815  if (already_disabled == Qfalse) rb_gc_enable();
4816  objspace->malloc_params.increase = saved_malloc_increase;
4817 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
4818  objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase = saved_oldmalloc_increase;
4819 #endif
4820 }
4821 #endif /* RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 4 */
4822 
4823 struct verify_internal_consistency_struct {
4824  rb_objspace_t *objspace;
4825  int err_count;
4826  size_t live_object_count;
4827  size_t zombie_object_count;
4828 
4829 #if USE_RGENGC
4830  VALUE parent;
4831  size_t old_object_count;
4832  size_t remembered_shady_count;
4833 #endif
4834 };
4835 
4836 #if USE_RGENGC
4837 static void
4838 check_generation_i(const VALUE child, void *ptr)
4839 {
4840  struct verify_internal_consistency_struct *data = (struct verify_internal_consistency_struct *)ptr;
4841  const VALUE parent = data->parent;
4842 
4843  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(RVALUE_OLD_P(parent));
4844 
4845  if (!RVALUE_OLD_P(child)) {
4846  if (!RVALUE_REMEMBERED(parent) &&
4847  !RVALUE_REMEMBERED(child) &&
4848  !RVALUE_UNCOLLECTIBLE(child)) {
4849  fprintf(stderr, "verify_internal_consistency_reachable_i: WB miss (O->Y) %s -> %s\n", obj_info(parent), obj_info(child));
4850  data->err_count++;
4851  }
4852  }
4853 }
4854 
4855 static void
4856 check_color_i(const VALUE child, void *ptr)
4857 {
4858  struct verify_internal_consistency_struct *data = (struct verify_internal_consistency_struct *)ptr;
4859  const VALUE parent = data->parent;
4860 
4861  if (!RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(parent) && RVALUE_WHITE_P(child)) {
4862  fprintf(stderr, "verify_internal_consistency_reachable_i: WB miss (B->W) - %s -> %s\n",
4863  obj_info(parent), obj_info(child));
4864  data->err_count++;
4865  }
4866 }
4867 #endif
4868 
4869 static void
4870 check_children_i(const VALUE child, void *ptr)
4871 {
4872  check_rvalue_consistency(child);
4873 }
4874 
4875 static int
4876 verify_internal_consistency_i(void *page_start, void *page_end, size_t stride, void *ptr)
4877 {
4878  struct verify_internal_consistency_struct *data = (struct verify_internal_consistency_struct *)ptr;
4879  VALUE obj;
4880  rb_objspace_t *objspace = data->objspace;
4881 
4882  for (obj = (VALUE)page_start; obj != (VALUE)page_end; obj += stride) {
4883  if (is_live_object(objspace, obj)) {
4884  /* count objects */
4885  data->live_object_count++;
4886 
4887  rb_objspace_reachable_objects_from(obj, check_children_i, (void *)data);
4888 
4889 #if USE_RGENGC
4890  /* check health of children */
4891  data->parent = obj;
4892 
4893  if (RVALUE_OLD_P(obj)) data->old_object_count++;
4894  if (RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj) && RVALUE_UNCOLLECTIBLE(obj)) data->remembered_shady_count++;
4895 
4896  if (!is_marking(objspace) && RVALUE_OLD_P(obj)) {
4897  /* reachable objects from an oldgen object should be old or (young with remember) */
4898  data->parent = obj;
4899  rb_objspace_reachable_objects_from(obj, check_generation_i, (void *)data);
4900  }
4901 
4902  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
4903  if (RVALUE_BLACK_P(obj)) {
4904  /* reachable objects from black objects should be black or grey objects */
4905  data->parent = obj;
4906  rb_objspace_reachable_objects_from(obj, check_color_i, (void *)data);
4907  }
4908  }
4909 #endif
4910  }
4911  else {
4912  if (BUILTIN_TYPE(obj) == T_ZOMBIE) {
4913  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(RBASIC(obj)->flags == T_ZOMBIE);
4914  data->zombie_object_count++;
4915  }
4916  }
4917  }
4918 
4919  return 0;
4920 }
4921 
4922 static int
4923 gc_verify_heap_page(rb_objspace_t *objspace, struct heap_page *page, VALUE obj)
4924 {
4925 #if USE_RGENGC
4926  int i;
4927  unsigned int has_remembered_shady = FALSE;
4928  unsigned int has_remembered_old = FALSE;
4929  int rememberd_old_objects = 0;
4930 
4931  for (i=0; i<page->total_slots; i++) {
4932  VALUE obj = (VALUE)&page->start[i];
4933  if (RVALUE_PAGE_UNCOLLECTIBLE(page, obj) && RVALUE_PAGE_WB_UNPROTECTED(page, obj)) has_remembered_shady = TRUE;
4934  if (RVALUE_PAGE_MARKING(page, obj)) {
4935  has_remembered_old = TRUE;
4936  rememberd_old_objects++;
4937  }
4938  }
4939 
4940  if (!is_incremental_marking(objspace) &&
4941  page->flags.has_remembered_objects == FALSE && has_remembered_old == TRUE) {
4942 
4943  for (i=0; i<page->total_slots; i++) {
4944  VALUE obj = (VALUE)&page->start[i];
4945  if (RVALUE_PAGE_MARKING(page, obj)) {
4946  fprintf(stderr, "marking -> %s\n", obj_info(obj));
4947  }
4948  }
4949  rb_bug("page %p's has_remembered_objects should be false, but there are remembered old objects (%d). %s",
4950  page, rememberd_old_objects, obj ? obj_info(obj) : "");
4951  }
4952 
4953  if (page->flags.has_uncollectible_shady_objects == FALSE && has_remembered_shady == TRUE) {
4954  rb_bug("page %p's has_remembered_shady should be false, but there are remembered shady objects. %s",
4955  page, obj ? obj_info(obj) : "");
4956  }
4957 
4958  return rememberd_old_objects;
4959 #else
4960  return 0;
4961 #endif
4962 }
4963 
4964 static int
4965 gc_verify_heap_pages(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
4966 {
4967  int rememberd_old_objects = 0;
4968  struct heap_page *page = heap_eden->pages;
4969 
4970  while (page) {
4971  if (page->flags.has_remembered_objects == FALSE)
4972  rememberd_old_objects += gc_verify_heap_page(objspace, page, Qfalse);
4973  page = page->next;
4974  }
4975 
4976  return rememberd_old_objects;
4977 }
4978 
4979 /*
4980  * call-seq:
4981  * GC.verify_internal_consistency -> nil
4982  *
4983  * Verify internal consistency.
4984  *
4985  * This method is implementation specific.
4986  * Now this method checks generational consistency
4987  * if RGenGC is supported.
4988  */
4989 static VALUE
4990 gc_verify_internal_consistency(VALUE dummy)
4991 {
4992  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
4993  struct verify_internal_consistency_struct data = {0};
4994  struct each_obj_args eo_args;
4995 
4996  data.objspace = objspace;
4997  gc_report(5, objspace, "gc_verify_internal_consistency: start\n");
4998 
4999  /* check relations */
5000 
5001  eo_args.callback = verify_internal_consistency_i;
5002  eo_args.data = (void *)&data;
5003  objspace_each_objects((VALUE)&eo_args);
5004 
5005  if (data.err_count != 0) {
5006 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 5
5007  objspace->rgengc.error_count = data.err_count;
5008  gc_marks_check(objspace, NULL, NULL);
5009  allrefs_dump(objspace);
5010 #endif
5011  rb_bug("gc_verify_internal_consistency: found internal inconsistency.");
5012  }
5013 
5014  /* check heap_page status */
5015  gc_verify_heap_pages(objspace);
5016 
5017  /* check counters */
5018 
5019  if (!is_lazy_sweeping(heap_eden) && !finalizing) {
5020  if (objspace_live_slots(objspace) != data.live_object_count) {
5021  fprintf(stderr, "heap_pages_final_slots: %d, objspace->profile.total_freed_objects: %d\n",
5022  (int)heap_pages_final_slots, (int)objspace->profile.total_freed_objects);
5023  rb_bug("inconsistent live slot nubmer: expect %"PRIuSIZE", but %"PRIuSIZE".", objspace_live_slots(objspace), data.live_object_count);
5024  }
5025  }
5026 
5027 #if USE_RGENGC
5028  if (!is_marking(objspace)) {
5029  if (objspace->rgengc.old_objects != data.old_object_count) {
5030  rb_bug("inconsistent old slot nubmer: expect %"PRIuSIZE", but %"PRIuSIZE".", objspace->rgengc.old_objects, data.old_object_count);
5031  }
5032  if (objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects != data.remembered_shady_count) {
5033  rb_bug("inconsistent old slot nubmer: expect %"PRIuSIZE", but %"PRIuSIZE".", objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects, data.remembered_shady_count);
5034  }
5035  }
5036 #endif
5037 
5038  if (!finalizing) {
5039  size_t list_count = 0;
5040 
5041  {
5042  VALUE z = heap_pages_deferred_final;
5043  while (z) {
5044  list_count++;
5045  z = RZOMBIE(z)->next;
5046  }
5047  }
5048 
5049  if (heap_pages_final_slots != data.zombie_object_count ||
5050  heap_pages_final_slots != list_count) {
5051 
5052  rb_bug("inconsistent finalizing object count:\n"
5053  " expect %"PRIuSIZE"\n"
5054  " but %"PRIuSIZE" zombies\n"
5055  " heap_pages_deferred_final list has %"PRIuSIZE" items.",
5056  heap_pages_final_slots,
5057  data.zombie_object_count,
5058  list_count);
5059  }
5060  }
5061 
5062  gc_report(5, objspace, "gc_verify_internal_consistency: OK\n");
5063 
5064  return Qnil;
5065 }
5066 
5067 void
5068 rb_gc_verify_internal_consistency(void)
5069 {
5070  gc_verify_internal_consistency(Qnil);
5071 }
5072 
5073 /* marks */
5074 
5075 static void
5076 gc_marks_start(rb_objspace_t *objspace, int full_mark)
5077 {
5078  /* start marking */
5079  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_marks_start: (%s)\n", full_mark ? "full" : "minor");
5080  gc_stat_transition(objspace, gc_stat_marking);
5081 
5082 #if USE_RGENGC
5083  if (full_mark) {
5084 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
5085  objspace->rincgc.step_slots = (objspace->marked_slots * 2) / ((objspace->rincgc.pooled_slots / HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT) + 1);
5086 
5087  if (0) fprintf(stderr, "objspace->marked_slots: %d, objspace->rincgc.pooled_page_num: %d, objspace->rincgc.step_slots: %d, \n",
5088  (int)objspace->marked_slots, (int)objspace->rincgc.pooled_slots, (int)objspace->rincgc.step_slots);
5089 #endif
5090  objspace->flags.during_minor_gc = FALSE;
5091  objspace->profile.major_gc_count++;
5092  objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects = 0;
5093  objspace->rgengc.old_objects = 0;
5094  objspace->rgengc.last_major_gc = objspace->profile.count;
5095  objspace->marked_slots = 0;
5096  rgengc_mark_and_rememberset_clear(objspace, heap_eden);
5097  }
5098  else {
5099  objspace->flags.during_minor_gc = TRUE;
5100  objspace->marked_slots =
5101  objspace->rgengc.old_objects + objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects; /* uncollectible objects are marked already */
5102  objspace->profile.minor_gc_count++;
5103  rgengc_rememberset_mark(objspace, heap_eden);
5104  }
5105 #endif
5106 
5107  gc_mark_roots(objspace, NULL);
5108 
5109  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_marks_start: (%s) end, stack in %d\n", full_mark ? "full" : "minor", (int)mark_stack_size(&objspace->mark_stack));
5110 }
5111 
5112 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
5113 static void
5114 gc_marks_wb_unprotected_objects(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
5115 {
5116  struct heap_page *page = heap_eden->pages;
5117 
5118  while (page) {
5119  bits_t *mark_bits = page->mark_bits;
5120  bits_t *wbun_bits = page->wb_unprotected_bits;
5121  RVALUE *p = page->start;
5122  RVALUE *offset = p - NUM_IN_PAGE(p);
5123  size_t j;
5124 
5125  for (j=0; j<HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT; j++) {
5126  bits_t bits = mark_bits[j] & wbun_bits[j];
5127 
5128  if (bits) {
5129  p = offset + j * BITS_BITLENGTH;
5130 
5131  do {
5132  if (bits & 1) {
5133  gc_report(2, objspace, "gc_marks_wb_unprotected_objects: marked shady: %s\n", obj_info((VALUE)p));
5134  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE > 0) {
5135  assert(RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED((VALUE)p));
5136  assert(RVALUE_MARKED((VALUE)p));
5137  }
5138  gc_mark_children(objspace, (VALUE)p);
5139  }
5140  p++;
5141  bits >>= 1;
5142  } while (bits);
5143  }
5144  }
5145 
5146  page = page->next;
5147  }
5148 
5149  gc_mark_stacked_objects_all(objspace);
5150 }
5151 
5152 static struct heap_page *
5153 heap_move_pooled_pages_to_free_pages(rb_heap_t *heap)
5154 {
5155  struct heap_page *page = heap->pooled_pages;
5156 
5157  if (page) {
5158  heap->pooled_pages = page->free_next;
5159  page->free_next = heap->free_pages;
5160  heap->free_pages = page;
5161  }
5162 
5163  return page;
5164 }
5165 #endif
5166 
5167 static int
5168 gc_marks_finish(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
5169 {
5170 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
5171  /* finish incremental GC */
5172  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
5173  if (heap_eden->pooled_pages) {
5174  heap_move_pooled_pages_to_free_pages(heap_eden);
5175  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_marks_finish: pooled pages are exists. retry.\n");
5176  return FALSE; /* continue marking phase */
5177  }
5178 
5179  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE && is_mark_stack_empty(&objspace->mark_stack) == 0) {
5180  rb_bug("gc_marks_finish: mark stack is not empty (%d).", (int)mark_stack_size(&objspace->mark_stack));
5181  }
5182 
5183  gc_mark_roots(objspace, 0);
5184 
5185  if (is_mark_stack_empty(&objspace->mark_stack) == FALSE) {
5186  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_marks_finish: not empty (%d). retry.\n", (int)mark_stack_size(&objspace->mark_stack));
5187  return FALSE;
5188  }
5189 
5190 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 2
5191  if (gc_verify_heap_pages(objspace) != 0) {
5192  rb_bug("gc_marks_finish (incremental): there are remembered old objects.");
5193  }
5194 #endif
5195 
5196  objspace->flags.during_incremental_marking = FALSE;
5197  /* check children of all marked wb-unprotected objects */
5198  gc_marks_wb_unprotected_objects(objspace);
5199  }
5200 #endif /* GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK */
5201 
5202 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 2
5203  gc_verify_internal_consistency(Qnil);
5204 #endif
5205 
5206 #if USE_RGENGC
5207  if (is_full_marking(objspace)) {
5208  /* See the comment about RUBY_GC_HEAP_OLDOBJECT_LIMIT_FACTOR */
5209  const double r = gc_params.oldobject_limit_factor;
5210  objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects_limit = (size_t)(objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects * r);
5211  objspace->rgengc.old_objects_limit = (size_t)(objspace->rgengc.old_objects * r);
5212  }
5213 #endif
5214 
5215 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 4
5216  gc_marks_check(objspace, gc_check_after_marks_i, "after_marks");
5217 #endif
5218 
5219  { /* decide full GC is needed or not */
5220  rb_heap_t *heap = heap_eden;
5221  size_t sweep_slots =
5222  (heap_allocatable_pages * HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT) + /* allocatable slots in empty pages */
5223  (heap->total_slots - objspace->marked_slots); /* will be sweep slots */
5224 
5225 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE
5226  assert(heap->total_slots >= objspace->marked_slots);
5227 #endif
5228 
5229  if (sweep_slots < heap_pages_min_free_slots) {
5230 #if USE_RGENGC
5231  if (!is_full_marking(objspace) && objspace->profile.count - objspace->rgengc.last_major_gc > 3 /* magic number */) {
5232  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_marks_finish: next is full GC!!)\n");
5233  objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc |= GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_NOFREE;
5234  }
5235  else {
5236  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_marks_finish: heap_set_increment!!\n");
5237  heap_set_increment(objspace, heap_extend_pages(objspace));
5238  heap_increment(objspace, heap);
5239  }
5240 #else
5241  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_marks_finish: heap_set_increment!!\n");
5242  heap_set_increment(objspace, heap_extend_pages(objspace));
5243  heap_increment(objspace, heap);
5244 #endif
5245  }
5246 
5247 #if USE_RGENGC
5248  if (objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects > objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects_limit) {
5249  objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc |= GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_SHADY;
5250  }
5251  if (objspace->rgengc.old_objects > objspace->rgengc.old_objects_limit) {
5252  objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc |= GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_OLDGEN;
5253  }
5254  if (RGENGC_FORCE_MAJOR_GC) {
5255  objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc = GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_FORCE;
5256  }
5257 
5258  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_marks_finish (marks %d objects, old %d objects, total %d slots, sweep %d slots, increment: %d, next GC: %s)\n",
5259  (int)objspace->marked_slots, (int)objspace->rgengc.old_objects, (int)heap->total_slots, (int)sweep_slots, (int)heap_allocatable_pages,
5260  objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc ? "major" : "minor");
5261 #endif
5262  }
5263 
5264  gc_event_hook(objspace, RUBY_INTERNAL_EVENT_GC_END_MARK, 0);
5265 
5266  return TRUE;
5267 }
5268 
5269 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
5270 static void
5271 gc_marks_step(rb_objspace_t *objspace, int slots)
5272 {
5273  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(is_marking(objspace));
5274 
5275  if (gc_mark_stacked_objects_incremental(objspace, slots)) {
5276  if (gc_marks_finish(objspace)) {
5277  /* finish */
5278  gc_sweep(objspace);
5279  }
5280  }
5281  if (0) fprintf(stderr, "objspace->marked_slots: %d\n", (int)objspace->marked_slots);
5282 }
5283 #endif
5284 
5285 static void
5286 gc_marks_rest(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
5287 {
5288  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_marks_rest\n");
5289 
5290 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
5291  heap_eden->pooled_pages = NULL;
5292 #endif
5293 
5294  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
5295  do {
5296  while (gc_mark_stacked_objects_incremental(objspace, INT_MAX) == FALSE);
5297  } while (gc_marks_finish(objspace) == FALSE);
5298  }
5299  else {
5300  gc_mark_stacked_objects_all(objspace);
5301  gc_marks_finish(objspace);
5302  }
5303 
5304  /* move to sweep */
5305  gc_sweep(objspace);
5306 }
5307 
5308 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
5309 static void
5310 gc_marks_continue(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
5311 {
5312  int slots = 0;
5313  const char *from;
5314 
5315  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(dont_gc == FALSE);
5316 
5317  gc_enter(objspace, "marks_continue");
5318 
5319  PUSH_MARK_FUNC_DATA(NULL);
5320  {
5321  if (heap->pooled_pages) {
5322  while (heap->pooled_pages && slots < HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT) {
5323  struct heap_page *page = heap_move_pooled_pages_to_free_pages(heap);
5324  slots += page->free_slots;
5325  }
5326  from = "pooled-pages";
5327  }
5328  else if (heap_increment(objspace, heap)) {
5329  slots = heap->free_pages->free_slots;
5330  from = "incremented-pages";
5331  }
5332 
5333  if (slots > 0) {
5334  gc_report(2, objspace, "gc_marks_continue: provide %d slots from %s.\n", slots, from);
5335  gc_marks_step(objspace, (int)objspace->rincgc.step_slots);
5336  }
5337  else {
5338  gc_report(2, objspace, "gc_marks_continue: no more pooled pages (stack depth: %d).\n", (int)mark_stack_size(&objspace->mark_stack));
5339  gc_marks_rest(objspace);
5340  }
5341  }
5342  POP_MARK_FUNC_DATA();
5343 
5344  gc_exit(objspace, "marks_continue");
5345 }
5346 #endif
5347 
5348 static void
5349 gc_marks(rb_objspace_t *objspace, int full_mark)
5350 {
5351  gc_prof_mark_timer_start(objspace);
5352 
5353  PUSH_MARK_FUNC_DATA(NULL);
5354  {
5355  /* setup marking */
5356 
5357 #if USE_RGENGC
5358  gc_marks_start(objspace, full_mark);
5359  if (!is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
5360  gc_marks_rest(objspace);
5361  }
5362 
5363 #if RGENGC_PROFILE > 0
5364  if (gc_prof_record(objspace)) {
5365  gc_profile_record *record = gc_prof_record(objspace);
5366  record->old_objects = objspace->rgengc.old_objects;
5367  }
5368 #endif
5369 
5370 #else /* USE_RGENGC */
5371  gc_marks_start(objspace, TRUE);
5372  gc_marks_rest(objspace);
5373 #endif
5374  }
5375  POP_MARK_FUNC_DATA();
5376  gc_prof_mark_timer_stop(objspace);
5377 }

5381 static void
5382 gc_report_body(int level, rb_objspace_t *objspace, const char *fmt, ...)
5383 {
5384  if (level <= RGENGC_DEBUG) {
5385  char buf[1024];
5386  FILE *out = stderr;
5387  va_list args;
5388  const char *status = " ";
5389 
5390 #if USE_RGENGC
5391  if (during_gc) {
5392  status = is_full_marking(objspace) ? "+" : "-";
5393  }
5394  else {
5395  if (is_lazy_sweeping(heap_eden)) {
5396  status = "S";
5397  }
5398  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
5399  status = "M";
5400  }
5401  }
5402 #endif
5403 
5404  va_start(args, fmt);
5405  vsnprintf(buf, 1024, fmt, args);
5406  va_end(args);
5407 
5408  fprintf(out, "%s|", status);
5409  fputs(buf, out);
5410  }
5411 }
5412 
5413 #if USE_RGENGC
5414 
5415 /* bit operations */
5416 
5417 static int
5418 rgengc_remembersetbits_get(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
5419 {
5420  return RVALUE_REMEMBERED(obj);
5421 }
5422 
5423 static int
5424 rgengc_remembersetbits_set(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
5425 {
5426  struct heap_page *page = GET_HEAP_PAGE(obj);
5427  bits_t *bits = &page->marking_bits[0];
5428 
5429  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(!is_incremental_marking(objspace));
5430 
5431  if (MARKED_IN_BITMAP(bits, obj)) {
5432  return FALSE;
5433  }
5434  else {
5435  page->flags.has_remembered_objects = TRUE;
5436  MARK_IN_BITMAP(bits, obj);
5437  return TRUE;
5438  }
5439 }
5440 
5441 /* wb, etc */
5442 
5443 /* return FALSE if already remembered */
5444 static int
5445 rgengc_remember(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
5446 {
5447  gc_report(6, objspace, "rgengc_remember: %s %s\n", obj_info(obj),
5448  rgengc_remembersetbits_get(objspace, obj) ? "was already remembered" : "is remembered now");
5449 
5450  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
5451 
5452  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) {
5453  if (RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj)) rb_bug("rgengc_remember: %s is not wb protected.", obj_info(obj));
5454  }
5455 
5456 #if RGENGC_PROFILE > 0
5457  if (!rgengc_remembered(objspace, obj)) {
5458  if (RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj) == 0) {
5459  objspace->profile.total_remembered_normal_object_count++;
5460 #if RGENGC_PROFILE >= 2
5461  objspace->profile.remembered_normal_object_count_types[BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)]++;
5462 #endif
5463  }
5464  }
5465 #endif /* RGENGC_PROFILE > 0 */
5466 
5467  return rgengc_remembersetbits_set(objspace, obj);
5468 }
5469 
5470 static int
5471 rgengc_remembered(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj)
5472 {
5473  int result = rgengc_remembersetbits_get(objspace, obj);
5474  check_rvalue_consistency(obj);
5475  gc_report(6, objspace, "rgengc_remembered: %s\n", obj_info(obj));
5476  return result;
5477 }
5478 
5479 #ifndef PROFILE_REMEMBERSET_MARK
5480 #define PROFILE_REMEMBERSET_MARK 0
5481 #endif
5482 
5483 static void
5484 rgengc_rememberset_mark(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
5485 {
5486  size_t j;
5487  struct heap_page *page = heap->pages;
5488 #if PROFILE_REMEMBERSET_MARK
5489  int has_old = 0, has_shady = 0, has_both = 0, skip = 0;
5490 #endif
5491  gc_report(1, objspace, "rgengc_rememberset_mark: start\n");
5492 
5493  while (page) {
5494  if (page->flags.has_remembered_objects | page->flags.has_uncollectible_shady_objects) {
5495  RVALUE *p = page->start;
5496  RVALUE *offset = p - NUM_IN_PAGE(p);
5497  bits_t bitset, bits[HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT];
5498  bits_t *marking_bits = page->marking_bits;
5499  bits_t *uncollectible_bits = page->uncollectible_bits;
5500  bits_t *wb_unprotected_bits = page->wb_unprotected_bits;
5501 #if PROFILE_REMEMBERSET_MARK
5502  if (page->flags.has_remembered_objects && page->flags.has_uncollectible_shady_objects) has_both++;
5503  else if (page->flags.has_remembered_objects) has_old++;
5504  else if (page->flags.has_uncollectible_shady_objects) has_shady++;
5505 #endif
5506  for (j=0; j<HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT; j++) {
5507  bits[j] = marking_bits[j] | (uncollectible_bits[j] & wb_unprotected_bits[j]);
5508  marking_bits[j] = 0;
5509  }
5510  page->flags.has_remembered_objects = FALSE;
5511 
5512  for (j=0; j < HEAP_BITMAP_LIMIT; j++) {
5513  bitset = bits[j];
5514 
5515  if (bitset) {
5516  p = offset + j * BITS_BITLENGTH;
5517 
5518  do {
5519  if (bitset & 1) {
5520  VALUE obj = (VALUE)p;
5521  gc_report(2, objspace, "rgengc_rememberset_mark: mark %s\n", obj_info(obj));
5522 
5523  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) {
5524  assert(RVALUE_UNCOLLECTIBLE(obj));
5525  assert(RVALUE_OLD_P(obj) || RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj));
5526  }
5527 
5528  gc_mark_children(objspace, obj);
5529  }
5530  p++;
5531  bitset >>= 1;
5532  } while (bitset);
5533  }
5534  }
5535  }
5536 #if PROFILE_REMEMBERSET_MARK
5537  else {
5538  skip++;
5539  }
5540 #endif
5541 
5542  page = page->next;
5543  }
5544 
5545 #if PROFILE_REMEMBERSET_MARK
5546  fprintf(stderr, "%d\t%d\t%d\t%d\n", has_both, has_old, has_shady, skip);
5547 #endif
5548  gc_report(1, objspace, "rgengc_rememberset_mark: finished\n");
5549 }
5550 
5551 static void
5552 rgengc_mark_and_rememberset_clear(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
5553 {
5554  struct heap_page *page = heap->pages;
5555 
5556  while (page) {
5557  memset(&page->mark_bits[0], 0, HEAP_BITMAP_SIZE);
5558  memset(&page->marking_bits[0], 0, HEAP_BITMAP_SIZE);
5559  memset(&page->uncollectible_bits[0], 0, HEAP_BITMAP_SIZE);
5560  page->flags.has_uncollectible_shady_objects = FALSE;
5561  page->flags.has_remembered_objects = FALSE;
5562  page = page->next;
5563  }
5564 }
5565 
5566 /* RGENGC: APIs */
5567 
5568 NOINLINE(static void gc_writebarrier_generational(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE a, VALUE b));
5569 
5570 static void
5571 gc_writebarrier_generational(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE a, VALUE b)
5572 {
5573  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) {
5574  if (!RVALUE_OLD_P(a)) rb_bug("gc_writebarrier_generational: %s is not an old object.", obj_info(a));
5575  if ( RVALUE_OLD_P(b)) rb_bug("gc_writebarrier_generational: %s is an old object.", obj_info(b));
5576  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) rb_bug("gc_writebarrier_generational: called while incremental marking: %s -> %s", obj_info(a), obj_info(b));
5577  }
5578 
5579 #if 1
5580  /* mark `a' and remember (default behaviour) */
5581  if (!rgengc_remembered(objspace, a)) {
5582  rgengc_remember(objspace, a);
5583  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_writebarrier_generational: %s (remembered) -> %s\n", obj_info(a), obj_info(b));
5584  }
5585 #else
5586  /* mark `b' and remember */
5587  MARK_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARK_BITS(b), b);
5588  if (RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(b)) {
5589  gc_remember_unprotected(objspace, b);
5590  }
5591  else {
5592  RVALUE_AGE_SET_OLD(objspace, b);
5593  rgengc_remember(objspace, b);
5594  }
5595 
5596  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_writebarrier_generational: %s -> %s (remembered)\n", obj_info(a), obj_info(b));
5597 #endif
5598 
5599  check_rvalue_consistency(a);
5600  check_rvalue_consistency(b);
5601 }
5602 
5603 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
5604 static void
5605 gc_mark_from(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE obj, VALUE parent)
5606 {
5607  gc_mark_set_parent(objspace, parent);
5608  rgengc_check_relation(objspace, obj);
5609  if (gc_mark_set(objspace, obj) == FALSE) return;
5610  gc_aging(objspace, obj);
5611  gc_grey(objspace, obj);
5612 }
5613 
5614 NOINLINE(static void gc_writebarrier_incremental(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE a, VALUE b));
5615 
5616 static void
5617 gc_writebarrier_incremental(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE a, VALUE b)
5618 {
5619  gc_report(2, objspace, "gc_writebarrier_incremental: [LG] %s -> %s\n", obj_info(a), obj_info(b));
5620 
5621  if (RVALUE_BLACK_P(a)) {
5622  if (RVALUE_WHITE_P(b)) {
5623  if (!RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(a)) {
5624  gc_report(2, objspace, "gc_writebarrier_incremental: [IN] %s -> %s\n", obj_info(a), obj_info(b));
5625  gc_mark_from(objspace, b, a);
5626  }
5627  }
5628  else if (RVALUE_OLD_P(a) && !RVALUE_OLD_P(b)) {
5629  if (!RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(b)) {
5630  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_writebarrier_incremental: [GN] %s -> %s\n", obj_info(a), obj_info(b));
5631  RVALUE_AGE_SET_OLD(objspace, b);
5632 
5633  if (RVALUE_BLACK_P(b)) {
5634  gc_grey(objspace, b);
5635  }
5636  }
5637  else {
5638  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_writebarrier_incremental: [LL] %s -> %s\n", obj_info(a), obj_info(b));
5639  gc_remember_unprotected(objspace, b);
5640  }
5641  }
5642  }
5643 }
5644 #else
5645 #define gc_writebarrier_incremental(objspace, a, b)
5646 #endif
5647 
5648 void
5649 rb_gc_writebarrier(VALUE a, VALUE b)
5650 {
5651  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
5652 
5653  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE && SPECIAL_CONST_P(a)) rb_bug("rb_gc_writebarrier: a is special const");
5654  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE && SPECIAL_CONST_P(b)) rb_bug("rb_gc_writebarrier: b is special const");
5655 
5656  if (LIKELY(!is_incremental_marking(objspace))) {
5657  if (!RVALUE_OLD_P(a) || RVALUE_OLD_P(b)) {
5658  return;
5659  }
5660  else {
5661  gc_writebarrier_generational(objspace, a, b);
5662  }
5663  }
5664  else { /* slow path */
5665  gc_writebarrier_incremental(objspace, a, b);
5666  }
5667 }
5668 
5669 void
5670 rb_gc_writebarrier_unprotect(VALUE obj)
5671 {
5672  if (RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj)) {
5673  return;
5674  }
5675  else {
5676  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
5677 
5678  gc_report(2, objspace, "rb_gc_writebarrier_unprotect: %s %s\n", obj_info(obj),
5679  rgengc_remembered(objspace, obj) ? " (already remembered)" : "");
5680 
5681  if (RVALUE_OLD_P(obj)) {
5682  gc_report(1, objspace, "rb_gc_writebarrier_unprotect: %s\n", obj_info(obj));
5683  RVALUE_DEMOTE(objspace, obj);
5684  gc_mark_set(objspace, obj);
5685  gc_remember_unprotected(objspace, obj);
5686 
5687 #if RGENGC_PROFILE
5688  objspace->profile.total_shade_operation_count++;
5689 #if RGENGC_PROFILE >= 2
5690  objspace->profile.shade_operation_count_types[BUILTIN_TYPE(obj)]++;
5691 #endif /* RGENGC_PROFILE >= 2 */
5692 #endif /* RGENGC_PROFILE */
5693  }
5694  else {
5695  RVALUE_AGE_RESET(obj);
5696  }
5697 
5698  MARK_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_WB_UNPROTECTED_BITS(obj), obj);
5699  }
5700 }

5702 /*
5703  * remember `obj' if needed.
5704  */
5705 void
5706 rb_gc_writebarrier_remember(VALUE obj)
5707 {
5708  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
5709 
5710  gc_report(1, objspace, "rb_gc_writebarrier_remember: %s\n", obj_info(obj));
5711 
5712  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
5713  if (RVALUE_BLACK_P(obj)) {
5714  gc_grey(objspace, obj);
5715  }
5716  }
5717  else {
5718  if (RVALUE_OLD_P(obj)) {
5719  rgengc_remember(objspace, obj);
5720  }
5721  }
5722 }

5739 void
5740 rb_gc_unprotect_logging(void *objptr, const char *filename, int line)
5741 {
5742  VALUE obj = (VALUE)objptr;
5743 
5744  if (rgengc_unprotect_logging_table == 0) {
5745  rgengc_unprotect_logging_table = st_init_strtable();
5746  atexit(rgengc_unprotect_logging_exit_func);
5747  }
5748 
5749  if (RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj) == 0) {
5750  char buff[0x100];
5751  st_data_t cnt = 1;
5752  char *ptr = buff;
5753 
5754  snprintf(ptr, 0x100 - 1, "%s|%s:%d", obj_info(obj), filename, line);
5755 
5756  if (st_lookup(rgengc_unprotect_logging_table, (st_data_t)ptr, &cnt)) {
5757  cnt++;
5758  }
5759  else {
5760  ptr = (char *)malloc(strlen(buff) + 1);
5761  strcpy(ptr, buff);
5762  }
5763  st_insert(rgengc_unprotect_logging_table, (st_data_t)ptr, cnt);
5764  }
5765 }
5766 #endif /* USE_RGENGC */

5806 size_t
5807 rb_obj_gc_flags(VALUE obj, ID* flags, size_t max)
5808 {
5809  size_t n = 0;
5810  static ID ID_marked;
5811 #if USE_RGENGC
5812  static ID ID_wb_protected, ID_old, ID_marking, ID_uncollectible;
5813 #endif
5814 
5815  if (!ID_marked) {
5816 #define I(s) ID_##s = rb_intern(#s);
5817  I(marked);
5818 #if USE_RGENGC
5819  I(wb_protected);
5820  I(old);
5821  I(marking);
5822  I(uncollectible);
5823 #endif
5824 #undef I
5825  }
5826 
5827 #if USE_RGENGC
5828  if (RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj) == 0 && n<max) flags[n++] = ID_wb_protected;
5829  if (RVALUE_OLD_P(obj) && n<max) flags[n++] = ID_old;
5830  if (RVALUE_UNCOLLECTIBLE(obj) && n<max) flags[n++] = ID_uncollectible;
5831  if (MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARKING_BITS(obj), obj) && n<max) flags[n++] = ID_marking;
5832 #endif
5833  if (MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARK_BITS(obj), obj) && n<max) flags[n++] = ID_marked;
5834  return n;
5835 }

5839 void
5840 rb_gc_force_recycle(VALUE obj)
5841 {
5842  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
5843 
5844 #if USE_RGENGC
5845  int is_old = RVALUE_OLD_P(obj);
5846 
5847  gc_report(2, objspace, "rb_gc_force_recycle: %s\n", obj_info(obj));
5848 
5849  if (is_old) {
5850  if (RVALUE_MARKED(obj)) {
5851  objspace->rgengc.old_objects--;
5852  }
5853  }
5854  CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_UNCOLLECTIBLE_BITS(obj), obj);
5855  CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_WB_UNPROTECTED_BITS(obj), obj);
5856 
5857 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
5858  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
5859  if (MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARKING_BITS(obj), obj)) {
5860  invalidate_mark_stack(&objspace->mark_stack, obj);
5861  CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARKING_BITS(obj), obj);
5862  }
5863  CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARK_BITS(obj), obj);
5864  }
5865  else {
5866 #endif
5867  if (is_old || !GET_HEAP_PAGE(obj)->flags.before_sweep) {
5868  CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARK_BITS(obj), obj);
5869  }
5870  CLEAR_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARKING_BITS(obj), obj);
5871 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
5872  }
5873 #endif
5874 #endif
5875 
5876  objspace->profile.total_freed_objects++;
5877 
5878  heap_page_add_freeobj(objspace, GET_HEAP_PAGE(obj), obj);
5879 
5880  /* Disable counting swept_slots because there are no meaning.
5881  * if (!MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARK_BITS(p), p)) {
5882  * objspace->heap.swept_slots++;
5883  * }
5884  */
5885 }

5905 void
5906 rb_gc_register_address(VALUE *addr)
5907 {
5908  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
5909  struct gc_list *tmp;
5910 
5911  tmp = ALLOC(struct gc_list);
5912  tmp->next = global_list;
5913  tmp->varptr = addr;
5914  global_list = tmp;
5915 }
5916 
5917 void
5918 rb_gc_unregister_address(VALUE *addr)
5919 {
5920  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
5921  struct gc_list *tmp = global_list;
5922 
5923  if (tmp->varptr == addr) {
5924  global_list = tmp->next;
5925  xfree(tmp);
5926  return;
5927  }
5928  while (tmp->next) {
5929  if (tmp->next->varptr == addr) {
5930  struct gc_list *t = tmp->next;
5931 
5932  tmp->next = tmp->next->next;
5933  xfree(t);
5934  break;
5935  }
5936  tmp = tmp->next;
5937  }
5938 }
5939 
5940 void
5941 rb_global_variable(VALUE *var)
5942 {
5943  rb_gc_register_address(var);
5944 }

5946 #define GC_NOTIFY 0
5947 
5948 enum {
5949  gc_stress_no_major,
5950  gc_stress_no_immediate_sweep,
5951  gc_stress_full_mark_after_malloc,
5952  gc_stress_max
5953 };
5954 
5955 #define gc_stress_full_mark_after_malloc_p() \
5956  (FIXNUM_P(ruby_gc_stress_mode) && (FIX2LONG(ruby_gc_stress_mode) & (1<<gc_stress_full_mark_after_malloc)))
5957 
5958 static void
5959 heap_ready_to_gc(rb_objspace_t *objspace, rb_heap_t *heap)
5960 {
5961  if (!heap->freelist && !heap->free_pages) {
5962  if (!heap_increment(objspace, heap)) {
5963  heap_set_increment(objspace, 1);
5964  heap_increment(objspace, heap);
5965  }
5966  }
5967 }

5969 static int
5970 ready_to_gc(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
5971 {
5972  if (dont_gc || during_gc || ruby_disable_gc) {
5973  heap_ready_to_gc(objspace, heap_eden);
5974  return FALSE;
5975  }
5976  else {
5977  return TRUE;
5978  }
5979 }
5980 
5981 static void
5982 gc_reset_malloc_info(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
5983 {
5984  gc_prof_set_malloc_info(objspace);
5985  {
5986  size_t inc = ATOMIC_SIZE_EXCHANGE(malloc_increase, 0);
5987  size_t old_limit = malloc_limit;
5988 
5989  if (inc > malloc_limit) {
5990  malloc_limit = (size_t)(inc * gc_params.malloc_limit_growth_factor);
5991  if (gc_params.malloc_limit_max > 0 && /* ignore max-check if 0 */
5992  malloc_limit > gc_params.malloc_limit_max) {
5993  malloc_limit = gc_params.malloc_limit_max;
5994  }
5995  }
5996  else {
5997  malloc_limit = (size_t)(malloc_limit * 0.98); /* magic number */
5998  if (malloc_limit < gc_params.malloc_limit_min) {
5999  malloc_limit = gc_params.malloc_limit_min;
6000  }
6001  }
6002 
6003  if (0) {
6004  if (old_limit != malloc_limit) {
6005  fprintf(stderr, "[%"PRIuSIZE"] malloc_limit: %"PRIuSIZE" -> %"PRIuSIZE"\n",
6006  rb_gc_count(), old_limit, malloc_limit);
6007  }
6008  else {
6009  fprintf(stderr, "[%"PRIuSIZE"] malloc_limit: not changed (%"PRIuSIZE")\n",
6010  rb_gc_count(), malloc_limit);
6011  }
6012  }
6013  }
6014 
6015  /* reset oldmalloc info */
6016 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
6017  if (!is_full_marking(objspace)) {
6018  if (objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase > objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit) {
6019  objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc |= GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_OLDMALLOC;;
6020  objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit =
6021  (size_t)(objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit * gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_growth_factor);
6022 
6023  if (objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit > gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_max) {
6024  objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit = gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_max;
6025  }
6026  }
6027 
6028  if (0) fprintf(stderr, "%d\t%d\t%u\t%u\t%d\n",
6029  (int)rb_gc_count(),
6030  (int)objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc,
6031  (unsigned int)objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase,
6032  (unsigned int)objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit,
6033  (unsigned int)gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_max);
6034  }
6035  else {
6036  /* major GC */
6037  objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase = 0;
6038 
6039  if ((objspace->profile.latest_gc_info & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_OLDMALLOC) == 0) {
6040  objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit =
6041  (size_t)(objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit / ((gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_growth_factor - 1)/10 + 1));
6042  if (objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit < gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_min) {
6043  objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit = gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_min;
6044  }
6045  }
6046  }
6047 #endif
6048 }
6049 
6050 static int
6051 garbage_collect(rb_objspace_t *objspace, int full_mark, int immediate_mark, int immediate_sweep, int reason)
6052 {
6053 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
6054  objspace->profile.prepare_time = getrusage_time();
6055 #endif
6056 
6057  gc_rest(objspace);
6058 
6059 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
6060  objspace->profile.prepare_time = getrusage_time() - objspace->profile.prepare_time;
6061 #endif
6062 
6063  return gc_start(objspace, full_mark, immediate_mark, immediate_sweep, reason);
6064 }
6065 
6066 static int
6067 gc_start(rb_objspace_t *objspace, const int full_mark, const int immediate_mark, const unsigned int immediate_sweep, int reason)
6068 {
6069  int do_full_mark = full_mark;
6070  objspace->flags.immediate_sweep = immediate_sweep;
6071 
6072  if (!heap_allocated_pages) return FALSE; /* heap is not ready */
6073  if (!ready_to_gc(objspace)) return TRUE; /* GC is not allowed */
6074 
6075  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) {
6076  assert(objspace->flags.stat == gc_stat_none);
6077  assert(!is_lazy_sweeping(heap_eden));
6078  assert(!is_incremental_marking(objspace));
6079 #if RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 2
6080  gc_verify_internal_consistency(Qnil);
6081 #endif
6082  }
6083 
6084  gc_enter(objspace, "gc_start");
6085 
6086  if (ruby_gc_stressful) {
6087  int flag = FIXNUM_P(ruby_gc_stress_mode) ? FIX2INT(ruby_gc_stress_mode) : 0;
6088 
6089  if ((flag & (1<<gc_stress_no_major)) == 0) {
6090  do_full_mark = TRUE;
6091  }
6092 
6093  objspace->flags.immediate_sweep = !(flag & (1<<gc_stress_no_immediate_sweep));
6094  }
6095  else {
6096 #if USE_RGENGC
6097  if (objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc) {
6098  reason |= objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc;
6099  do_full_mark = TRUE;
6100  }
6101  else if (RGENGC_FORCE_MAJOR_GC) {
6102  reason = GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_FORCE;
6103  do_full_mark = TRUE;
6104  }
6105 
6106  objspace->rgengc.need_major_gc = GPR_FLAG_NONE;
6107 #endif
6108  }
6109 
6110  if (do_full_mark && (reason & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_MASK) == 0) {
6111  reason |= GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_FORCE; /* GC by CAPI, METHOD, and so on. */
6112  }
6113 
6114 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
6115  if (!GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK || objspace->flags.dont_incremental || immediate_mark) {
6116  objspace->flags.during_incremental_marking = FALSE;
6117  }
6118  else {
6119  objspace->flags.during_incremental_marking = do_full_mark;
6120  }
6121 #endif
6122 
6123  if (!GC_ENABLE_LAZY_SWEEP || objspace->flags.dont_incremental) {
6124  objspace->flags.immediate_sweep = TRUE;
6125  }
6126 
6127  if (objspace->flags.immediate_sweep) reason |= GPR_FLAG_IMMEDIATE_SWEEP;
6128 
6129  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_start(%d, %d, %d, reason: %d) => %d, %d, %d\n",
6130  full_mark, immediate_mark, immediate_sweep, reason,
6131  do_full_mark, !is_incremental_marking(objspace), objspace->flags.immediate_sweep);
6132 
6133  objspace->profile.count++;
6134  objspace->profile.latest_gc_info = reason;
6135  objspace->profile.total_allocated_objects_at_gc_start = objspace->total_allocated_objects;
6136  objspace->profile.heap_used_at_gc_start = heap_allocated_pages;
6137  gc_prof_setup_new_record(objspace, reason);
6138  gc_reset_malloc_info(objspace);
6139 
6140  gc_event_hook(objspace, RUBY_INTERNAL_EVENT_GC_START, 0 /* TODO: pass minor/immediate flag? */);
6141  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(during_gc);
6142 
6143  gc_prof_timer_start(objspace);
6144  {
6145  gc_marks(objspace, do_full_mark);
6146  }
6147  gc_prof_timer_stop(objspace);
6148 
6149  gc_exit(objspace, "gc_start");
6150  return TRUE;
6151 }
6152 
6153 static void
6154 gc_rest(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
6155 {
6156  int marking = is_incremental_marking(objspace);
6157  int sweeping = is_lazy_sweeping(heap_eden);
6158 
6159  if (marking || sweeping) {
6160  gc_enter(objspace, "gc_rest");
6161 
6162  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 2) gc_verify_internal_consistency(Qnil);
6163 
6164  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) {
6165  PUSH_MARK_FUNC_DATA(NULL);
6166  gc_marks_rest(objspace);
6167  POP_MARK_FUNC_DATA();
6168  }
6169  if (is_lazy_sweeping(heap_eden)) {
6170  gc_sweep_rest(objspace);
6171  }
6172  gc_exit(objspace, "gc_rest");
6173  }
6174 }
6175 
6176 struct objspace_and_reason {
6177  rb_objspace_t *objspace;
6178  int reason;
6179  int full_mark;
6180  int immediate_mark;
6181  int immediate_sweep;
6182 };
6183 
6184 static void
6185 gc_current_status_fill(rb_objspace_t *objspace, char *buff)
6186 {
6187  int i = 0;
6188  if (is_marking(objspace)) {
6189  buff[i++] = 'M';
6190 #if USE_RGENGC
6191  if (is_full_marking(objspace)) buff[i++] = 'F';
6192 #if GC_ENABLE_INCREMENTAL_MARK
6193  if (is_incremental_marking(objspace)) buff[i++] = 'I';
6194 #endif
6195 #endif
6196  }
6197  else if (is_sweeping(objspace)) {
6198  buff[i++] = 'S';
6199  if (is_lazy_sweeping(heap_eden)) buff[i++] = 'L';
6200  }
6201  else {
6202  buff[i++] = 'N';
6203  }
6204  buff[i] = '\0';
6205 }
6206 
6207 static const char *
6208 gc_current_status(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
6209 {
6210  static char buff[0x10];
6211  gc_current_status_fill(objspace, buff);
6212  return buff;
6213 }
6214 
6215 #if PRINT_ENTER_EXIT_TICK
6216 
6217 static tick_t last_exit_tick;
6218 static tick_t enter_tick;
6219 static int enter_count = 0;
6220 static char last_gc_status[0x10];
6221 
6222 static inline void
6223 gc_record(rb_objspace_t *objspace, int direction, const char *event)
6224 {
6225  if (direction == 0) { /* enter */
6226  enter_count++;
6227  enter_tick = tick();
6228  gc_current_status_fill(objspace, last_gc_status);
6229  }
6230  else { /* exit */
6231  tick_t exit_tick = tick();
6232  char current_gc_status[0x10];
6233  gc_current_status_fill(objspace, current_gc_status);
6234 #if 1
6235  /* [last mutator time] [gc time] [event] */
6236  fprintf(stderr, "%"PRItick"\t%"PRItick"\t%s\t[%s->%s|%c]\n",
6237  enter_tick - last_exit_tick,
6238  exit_tick - enter_tick,
6239  event,
6240  last_gc_status, current_gc_status,
6241  (objspace->profile.latest_gc_info & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_MASK) ? '+' : '-');
6242  last_exit_tick = exit_tick;
6243 #else
6244  /* [enter_tick] [gc time] [event] */
6245  fprintf(stderr, "%"PRItick"\t%"PRItick"\t%s\t[%s->%s|%c]\n",
6246  enter_tick,
6247  exit_tick - enter_tick,
6248  event,
6249  last_gc_status, current_gc_status,
6250  (objspace->profile.latest_gc_info & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_MASK) ? '+' : '-');
6251 #endif
6252  }
6253 }
6254 #else /* PRINT_ENTER_EXIT_TICK */
6255 static inline void
6256 gc_record(rb_objspace_t *objspace, int direction, const char *event)
6257 {
6258  /* null */
6259 }
6260 #endif /* PRINT_ENTER_EXIT_TICK */
6261 
6262 static inline void
6263 gc_enter(rb_objspace_t *objspace, const char *event)
6264 {
6265  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(during_gc == 0);
6266  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE >= 3) gc_verify_internal_consistency(Qnil);
6267 
6268  during_gc = TRUE;
6269  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_entr: %s [%s]\n", event, gc_current_status(objspace));
6270  gc_record(objspace, 0, event);
6271  gc_event_hook(objspace, RUBY_INTERNAL_EVENT_GC_ENTER, 0); /* TODO: which parameter should be passed? */
6272 }
6273 
6274 static inline void
6275 gc_exit(rb_objspace_t *objspace, const char *event)
6276 {
6277  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(during_gc != 0);
6278 
6279  gc_event_hook(objspace, RUBY_INTERNAL_EVENT_GC_EXIT, 0); /* TODO: which parameter should be passsed? */
6280  gc_record(objspace, 1, event);
6281  gc_report(1, objspace, "gc_exit: %s [%s]\n", event, gc_current_status(objspace));
6282  during_gc = FALSE;
6283 }
6284 
6285 static void *
6286 gc_with_gvl(void *ptr)
6287 {
6288  struct objspace_and_reason *oar = (struct objspace_and_reason *)ptr;
6289  return (void *)(VALUE)garbage_collect(oar->objspace, oar->full_mark, oar->immediate_mark, oar->immediate_sweep, oar->reason);
6290 }
6291 
6292 static int
6293 garbage_collect_with_gvl(rb_objspace_t *objspace, int full_mark, int immediate_mark, int immediate_sweep, int reason)
6294 {
6295  if (dont_gc) return TRUE;
6296  if (ruby_thread_has_gvl_p()) {
6297  return garbage_collect(objspace, full_mark, immediate_mark, immediate_sweep, reason);
6298  }
6299  else {
6300  if (ruby_native_thread_p()) {
6301  struct objspace_and_reason oar;
6302  oar.objspace = objspace;
6303  oar.reason = reason;
6304  oar.full_mark = full_mark;
6305  oar.immediate_mark = immediate_mark;
6306  oar.immediate_sweep = immediate_sweep;
6307  return (int)(VALUE)rb_thread_call_with_gvl(gc_with_gvl, (void *)&oar);
6308  }
6309  else {
6310  /* no ruby thread */
6311  fprintf(stderr, "[FATAL] failed to allocate memory\n");
6312  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
6313  }
6314  }
6315 }
6316 
6317 int
6318 rb_garbage_collect(void)
6319 {
6320  return garbage_collect(&rb_objspace, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, GPR_FLAG_CAPI);
6321 }

6326 Init_stack(volatile VALUE *addr)

6330 
6331 /*
6332  * call-seq:
6333  * GC.start -> nil
6334  * GC.garbage_collect -> nil
6335  * GC.start(full_mark: true, immediate_sweep: true) -> nil
6336  * GC.garbage_collect(full_mark: true, immediate_sweep: true) -> nil
6337  *
6338  * Initiates garbage collection, unless manually disabled.
6339  *
6340  * This method is defined with keyword arguments that default to true:
6341  *
6342  * def GC.start(full_mark: true, immediate_sweep: true); end
6343  *
6344  * Use full_mark: false to perform a minor GC.
6345  * Use immediate_sweep: false to defer sweeping (use lazy sweep).
6346  *
6347  * Note: These keyword arguments are implementation and version dependent. They
6348  * are not guaranteed to be future-compatible, and may be ignored if the
6349  * underlying implementation does not support them.
6350  */
6351 
6352 static VALUE
6353 gc_start_internal(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE self)
6354 {
6355  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
6356  int full_mark = TRUE, immediate_mark = TRUE, immediate_sweep = TRUE;
6357  VALUE opt = Qnil;
6358  static ID keyword_ids[3];
6359 
6360  rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "0:", &opt);
6361 
6362  if (!NIL_P(opt)) {
6363  VALUE kwvals[3];
6364 
6365  if (!keyword_ids[0]) {
6366  keyword_ids[0] = rb_intern("full_mark");
6367  keyword_ids[1] = rb_intern("immediate_mark");
6368  keyword_ids[2] = rb_intern("immediate_sweep");
6369  }
6370 
6371  rb_get_kwargs(opt, keyword_ids, 0, 3, kwvals);
6372 
6373  if (kwvals[0] != Qundef) full_mark = RTEST(kwvals[0]);
6374  if (kwvals[1] != Qundef) immediate_mark = RTEST(kwvals[1]);
6375  if (kwvals[2] != Qundef) immediate_sweep = RTEST(kwvals[2]);
6376  }
6377 
6378  garbage_collect(objspace, full_mark, immediate_mark, immediate_sweep, GPR_FLAG_METHOD);
6379  if (!finalizing) finalize_deferred(objspace);
6380 
6381  return Qnil;
6382 }
6383 
6384 VALUE
6385 rb_gc_start(void)
6386 {
6387  rb_gc();
6388  return Qnil;
6389 }
6390 
6391 void
6392 rb_gc(void)
6393 {
6394  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
6395  garbage_collect(objspace, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, GPR_FLAG_CAPI);
6396  if (!finalizing) finalize_deferred(objspace);
6397 }

6409 
6410 static void
6411 gc_count_add_each_types(VALUE hash, const char *name, const size_t *types)
6412 {
6413  VALUE result = rb_hash_new();
6414  int i;
6415  for (i=0; i<T_MASK; i++) {
6416  const char *type = type_name(i, 0);
6417  rb_hash_aset(result, ID2SYM(rb_intern(type)), SIZET2NUM(types[i]));
6418  }
6419  rb_hash_aset(hash, ID2SYM(rb_intern(name)), result);
6420 }
6421 #endif
