6445 static VALUE
6446 gc_info_decode(rb_objspace_t *objspace, const VALUE hash_or_key, const int orig_flags)
6447 {
6448  static VALUE sym_major_by = Qnil, sym_gc_by, sym_immediate_sweep, sym_have_finalizer, sym_state;
6449  static VALUE sym_nofree, sym_oldgen, sym_shady, sym_force, sym_stress;
6450 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
6451  static VALUE sym_oldmalloc;
6452 #endif
6453  static VALUE sym_newobj, sym_malloc, sym_method, sym_capi;
6454  static VALUE sym_none, sym_marking, sym_sweeping;
6455  VALUE hash = Qnil, key = Qnil;
6456  VALUE major_by;
6457  VALUE flags = orig_flags ? orig_flags : objspace->profile.latest_gc_info;
6458 
6459  if (SYMBOL_P(hash_or_key)) {
6460  key = hash_or_key;
6461  }
6462  else if (RB_TYPE_P(hash_or_key, T_HASH)) {
6463  hash = hash_or_key;
6464  }
6465  else {
6466  rb_raise(rb_eTypeError, "non-hash or symbol given");
6467  }
6468 
6469  if (sym_major_by == Qnil) {
6470 #define S(s) sym_##s = ID2SYM(rb_intern_const(#s))
6471  S(major_by);
6472  S(gc_by);
6473  S(immediate_sweep);
6474  S(have_finalizer);
6475  S(state);
6476 
6477  S(stress);
6478  S(nofree);
6479  S(oldgen);
6480  S(shady);
6481  S(force);
6482 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
6483  S(oldmalloc);
6484 #endif
6485  S(newobj);
6486  S(malloc);
6487  S(method);
6488  S(capi);
6489 
6490  S(none);
6491  S(marking);
6492  S(sweeping);
6493 #undef S
6494  }
6495 
6496 #define SET(name, attr) \
6497  if (key == sym_##name) \
6498  return (attr); \
6499  else if (hash != Qnil) \
6500  rb_hash_aset(hash, sym_##name, (attr));
6501 
6502  major_by =
6503  (flags & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_NOFREE) ? sym_nofree :
6504  (flags & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_OLDGEN) ? sym_oldgen :
6505  (flags & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_SHADY) ? sym_shady :
6506  (flags & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_FORCE) ? sym_force :
6507 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
6508  (flags & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_OLDMALLOC) ? sym_oldmalloc :
6509 #endif
6510  Qnil;
6511  SET(major_by, major_by);
6512 
6513  SET(gc_by,
6514  (flags & GPR_FLAG_NEWOBJ) ? sym_newobj :
6515  (flags & GPR_FLAG_MALLOC) ? sym_malloc :
6516  (flags & GPR_FLAG_METHOD) ? sym_method :
6517  (flags & GPR_FLAG_CAPI) ? sym_capi :
6518  (flags & GPR_FLAG_STRESS) ? sym_stress :
6519  Qnil
6520  );
6521 
6522  SET(have_finalizer, (flags & GPR_FLAG_HAVE_FINALIZE) ? Qtrue : Qfalse);
6523  SET(immediate_sweep, (flags & GPR_FLAG_IMMEDIATE_SWEEP) ? Qtrue : Qfalse);
6524 
6525  if (orig_flags == 0) {
6526  SET(state, objspace->flags.stat == gc_stat_none ? sym_none :
6527  objspace->flags.stat == gc_stat_marking ? sym_marking : sym_sweeping);
6528  }
6529 #undef SET
6530 
6531  if (!NIL_P(key)) {/* matched key should return above */
6532  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "unknown key: %"PRIsVALUE, rb_sym2str(key));
6533  }
6534 
6535  return hash;
6536 }

6538 VALUE
6539 rb_gc_latest_gc_info(VALUE key)
6540 {
6541  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
6542  return gc_info_decode(objspace, key, 0);
6543 }
6544 
6545 /*
6546  * call-seq:
6547  * GC.latest_gc_info -> {:gc_by=>:newobj}
6548  * GC.latest_gc_info(hash) -> hash
6549  * GC.latest_gc_info(:major_by) -> :malloc
6550  *
6551  * Returns information about the most recent garbage collection.
6552  */
6553 
6554 static VALUE
6555 gc_latest_gc_info(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE self)
6556 {
6557  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
6558  VALUE arg = Qnil;
6559 
6560  if (rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "01", &arg) == 1) {
6561  if (!SYMBOL_P(arg) && !RB_TYPE_P(arg, T_HASH)) {
6562  rb_raise(rb_eTypeError, "non-hash or symbol given");
6563  }
6564  }
6565 
6566  if (arg == Qnil) {
6567  arg = rb_hash_new();
6568  }
6569 
6570  return gc_info_decode(objspace, arg, 0);
6571 }

6671  S(major_gc_count);
6672  S(remembered_wb_unprotected_objects);
6673  S(remembered_wb_unprotected_objects_limit);
6674  S(old_objects);
6675  S(old_objects_limit);
6676 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
6677  S(oldmalloc_increase_bytes);
6678  S(oldmalloc_increase_bytes_limit);
6679 #endif
6680 #if RGENGC_PROFILE
6681  S(total_generated_normal_object_count);
6682  S(total_generated_shady_object_count);
6683  S(total_shade_operation_count);
6684  S(total_promoted_count);
6685  S(total_remembered_normal_object_count);
6686  S(total_remembered_shady_object_count);
6687 #endif /* RGENGC_PROFILE */
6688 #endif /* USE_RGENGC */
6689 #undef S
6690 #define S(s) gc_stat_compat_symbols[gc_stat_compat_sym_##s] = ID2SYM(rb_intern_const(#s))
6691  S(gc_stat_heap_used);
6692  S(heap_eden_page_length);
6693  S(heap_tomb_page_length);
6694  S(heap_increment);
6695  S(heap_length);
6696  S(heap_live_slot);
6697  S(heap_free_slot);
6698  S(heap_final_slot);
6699  S(heap_swept_slot);
6700 #if USE_RGEGC
6701  S(remembered_shady_object);
6702  S(remembered_shady_object_limit);
6703  S(old_object);
6704  S(old_object_limit);
6705 #endif
6706  S(total_allocated_object);
6707  S(total_freed_object);
6708  S(malloc_increase);
6709  S(malloc_limit);
6710 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
6711  S(oldmalloc_increase);
6712  S(oldmalloc_limit);
6713 #endif
6714 #undef S
6715 
6716  {
6717  VALUE table = gc_stat_compat_table = rb_hash_new();
6718  rb_obj_hide(table);
6719  rb_gc_register_mark_object(table);
6720

6722 #define OLD_SYM(s) gc_stat_compat_symbols[gc_stat_compat_sym_##s]
6723 #define NEW_SYM(s) gc_stat_symbols[gc_stat_sym_##s]
6724  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(gc_stat_heap_used), NEW_SYM(heap_allocated_pages));
6725  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(heap_eden_page_length), NEW_SYM(heap_eden_pages));
6726  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(heap_tomb_page_length), NEW_SYM(heap_tomb_pages));
6727  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(heap_increment), NEW_SYM(heap_allocatable_pages));
6728  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(heap_length), NEW_SYM(heap_sorted_length));
6729  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(heap_live_slot), NEW_SYM(heap_live_slots));
6730  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(heap_free_slot), NEW_SYM(heap_free_slots));
6731  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(heap_final_slot), NEW_SYM(heap_final_slots));
6732  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(heap_swept_slot), NEW_SYM(heap_swept_slots));
6733 #if USE_RGEGC
6734  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(remembered_shady_object), NEW_SYM(remembered_wb_unprotected_objects));
6735  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(remembered_shady_object_limit), NEW_SYM(remembered_wb_unprotected_objects_limit));
6736  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(old_object), NEW_SYM(old_objects));
6737  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(old_object_limit), NEW_SYM(old_objects_limit));
6738 #endif
6739  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(total_allocated_object), NEW_SYM(total_allocated_objects));
6740  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(total_freed_object), NEW_SYM(total_freed_objects));

6742  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(malloc_limit), NEW_SYM(malloc_increase_bytes_limit));
6743 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC

6745  rb_hash_aset(table, OLD_SYM(oldmalloc_limit), NEW_SYM(oldmalloc_increase_bytes_limit));
6746 #endif
6747 #undef OLD_SYM
6748 #undef NEW_SYM
6749  rb_obj_freeze(table);
6750  }
6751  }

6754 static VALUE
6755 compat_key(VALUE key)
6756 {
6757  VALUE new_key = rb_hash_lookup(gc_stat_compat_table, key);
6758 
6759  if (!NIL_P(new_key)) {
6760  static int warned = 0;
6761  if (warned == 0) {
6762  rb_warn("GC.stat keys were changed from Ruby 2.1. "
6763  "In this case, you refer to obsolete `%"PRIsVALUE"' (new key is `%"PRIsVALUE"'). "
6764  "Please check <https://bugs.ruby-lang.org/issues/9924> for more information.",
6765  key, new_key);
6766  warned = 1;
6767  }
6768  }
6769 
6770  return new_key;
6771 }
6772 
6773 static VALUE
6774 default_proc_for_compat_func(VALUE hash, VALUE dmy, int argc, VALUE *argv)
6775 {
6776  VALUE key, new_key;
6777 
6778  Check_Type(hash, T_HASH);
6779  rb_check_arity(argc, 2, 2);
6780  key = argv[1];
6781 
6782  if ((new_key = compat_key(key)) != Qnil) {
6783  return rb_hash_lookup(hash, new_key);
6784  }
6785 
6786  return Qnil;
6787 }
6788 
6789 size_t
6790 gc_stat_internal(VALUE hash_or_sym)
6791 {
6792  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
6793  VALUE hash = Qnil, key = Qnil;
6794 
6795  setup_gc_stat_symbols();
6796 
6797  if (RB_TYPE_P(hash_or_sym, T_HASH)) {
6798  hash = hash_or_sym;
6799 
6800  if (NIL_P(RHASH_IFNONE(hash))) {
6801  static VALUE default_proc_for_compat = 0;
6802  if (default_proc_for_compat == 0) { /* TODO: it should be */
6803  default_proc_for_compat = rb_proc_new(default_proc_for_compat_func, Qnil);
6804  rb_gc_register_mark_object(default_proc_for_compat);
6805  }
6806  rb_hash_set_default_proc(hash, default_proc_for_compat);
6807  }
6808  }
6809  else if (SYMBOL_P(hash_or_sym)) {
6810  key = hash_or_sym;
6811  }
6812  else {
6813  rb_raise(rb_eTypeError, "non-hash or symbol argument");
6814  }
6815 
6816 #define SET(name, attr) \
6817  if (key == gc_stat_symbols[gc_stat_sym_##name]) \
6818  return attr; \
6819  else if (hash != Qnil) \
6820  rb_hash_aset(hash, gc_stat_symbols[gc_stat_sym_##name], SIZET2NUM(attr));
6821 
6822  again:
6823  SET(count, objspace->profile.count);
6824 
6825  /* implementation dependent counters */
6826  SET(heap_allocated_pages, heap_allocated_pages);
6827  SET(heap_sorted_length, heap_pages_sorted_length);
6828  SET(heap_allocatable_pages, heap_allocatable_pages);
6829  SET(heap_available_slots, objspace_available_slots(objspace));
6830  SET(heap_live_slots, objspace_live_slots(objspace));
6831  SET(heap_free_slots, objspace_free_slots(objspace));
6832  SET(heap_final_slots, heap_pages_final_slots);
6833  SET(heap_marked_slots, objspace->marked_slots);
6834  SET(heap_swept_slots, heap_pages_swept_slots);
6835  SET(heap_eden_pages, heap_eden->page_length);
6836  SET(heap_tomb_pages, heap_tomb->page_length);
6837  SET(total_allocated_pages, objspace->profile.total_allocated_pages);
6838  SET(total_freed_pages, objspace->profile.total_freed_pages);
6839  SET(total_allocated_objects, objspace->total_allocated_objects);
6840  SET(total_freed_objects, objspace->profile.total_freed_objects);
6841  SET(malloc_increase_bytes, malloc_increase);
6842  SET(malloc_increase_bytes_limit, malloc_limit);
6843 #if USE_RGENGC
6844  SET(minor_gc_count, objspace->profile.minor_gc_count);
6845  SET(major_gc_count, objspace->profile.major_gc_count);
6846  SET(remembered_wb_unprotected_objects, objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects);
6847  SET(remembered_wb_unprotected_objects_limit, objspace->rgengc.uncollectible_wb_unprotected_objects_limit);
6848  SET(old_objects, objspace->rgengc.old_objects);
6849  SET(old_objects_limit, objspace->rgengc.old_objects_limit);
6850 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
6851  SET(oldmalloc_increase_bytes, objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase);
6852  SET(oldmalloc_increase_bytes_limit, objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit);
6853 #endif
6854 
6855 #if RGENGC_PROFILE
6856  SET(total_generated_normal_object_count, objspace->profile.total_generated_normal_object_count);
6857  SET(total_generated_shady_object_count, objspace->profile.total_generated_shady_object_count);
6858  SET(total_shade_operation_count, objspace->profile.total_shade_operation_count);
6859  SET(total_promoted_count, objspace->profile.total_promoted_count);
6860  SET(total_remembered_normal_object_count, objspace->profile.total_remembered_normal_object_count);
6861  SET(total_remembered_shady_object_count, objspace->profile.total_remembered_shady_object_count);
6862 #endif /* RGENGC_PROFILE */
6863 #endif /* USE_RGENGC */
6864 #undef SET
6865 
6866  if (!NIL_P(key)) { /* matched key should return above */
6867  VALUE new_key;
6868  if ((new_key = compat_key(key)) != Qnil) {
6869  key = new_key;
6870  goto again;
6871  }
6872  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "unknown key: %"PRIsVALUE, rb_sym2str(key));
6873  }
6874 
6875 #if defined(RGENGC_PROFILE) && RGENGC_PROFILE >= 2
6876  if (hash != Qnil) {
6877  gc_count_add_each_types(hash, "generated_normal_object_count_types", objspace->profile.generated_normal_object_count_types);
6878  gc_count_add_each_types(hash, "generated_shady_object_count_types", objspace->profile.generated_shady_object_count_types);
6879  gc_count_add_each_types(hash, "shade_operation_count_types", objspace->profile.shade_operation_count_types);
6880  gc_count_add_each_types(hash, "promoted_types", objspace->profile.promoted_types);
6881  gc_count_add_each_types(hash, "remembered_normal_object_count_types", objspace->profile.remembered_normal_object_count_types);
6882  gc_count_add_each_types(hash, "remembered_shady_object_count_types", objspace->profile.remembered_shady_object_count_types);
6883  }
6884 #endif
6885 
6886  return 0;
6887 }
6888 
6889 /*
6890  * call-seq:
6891  * GC.stat -> Hash
6892  * GC.stat(hash) -> hash
6893  * GC.stat(:key) -> Numeric
6894  *
6895  * Returns a Hash containing information about the GC.
6896  *
6897  * The hash includes information about internal statistics about GC such as:
6898  *
6899  * {
6900  * :count=>0,
6901  * :heap_allocated_pages=>24,
6902  * :heap_sorted_length=>24,
6903  * :heap_allocatable_pages=>0,
6904  * :heap_available_slots=>9783,
6905  * :heap_live_slots=>7713,
6906  * :heap_free_slots=>2070,
6907  * :heap_final_slots=>0,
6908  * :heap_marked_slots=>0,
6909  * :heap_swept_slots=>0,
6910  * :heap_eden_pages=>24,
6911  * :heap_tomb_pages=>0,
6912  * :total_allocated_pages=>24,
6913  * :total_freed_pages=>0,
6914  * :total_allocated_objects=>7796,
6915  * :total_freed_objects=>83,
6916  * :malloc_increase_bytes=>2389312,
6917  * :malloc_increase_bytes_limit=>16777216,
6918  * :minor_gc_count=>0,
6919  * :major_gc_count=>0,
6920  * :remembered_wb_unprotected_objects=>0,
6921  * :remembered_wb_unprotected_objects_limit=>0,
6922  * :old_objects=>0,
6923  * :old_objects_limit=>0,
6924  * :oldmalloc_increase_bytes=>2389760,
6925  * :oldmalloc_increase_bytes_limit=>16777216
6926  * }
6927  *
6928  * The contents of the hash are implementation specific and may be changed in
6929  * the future.
6930  *
6931  * This method is only expected to work on C Ruby.
6932  *
6933  */
6934 
6935 static VALUE
6936 gc_stat(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE self)
6937 {
6938  VALUE arg = Qnil;
6939 
6940  if (rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "01", &arg) == 1) {
6941  if (SYMBOL_P(arg)) {
6942  size_t value = gc_stat_internal(arg);
6943  return SIZET2NUM(value);
6944  }
6945  else if (!RB_TYPE_P(arg, T_HASH)) {
6946  rb_raise(rb_eTypeError, "non-hash or symbol given");
6947  }
6948  }
6949 
6950  if (arg == Qnil) {
6951  arg = rb_hash_new();
6952  }
6953  gc_stat_internal(arg);
6954  return arg;
6955 }
6956 
6957 size_t
6958 rb_gc_stat(VALUE key)
6959 {
6960  if (SYMBOL_P(key)) {
6961  size_t value = gc_stat_internal(key);
6962  return value;
6963  }
6964  else {
6965  gc_stat_internal(key);
6966  return 0;
6967  }
6968 }

6970 /*
6971  * call-seq:
6972  * GC.stress -> fixnum, true or false
6973  *
6974  * Returns current status of GC stress mode.
6975  */
6976 
6977 static VALUE
6978 gc_stress_get(VALUE self)
6979 {
6980  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
6981  return ruby_gc_stress_mode;
6982 }
6983 
6984 static void
6985 gc_stress_set(rb_objspace_t *objspace, VALUE flag)
6986 {
6987  objspace->flags.gc_stressful = RTEST(flag);
6988  objspace->gc_stress_mode = flag;
6989 }
6990 
6991 /*
6992  * call-seq:
6993  * GC.stress = flag -> flag
6994  *
6995  * Updates the GC stress mode.
6996  *
6997  * When stress mode is enabled, the GC is invoked at every GC opportunity:
6998  * all memory and object allocations.
6999  *
7000  * Enabling stress mode will degrade performance, it is only for debugging.
7001  *
7002  * flag can be true, false, or a fixnum bit-ORed following flags.
7003  * 0x01:: no major GC
7004  * 0x02:: no immediate sweep
7005  * 0x04:: full mark after malloc/calloc/realloc
7006  */
7007 
7008 static VALUE
7009 gc_stress_set_m(VALUE self, VALUE flag)
7010 {
7011  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
7012  rb_secure(2);
7013  gc_stress_set(objspace, flag);
7014  return flag;
7015 }
7016 
7017 /*
7018  * call-seq:
7019  * GC.enable -> true or false
7020  *
7021  * Enables garbage collection, returning +true+ if garbage
7022  * collection was previously disabled.
7023  *
7024  * GC.disable #=> false
7025  * GC.enable #=> true
7026  * GC.enable #=> false
7027  *
7028  */
7029 
7030 VALUE
7031 rb_gc_enable(void)
7032 {
7033  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
7034  int old = dont_gc;
7035 
7036  dont_gc = FALSE;
7037  return old ? Qtrue : Qfalse;
7038 }
7039 
7040 /*
7041  * call-seq:
7042  * GC.disable -> true or false
7043  *
7044  * Disables garbage collection, returning +true+ if garbage
7045  * collection was already disabled.
7046  *
7047  * GC.disable #=> false
7048  * GC.disable #=> true
7049  *
7050  */
7051 
7052 VALUE
7053 rb_gc_disable(void)
7054 {
7055  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
7056  int old = dont_gc;
7057 
7058  gc_rest(objspace);
7059 
7060  dont_gc = TRUE;
7061  return old ? Qtrue : Qfalse;
7062 }
7063 
7064 static int
7065 get_envparam_size(const char *name, size_t *default_value, size_t lower_bound)
7066 {
7067  char *ptr = getenv(name);
7068  ssize_t val;
7069 
7070  if (ptr != NULL && *ptr) {
7071  size_t unit = 0;
7072  char *end;
7073 #if SIZEOF_SIZE_T == SIZEOF_LONG_LONG
7074  val = strtoll(ptr, &end, 0);
7075 #else
7076  val = strtol(ptr, &end, 0);
7077 #endif
7078  switch (*end) {
7079  case 'k': case 'K':
7080  unit = 1024;
7081  ++end;
7082  break;
7083  case 'm': case 'M':
7084  unit = 1024*1024;
7085  ++end;
7086  break;
7087  case 'g': case 'G':
7088  unit = 1024*1024*1024;
7089  ++end;
7090  break;
7091  }
7092  while (*end && isspace((unsigned char)*end)) end++;
7093  if (*end) {
7094  if (RTEST(ruby_verbose)) fprintf(stderr, "invalid string for %s: %s\n", name, ptr);
7095  return 0;
7096  }
7097  if (unit > 0) {
7098  if (val < -(ssize_t)(SIZE_MAX / 2 / unit) || (ssize_t)(SIZE_MAX / 2 / unit) < val) {
7099  if (RTEST(ruby_verbose)) fprintf(stderr, "%s=%s is ignored because it overflows\n", name, ptr);
7100  return 0;
7101  }
7102  val *= unit;
7103  }
7104  if (val > 0 && (size_t)val > lower_bound) {
7105  if (RTEST(ruby_verbose)) {
7106  fprintf(stderr, "%s=%"PRIdSIZE" (default value: %"PRIdSIZE")\n", name, val, *default_value);
7107  }
7108  *default_value = (size_t)val;
7109  return 1;
7110  }
7111  else {
7112  if (RTEST(ruby_verbose)) {
7113  fprintf(stderr, "%s=%"PRIdSIZE" (default value: %"PRIdSIZE") is ignored because it must be greater than %"PRIdSIZE".\n",
7114  name, val, *default_value, lower_bound);
7115  }
7116  return 0;
7117  }
7118  }
7119  return 0;
7120 }
7121 
7122 static int
7123 get_envparam_double(const char *name, double *default_value, double lower_bound)
7124 {
7125  char *ptr = getenv(name);
7126  double val;
7127 
7128  if (ptr != NULL && *ptr) {
7129  char *end;
7130  val = strtod(ptr, &end);
7131  if (!*ptr || *end) {
7132  if (RTEST(ruby_verbose)) fprintf(stderr, "invalid string for %s: %s\n", name, ptr);
7133  return 0;
7134  }
7135  if (val > lower_bound) {
7136  if (RTEST(ruby_verbose)) fprintf(stderr, "%s=%f (default value: %f)\n", name, val, *default_value);
7137  *default_value = val;
7138  return 1;
7139  }
7140  else {
7141  if (RTEST(ruby_verbose)) fprintf(stderr, "%s=%f (default value: %f) is ignored because it must be greater than %f.\n", name, val, *default_value, lower_bound);
7142  }
7143  }
7144  return 0;
7145 }
7146 
7147 static void
7148 gc_set_initial_pages(void)
7149 {
7150  size_t min_pages;
7151  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
7152 
7153  min_pages = gc_params.heap_init_slots / HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT;
7154  if (min_pages > heap_eden->page_length) {
7155  heap_add_pages(objspace, heap_eden, min_pages - heap_eden->page_length);
7156  }
7157 }
7158 
7159 /*
7160  * GC tuning environment variables
7161  *
7162  * * RUBY_GC_HEAP_INIT_SLOTS
7163  * - Initial allocation slots.
7164  * * RUBY_GC_HEAP_FREE_SLOTS
7165  * - Prepare at least this amount of slots after GC.
7166  * - Allocate slots if there are not enough slots.
7167  * * RUBY_GC_HEAP_GROWTH_FACTOR (new from 2.1)
7168  * - Allocate slots by this factor.
7169  * - (next slots number) = (current slots number) * (this factor)
7170  * * RUBY_GC_HEAP_GROWTH_MAX_SLOTS (new from 2.1)
7171  * - Allocation rate is limited to this number of slots.
7172  * * RUBY_GC_HEAP_OLDOBJECT_LIMIT_FACTOR (new from 2.1.1)
7173  * - Do full GC when the number of old objects is more than R * N
7174  * where R is this factor and
7175  * N is the number of old objects just after last full GC.
7176  *
7177  * * obsolete
7178  * * RUBY_FREE_MIN -> RUBY_GC_HEAP_FREE_SLOTS (from 2.1)
7179  * * RUBY_HEAP_MIN_SLOTS -> RUBY_GC_HEAP_INIT_SLOTS (from 2.1)
7180  *
7181  * * RUBY_GC_MALLOC_LIMIT
7182  * * RUBY_GC_MALLOC_LIMIT_MAX (new from 2.1)
7183  * * RUBY_GC_MALLOC_LIMIT_GROWTH_FACTOR (new from 2.1)
7184  *
7185  * * RUBY_GC_OLDMALLOC_LIMIT (new from 2.1)
7186  * * RUBY_GC_OLDMALLOC_LIMIT_MAX (new from 2.1)
7187  * * RUBY_GC_OLDMALLOC_LIMIT_GROWTH_FACTOR (new from 2.1)
7188  */
7189 
7190 void
7191 ruby_gc_set_params(int safe_level)
7192 {
7193  if (safe_level > 0) return;
7194 
7195  /* RUBY_GC_HEAP_FREE_SLOTS */
7196  if (get_envparam_size("RUBY_GC_HEAP_FREE_SLOTS", &gc_params.heap_free_slots, 0)) {
7197  /* ok */
7198  }
7199  else if (get_envparam_size("RUBY_FREE_MIN", &gc_params.heap_free_slots, 0)) {
7200  rb_warn("RUBY_FREE_MIN is obsolete. Use RUBY_GC_HEAP_FREE_SLOTS instead.");
7201  }
7202 
7203  /* RUBY_GC_HEAP_INIT_SLOTS */
7204  if (get_envparam_size("RUBY_GC_HEAP_INIT_SLOTS", &gc_params.heap_init_slots, 0)) {
7205  gc_set_initial_pages();
7206  }
7207  else if (get_envparam_size("RUBY_HEAP_MIN_SLOTS", &gc_params.heap_init_slots, 0)) {
7208  rb_warn("RUBY_HEAP_MIN_SLOTS is obsolete. Use RUBY_GC_HEAP_INIT_SLOTS instead.");
7209  gc_set_initial_pages();
7210  }
7211 
7212  get_envparam_double("RUBY_GC_HEAP_GROWTH_FACTOR", &gc_params.growth_factor, 1.0);
7213  get_envparam_size ("RUBY_GC_HEAP_GROWTH_MAX_SLOTS", &gc_params.growth_max_slots, 0);
7214  get_envparam_double("RUBY_GC_HEAP_OLDOBJECT_LIMIT_FACTOR", &gc_params.oldobject_limit_factor, 0.0);
7215 
7216  get_envparam_size ("RUBY_GC_MALLOC_LIMIT", &gc_params.malloc_limit_min, 0);
7217  get_envparam_size ("RUBY_GC_MALLOC_LIMIT_MAX", &gc_params.malloc_limit_max, 0);
7218  get_envparam_double("RUBY_GC_MALLOC_LIMIT_GROWTH_FACTOR", &gc_params.malloc_limit_growth_factor, 1.0);
7219 
7220 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
7221  if (get_envparam_size("RUBY_GC_OLDMALLOC_LIMIT", &gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_min, 0)) {
7222  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
7223  objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase_limit = gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_min;
7224  }
7225  get_envparam_size ("RUBY_GC_OLDMALLOC_LIMIT_MAX", &gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_max, 0);
7226  get_envparam_double("RUBY_GC_OLDMALLOC_LIMIT_GROWTH_FACTOR", &gc_params.oldmalloc_limit_growth_factor, 1.0);
7227 #endif
7228 }
7229 
7230 void
7231 rb_objspace_reachable_objects_from(VALUE obj, void (func)(VALUE, void *), void *data)
7232 {
7233  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
7234 
7235  if (is_markable_object(objspace, obj)) {
7236  struct mark_func_data_struct mfd;
7237  mfd.mark_func = func;
7238  mfd.data = data;
7239  PUSH_MARK_FUNC_DATA(&mfd);
7240  gc_mark_children(objspace, obj);
7241  POP_MARK_FUNC_DATA();
7242  }
7243 }
7244 
7245 struct root_objects_data {
7246  const char *category;
7247  void (*func)(const char *category, VALUE, void *);
7248  void *data;
7249 };
7250 
7251 static void
7252 root_objects_from(VALUE obj, void *ptr)
7253 {
7254  const struct root_objects_data *data = (struct root_objects_data *)ptr;
7255  (*data->func)(data->category, obj, data->data);
7256 }
7257 
7258 void
7259 rb_objspace_reachable_objects_from_root(void (func)(const char *category, VALUE, void *), void *passing_data)
7260 {
7261  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
7262  struct root_objects_data data;
7263  struct mark_func_data_struct mfd;
7264 
7265  data.func = func;
7266  data.data = passing_data;
7267 
7268  mfd.mark_func = root_objects_from;
7269  mfd.data = &data;
7270 
7271  PUSH_MARK_FUNC_DATA(&mfd);
7272  gc_mark_roots(objspace, &data.category);
7273  POP_MARK_FUNC_DATA();
7274 }

7282 static void *
7283 negative_size_allocation_error_with_gvl(void *ptr)
7284 {
7285  rb_raise(rb_eNoMemError, "%s", (const char *)ptr);
7286  return 0; /* should not be reached */
7287 }
7288 
7289 static void
7290 negative_size_allocation_error(const char *msg)
7291 {
7292  if (ruby_thread_has_gvl_p()) {
7293  rb_raise(rb_eNoMemError, "%s", msg);
7294  }
7295  else {
7296  if (ruby_native_thread_p()) {
7297  rb_thread_call_with_gvl(negative_size_allocation_error_with_gvl, (void *)msg);
7298  }
7299  else {
7300  fprintf(stderr, "[FATAL] %s\n", msg);
7301  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
7302  }
7303  }
7304 }
7305 
7306 static void *
7307 ruby_memerror_body(void *dummy)
7308 {
7309  rb_memerror();
7310  return 0;
7311 }
7312 
7313 static void
7314 ruby_memerror(void)
7315 {
7316  if (ruby_thread_has_gvl_p()) {
7317  rb_memerror();
7318  }
7319  else {
7320  if (ruby_native_thread_p()) {
7321  rb_thread_call_with_gvl(ruby_memerror_body, 0);
7322  }
7323  else {
7324  /* no ruby thread */
7325  fprintf(stderr, "[FATAL] failed to allocate memory\n");
7326  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
7327  }
7328  }
7329 }
7330 
7331 void
7332 rb_memerror(void)
7333 {
7334  rb_thread_t *th = GET_THREAD();
7335  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
7336 
7337  if (during_gc) gc_exit(objspace, "rb_memerror");
7338 
7339  if (!nomem_error ||
7340  rb_thread_raised_p(th, RAISED_NOMEMORY)) {
7341  fprintf(stderr, "[FATAL] failed to allocate memory\n");
7342  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
7343  }
7344  if (rb_thread_raised_p(th, RAISED_NOMEMORY)) {
7345  rb_thread_raised_clear(th);
7346  GET_THREAD()->errinfo = nomem_error;
7347  JUMP_TAG(TAG_RAISE);
7348  }
7349  rb_thread_raised_set(th, RAISED_NOMEMORY);
7350  rb_exc_raise(nomem_error);
7351 }
7352 
7353 static void *
7354 aligned_malloc(size_t alignment, size_t size)
7355 {
7356  void *res;
7357 
7358 #if defined __MINGW32__
7359  res = __mingw_aligned_malloc(size, alignment);
7360 #elif defined _WIN32 && !defined __CYGWIN__
7361  void *_aligned_malloc(size_t, size_t);
7362  res = _aligned_malloc(size, alignment);
7363 #elif defined(HAVE_POSIX_MEMALIGN)
7364  if (posix_memalign(&res, alignment, size) == 0) {
7365  return res;
7366  }
7367  else {
7368  return NULL;
7369  }
7370 #elif defined(HAVE_MEMALIGN)
7371  res = memalign(alignment, size);
7372 #else
7373  char* aligned;
7374  res = malloc(alignment + size + sizeof(void*));
7375  aligned = (char*)res + alignment + sizeof(void*);
7376  aligned -= ((VALUE)aligned & (alignment - 1));
7377  ((void**)aligned)[-1] = res;
7378  res = (void*)aligned;
7379 #endif
7380 
7381 #if defined(_DEBUG) || GC_DEBUG
7382  /* alignment must be a power of 2 */
7383  assert(((alignment - 1) & alignment) == 0);
7384  assert(alignment % sizeof(void*) == 0);
7385 #endif
7386  return res;
7387 }
7388 
7389 static void
7390 aligned_free(void *ptr)
7391 {
7392 #if defined __MINGW32__
7393  __mingw_aligned_free(ptr);
7394 #elif defined _WIN32 && !defined __CYGWIN__
7395  _aligned_free(ptr);
7396 #elif defined(HAVE_MEMALIGN) || defined(HAVE_POSIX_MEMALIGN)
7397  free(ptr);
7398 #else
7399  free(((void**)ptr)[-1]);
7400 #endif
7401 }

7403 static inline size_t
7404 objspace_malloc_size(rb_objspace_t *objspace, void *ptr, size_t hint)
7405 {
7406 #ifdef HAVE_MALLOC_USABLE_SIZE
7407  return malloc_usable_size(ptr);
7408 #else
7409  return hint;
7410 #endif
7411 }
7412 
7413 enum memop_type {
7414  MEMOP_TYPE_MALLOC = 1,
7415  MEMOP_TYPE_FREE = 2,
7416  MEMOP_TYPE_REALLOC = 3
7417 };
7418 
7419 static inline void
7420 atomic_sub_nounderflow(size_t *var, size_t sub)
7421 {
7422  if (sub == 0) return;
7423 
7424  while (1) {
7425  size_t val = *var;
7426  if (val < sub) sub = val;
7427  if (ATOMIC_SIZE_CAS(*var, val, val-sub) == val) break;
7428  }
7429 }
7430 
7431 static void
7432 objspace_malloc_gc_stress(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
7433 {
7434  if (ruby_gc_stressful && ruby_native_thread_p()) {
7435  garbage_collect_with_gvl(objspace, gc_stress_full_mark_after_malloc_p(), TRUE, TRUE, GPR_FLAG_STRESS | GPR_FLAG_MALLOC);
7436  }
7437 }
7438 
7439 static void
7440 objspace_malloc_increase(rb_objspace_t *objspace, void *mem, size_t new_size, size_t old_size, enum memop_type type)
7441 {
7442  if (new_size > old_size) {
7443  ATOMIC_SIZE_ADD(malloc_increase, new_size - old_size);
7444 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
7445  ATOMIC_SIZE_ADD(objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase, new_size - old_size);
7446 #endif
7447  }
7448  else {
7449  atomic_sub_nounderflow(&malloc_increase, old_size - new_size);
7450 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
7451  atomic_sub_nounderflow(&objspace->rgengc.oldmalloc_increase, old_size - new_size);
7452 #endif
7453  }
7454 
7455  if (type == MEMOP_TYPE_MALLOC) {
7456  retry:
7457  if (malloc_increase > malloc_limit && ruby_native_thread_p() && !dont_gc) {
7458  if (ruby_thread_has_gvl_p() && is_lazy_sweeping(heap_eden)) {
7459  gc_rest(objspace); /* gc_rest can reduce malloc_increase */
7460  goto retry;
7461  }
7462  garbage_collect_with_gvl(objspace, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, GPR_FLAG_MALLOC);
7463  }
7464  }
7465 
7466 #if MALLOC_ALLOCATED_SIZE
7467  if (new_size >= old_size) {
7468  ATOMIC_SIZE_ADD(objspace->malloc_params.allocated_size, new_size - old_size);
7469  }
7470  else {
7471  size_t dec_size = old_size - new_size;
7472  size_t allocated_size = objspace->malloc_params.allocated_size;
7473 
7474 #if MALLOC_ALLOCATED_SIZE_CHECK
7475  if (allocated_size < dec_size) {
7476  rb_bug("objspace_malloc_increase: underflow malloc_params.allocated_size.");
7477  }
7478 #endif
7479  atomic_sub_nounderflow(&objspace->malloc_params.allocated_size, dec_size);
7480  }
7481 
7482  if (0) fprintf(stderr, "increase - ptr: %p, type: %s, new_size: %d, old_size: %d\n",
7483  mem,
7484  type == MEMOP_TYPE_MALLOC ? "malloc" :
7485  type == MEMOP_TYPE_FREE ? "free " :
7486  type == MEMOP_TYPE_REALLOC ? "realloc": "error",
7487  (int)new_size, (int)old_size);
7488 
7489  switch (type) {
7490  case MEMOP_TYPE_MALLOC:
7491  ATOMIC_SIZE_INC(objspace->malloc_params.allocations);
7492  break;
7493  case MEMOP_TYPE_FREE:
7494  {
7495  size_t allocations = objspace->malloc_params.allocations;
7496  if (allocations > 0) {
7497  atomic_sub_nounderflow(&objspace->malloc_params.allocations, 1);
7498  }
7499 #if MALLOC_ALLOCATED_SIZE_CHECK
7500  else {
7501  if (RGENGC_CHECK_MODE) assert(objspace->malloc_params.allocations > 0);
7502  }
7503 #endif
7504  }
7505  break;
7506  case MEMOP_TYPE_REALLOC: /* ignore */ break;
7507  }
7508 #endif
7509 }
7510 
7511 static inline size_t
7512 objspace_malloc_prepare(rb_objspace_t *objspace, size_t size)
7513 {
7514  if ((ssize_t)size < 0) {
7515  negative_size_allocation_error("negative allocation size (or too big)");
7516  }
7517  if (size == 0) size = 1;
7518 
7519 #if CALC_EXACT_MALLOC_SIZE
7520  size += sizeof(size_t);
7521 #endif
7522 
7523  return size;
7524 }
7525 
7526 static inline void *
7527 objspace_malloc_fixup(rb_objspace_t *objspace, void *mem, size_t size)
7528 {
7529 #if CALC_EXACT_MALLOC_SIZE
7530  ((size_t *)mem)[0] = size;
7531  mem = (size_t *)mem + 1;
7532 #endif
7533 
7534  return mem;
7535 }
7536 
7537 #define TRY_WITH_GC(alloc) do { \
7538  objspace_malloc_gc_stress(objspace); \
7539  if (!(alloc) && \
7540  (!garbage_collect_with_gvl(objspace, TRUE, TRUE, TRUE, GPR_FLAG_MALLOC) || /* full/immediate mark && immediate sweep */ \
7541  !(alloc))) { \
7542  ruby_memerror(); \
7543  } \
7544  } while (0)
7545 
7546 static void *
7547 objspace_xmalloc(rb_objspace_t *objspace, size_t size)
7548 {
7549  void *mem;
7550 
7551  size = objspace_malloc_prepare(objspace, size);
7552  TRY_WITH_GC(mem = malloc(size));
7553  size = objspace_malloc_size(objspace, mem, size);
7554  objspace_malloc_increase(objspace, mem, size, 0, MEMOP_TYPE_MALLOC);
7555  return objspace_malloc_fixup(objspace, mem, size);
7556 }
7557 
7558 static void *
7559 objspace_xrealloc(rb_objspace_t *objspace, void *ptr, size_t new_size, size_t old_size)
7560 {
7561  void *mem;
7562 
7563  if ((ssize_t)new_size < 0) {
7564  negative_size_allocation_error("negative re-allocation size");
7565  }
7566 
7567  if (!ptr) return objspace_xmalloc(objspace, new_size);
7568 
7569  /*
7570  * The behavior of realloc(ptr, 0) is implementation defined.
7571  * Therefore we don't use realloc(ptr, 0) for portability reason.
7572  * see http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg14/www/docs/dr_400.htm
7573  */
7574  if (new_size == 0) {
7575  objspace_xfree(objspace, ptr, old_size);
7576  return 0;
7577  }
7578 
7579 #if CALC_EXACT_MALLOC_SIZE
7580  new_size += sizeof(size_t);
7581  ptr = (size_t *)ptr - 1;
7582  old_size = ((size_t *)ptr)[0];
7583 #endif
7584 
7585  old_size = objspace_malloc_size(objspace, ptr, old_size);
7586  TRY_WITH_GC(mem = realloc(ptr, new_size));
7587  new_size = objspace_malloc_size(objspace, mem, new_size);
7588 
7589 #if CALC_EXACT_MALLOC_SIZE
7590  ((size_t *)mem)[0] = new_size;
7591  mem = (size_t *)mem + 1;
7592 #endif
7593 
7594  objspace_malloc_increase(objspace, mem, new_size, old_size, MEMOP_TYPE_REALLOC);
7595 
7596  return mem;
7597 }
7598 
7599 static void
7600 objspace_xfree(rb_objspace_t *objspace, void *ptr, size_t old_size)
7601 {
7602 #if CALC_EXACT_MALLOC_SIZE
7603  ptr = ((size_t *)ptr) - 1;
7604  old_size = ((size_t*)ptr)[0];
7605 #endif
7606  old_size = objspace_malloc_size(objspace, ptr, old_size);
7607 
7608  free(ptr);
7609 
7610  objspace_malloc_increase(objspace, ptr, 0, old_size, MEMOP_TYPE_FREE);
7611 }
7612 
7613 void *
7614 ruby_xmalloc(size_t size)
7615 {
7616  return objspace_xmalloc(&rb_objspace, size);
7617 }

7619 static inline size_t
7620 xmalloc2_size(size_t n, size_t size)
7621 {
7622  size_t len = size * n;
7623  if (n != 0 && size != len / n) {
7624  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "malloc: possible integer overflow");
7625  }
7626  return len;
7627 }
7628

7630 ruby_xmalloc2(size_t n, size_t size)
7631 {
7632  return objspace_xmalloc(&rb_objspace, xmalloc2_size(n, size));
7633 }

7635 static void *
7636 objspace_xcalloc(rb_objspace_t *objspace, size_t count, size_t elsize)
7637 {
7638  void *mem;
7639  size_t size;
7640 
7641  size = xmalloc2_size(count, elsize);
7642  size = objspace_malloc_prepare(objspace, size);
7643 
7644  TRY_WITH_GC(mem = calloc(1, size));
7645  size = objspace_malloc_size(objspace, mem, size);
7646  objspace_malloc_increase(objspace, mem, size, 0, MEMOP_TYPE_MALLOC);
7647  return objspace_malloc_fixup(objspace, mem, size);
7648 }

7707 /* Mimic ruby_xmalloc, but need not rb_objspace.

7709  */

7711 ruby_mimmalloc(size_t size)
7712 {

7714 #if CALC_EXACT_MALLOC_SIZE
7715  size += sizeof(size_t);
7716 #endif
7717  mem = malloc(size);
7718 #if CALC_EXACT_MALLOC_SIZE
7719  /* set 0 for consistency of allocated_size/allocations */
7720  ((size_t *)mem)[0] = 0;
7721  mem = (size_t *)mem + 1;
7722 #endif
7723  return mem;
7724 }

7731  mem = mem - 1;
7732 #endif
7733  free(mem);
7734 }

7768 /*
7769  ------------------------------ WeakMap ------------------------------
7770 */
7771 
7772 struct weakmap {
7773  st_table *obj2wmap; /* obj -> [ref,...] */
7774  st_table *wmap2obj; /* ref -> obj */
7775  VALUE final;
7776 };
7777 
7778 #define WMAP_DELETE_DEAD_OBJECT_IN_MARK 0
7779 
7780 #if WMAP_DELETE_DEAD_OBJECT_IN_MARK
7781 static int
7782 wmap_mark_map(st_data_t key, st_data_t val, st_data_t arg)
7783 {
7784  rb_objspace_t *objspace = (rb_objspace_t *)arg;
7785  VALUE obj = (VALUE)val;
7786  if (!is_live_object(objspace, obj)) return ST_DELETE;
7787  return ST_CONTINUE;
7788 }
7789 #endif
7790 
7791 static void
7792 wmap_mark(void *ptr)
7793 {
7794  struct weakmap *w = ptr;
7795 #if WMAP_DELETE_DEAD_OBJECT_IN_MARK
7796  if (w->obj2wmap) st_foreach(w->obj2wmap, wmap_mark_map, (st_data_t)&rb_objspace);
7797 #endif
7798  rb_gc_mark(w->final);
7799 }
7800 
7801 static int
7802 wmap_free_map(st_data_t key, st_data_t val, st_data_t arg)
7803 {
7804  VALUE *ptr = (VALUE *)val;
7805  ruby_sized_xfree(ptr, (ptr[0] + 1) * sizeof(VALUE));
7806  return ST_CONTINUE;
7807 }
7808 
7809 static void
7810 wmap_free(void *ptr)
7811 {
7812  struct weakmap *w = ptr;
7813  st_foreach(w->obj2wmap, wmap_free_map, 0);
7814  st_free_table(w->obj2wmap);
7815  st_free_table(w->wmap2obj);
7816 }
7817 
7818 static int
7819 wmap_memsize_map(st_data_t key, st_data_t val, st_data_t arg)
7820 {
7821  VALUE *ptr = (VALUE *)val;
7822  *(size_t *)arg += (ptr[0] + 1) * sizeof(VALUE);
7823  return ST_CONTINUE;
7824 }
7825 
7826 static size_t
7827 wmap_memsize(const void *ptr)
7828 {
7829  size_t size;
7830  const struct weakmap *w = ptr;
7831  if (!w) return 0;
7832  size = sizeof(*w);
7833  size += st_memsize(w->obj2wmap);
7834  size += st_memsize(w->wmap2obj);
7835  st_foreach(w->obj2wmap, wmap_memsize_map, (st_data_t)&size);
7836  return size;
7837 }
7838 
7839 static const rb_data_type_t weakmap_type = {
7840  "weakmap",
7841  {
7842  wmap_mark,
7843  wmap_free,
7844  wmap_memsize,
7845  },
7846  0, 0, RUBY_TYPED_FREE_IMMEDIATELY
7847 };
7848 
7849 static VALUE
7850 wmap_allocate(VALUE klass)
7851 {
7852  struct weakmap *w;
7853  VALUE obj = TypedData_Make_Struct(klass, struct weakmap, &weakmap_type, w);
7854  w->obj2wmap = st_init_numtable();
7855  w->wmap2obj = st_init_numtable();
7856  w->final = rb_obj_method(obj, ID2SYM(rb_intern("finalize")));
7857  return obj;
7858 }
7859 
7860 static int
7861 wmap_final_func(st_data_t *key, st_data_t *value, st_data_t arg, int existing)
7862 {
7863  VALUE wmap, *ptr, size, i, j;
7864  if (!existing) return ST_STOP;
7865  wmap = (VALUE)arg, ptr = (VALUE *)*value;
7866  for (i = j = 1, size = ptr[0]; i <= size; ++i) {
7867  if (ptr[i] != wmap) {
7868  ptr[j++] = ptr[i];
7869  }
7870  }
7871  if (j == 1) {
7872  ruby_sized_xfree(ptr, i * sizeof(VALUE));
7873  return ST_DELETE;
7874  }
7875  if (j < i) {
7876  ptr = ruby_sized_xrealloc2(ptr, j + 1, sizeof(VALUE), i);
7877  ptr[0] = j;
7878  *value = (st_data_t)ptr;
7879  }
7880  return ST_CONTINUE;
7881 }
7882 
7883 static VALUE
7884 wmap_finalize(VALUE self, VALUE objid)
7885 {
7886  st_data_t orig, wmap, data;
7887  VALUE obj, *rids, i, size;
7888  struct weakmap *w;
7889 
7890  TypedData_Get_Struct(self, struct weakmap, &weakmap_type, w);
7891  /* Get reference from object id. */
7892  obj = obj_id_to_ref(objid);
7893 
7894  /* obj is original referenced object and/or weak reference. */
7895  orig = (st_data_t)obj;
7896  if (st_delete(w->obj2wmap, &orig, &data)) {
7897  rids = (VALUE *)data;
7898  size = *rids++;
7899  for (i = 0; i < size; ++i) {
7900  wmap = (st_data_t)rids[i];
7901  st_delete(w->wmap2obj, &wmap, NULL);
7902  }
7903  ruby_sized_xfree((VALUE *)data, (size + 1) * sizeof(VALUE));
7904  }
7905 
7906  wmap = (st_data_t)obj;
7907  if (st_delete(w->wmap2obj, &wmap, &orig)) {
7908  wmap = (st_data_t)obj;
7909  st_update(w->obj2wmap, orig, wmap_final_func, wmap);
7910  }
7911  return self;
7912 }
7913 
7914 struct wmap_iter_arg {
7915  rb_objspace_t *objspace;
7916  VALUE value;
7917 };
7918 
7919 static int
7920 wmap_inspect_i(st_data_t key, st_data_t val, st_data_t arg)
7921 {
7922  VALUE str = (VALUE)arg;
7923  VALUE k = (VALUE)key, v = (VALUE)val;
7924 
7925  if (RSTRING_PTR(str)[0] == '#') {
7926  rb_str_cat2(str, ", ");
7927  }
7928  else {
7929  rb_str_cat2(str, ": ");
7930  RSTRING_PTR(str)[0] = '#';
7931  }
7932  k = SPECIAL_CONST_P(k) ? rb_inspect(k) : rb_any_to_s(k);
7933  rb_str_append(str, k);
7934  rb_str_cat2(str, " => ");
7935  v = SPECIAL_CONST_P(v) ? rb_inspect(v) : rb_any_to_s(v);
7936  rb_str_append(str, v);
7937  OBJ_INFECT(str, k);
7938  OBJ_INFECT(str, v);
7939 
7940  return ST_CONTINUE;
7941 }
7942 
7943 static VALUE
7944 wmap_inspect(VALUE self)
7945 {
7946  VALUE str;
7947  VALUE c = rb_class_name(CLASS_OF(self));
7948  struct weakmap *w;
7949 
7950  TypedData_Get_Struct(self, struct weakmap, &weakmap_type, w);
7951  str = rb_sprintf("-<%"PRIsVALUE":%p", c, (void *)self);
7952  if (w->wmap2obj) {
7953  st_foreach(w->wmap2obj, wmap_inspect_i, str);
7954  }
7955  RSTRING_PTR(str)[0] = '#';
7956  rb_str_cat2(str, ">");
7957  return str;
7958 }

7960 static int
7961 wmap_each_i(st_data_t key, st_data_t val, st_data_t arg)
7962 {
7963  rb_objspace_t *objspace = (rb_objspace_t *)arg;
7964  VALUE obj = (VALUE)val;
7965  if (is_id_value(objspace, obj) && is_live_object(objspace, obj)) {
7966  rb_yield_values(2, (VALUE)key, obj);
7967  }
7968  return ST_CONTINUE;
7969 }

8082 
8083 static int
8084 wmap_aset_update(st_data_t *key, st_data_t *val, st_data_t arg, int existing)
8085 {
8086  VALUE size, *ptr, *optr;
8087  if (existing) {
8088  size = (ptr = optr = (VALUE *)*val)[0];
8089  ++size;
8090  ptr = ruby_sized_xrealloc2(ptr, size + 1, sizeof(VALUE), size);
8091  }
8092  else {
8093  optr = 0;
8094  size = 1;
8095  ptr = ruby_xmalloc2(2, sizeof(VALUE));
8096  }
8097  ptr[0] = size;
8098  ptr[size] = (VALUE)arg;
8099  if (ptr == optr) return ST_STOP;
8100  *val = (st_data_t)ptr;
8101  return ST_CONTINUE;
8102 }
8103 
8104 /* Creates a weak reference from the given key to the given value */
8105 static VALUE
8106 wmap_aset(VALUE self, VALUE wmap, VALUE orig)
8107 {
8108  struct weakmap *w;
8109 
8110  TypedData_Get_Struct(self, struct weakmap, &weakmap_type, w);
8111  should_be_finalizable(orig);
8112  should_be_finalizable(wmap);
8113  define_final0(orig, w->final);
8114  define_final0(wmap, w->final);
8115  st_update(w->obj2wmap, (st_data_t)orig, wmap_aset_update, wmap);
8116  st_insert(w->wmap2obj, (st_data_t)wmap, (st_data_t)orig);
8117  return nonspecial_obj_id(orig);
8118 }
8119 
8120 /* Retrieves a weakly referenced object with the given key */
8121 static VALUE
8122 wmap_aref(VALUE self, VALUE wmap)
8123 {
8124  st_data_t data;
8125  VALUE obj;
8126  struct weakmap *w;
8127  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
8128 
8129  TypedData_Get_Struct(self, struct weakmap, &weakmap_type, w);
8130  if (!st_lookup(w->wmap2obj, (st_data_t)wmap, &data)) return Qnil;
8131  obj = (VALUE)data;
8132  if (!is_id_value(objspace, obj)) return Qnil;
8133  if (!is_live_object(objspace, obj)) return Qnil;
8134  return obj;
8135 }
8136 
8137 /* Returns +true+ if +key+ is registered */
8138 static VALUE
8139 wmap_has_key(VALUE self, VALUE key)
8140 {
8141  return NIL_P(wmap_aref(self, key)) ? Qfalse : Qtrue;
8142 }

8144 static VALUE
8145 wmap_size(VALUE self)
8146 {
8147  struct weakmap *w;
8148  st_index_t n;
8149 
8150  TypedData_Get_Struct(self, struct weakmap, &weakmap_type, w);
8151  n = w->wmap2obj->num_entries;
8152 #if SIZEOF_ST_INDEX_T <= SIZEOF_LONG
8153  return ULONG2NUM(n);
8154 #else
8155  return ULL2NUM(n);
8156 #endif
8157 }
8158 
8159 /*
8160  ------------------------------ GC profiler ------------------------------
8161 */
8162 
8163 #define GC_PROFILE_RECORD_DEFAULT_SIZE 100
8164 
8165 /* return sec in user time */
8166 static double
8167 getrusage_time(void)
8168 {
8169 #if defined(HAVE_CLOCK_GETTIME) && defined(CLOCK_PROCESS_CPUTIME_ID)
8170  {
8171  static int try_clock_gettime = 1;
8172  struct timespec ts;
8173  if (try_clock_gettime && clock_gettime(CLOCK_PROCESS_CPUTIME_ID, &ts) == 0) {
8174  return ts.tv_sec + ts.tv_nsec * 1e-9;
8175  }
8176  else {
8177  try_clock_gettime = 0;
8178  }
8179  }
8180 #endif
8181 
8182 #ifdef RUSAGE_SELF
8183  {
8184  struct rusage usage;
8185  struct timeval time;
8186  if (getrusage(RUSAGE_SELF, &usage) == 0) {
8187  time = usage.ru_utime;
8188  return time.tv_sec + time.tv_usec * 1e-6;
8189  }
8190  }
8191 #endif
8192 
8193 #ifdef _WIN32
8194  {
8195  FILETIME creation_time, exit_time, kernel_time, user_time;
8196  ULARGE_INTEGER ui;
8197  LONG_LONG q;
8198  double t;
8199 
8200  if (GetProcessTimes(GetCurrentProcess(),
8201  &creation_time, &exit_time, &kernel_time, &user_time) != 0) {
8202  memcpy(&ui, &user_time, sizeof(FILETIME));
8203  q = ui.QuadPart / 10L;
8204  t = (DWORD)(q % 1000000L) * 1e-6;
8205  q /= 1000000L;
8206 #ifdef __GNUC__
8207  t += q;
8208 #else
8209  t += (double)(DWORD)(q >> 16) * (1 << 16);
8210  t += (DWORD)q & ~(~0 << 16);
8211 #endif
8212  return t;
8213  }
8214  }
8215 #endif
8216 
8217  return 0.0;
8218 }
8219 
8220 static inline void
8221 gc_prof_setup_new_record(rb_objspace_t *objspace, int reason)
8222 {
8223  if (objspace->profile.run) {
8224  size_t index = objspace->profile.next_index;
8225  gc_profile_record *record;
8226 
8227  /* create new record */
8228  objspace->profile.next_index++;
8229 
8230  if (!objspace->profile.records) {
8231  objspace->profile.size = GC_PROFILE_RECORD_DEFAULT_SIZE;
8232  objspace->profile.records = malloc(sizeof(gc_profile_record) * objspace->profile.size);
8233  }
8234  if (index >= objspace->profile.size) {
8235  objspace->profile.size += 1000;
8236  objspace->profile.records = realloc(objspace->profile.records, sizeof(gc_profile_record) * objspace->profile.size);
8237  }
8238  if (!objspace->profile.records) {
8239  rb_bug("gc_profile malloc or realloc miss");
8240  }
8241  record = objspace->profile.current_record = &objspace->profile.records[objspace->profile.next_index - 1];
8242  MEMZERO(record, gc_profile_record, 1);
8243 
8244  /* setup before-GC parameter */
8245  record->flags = reason | (ruby_gc_stressful ? GPR_FLAG_STRESS : 0);
8246 #if MALLOC_ALLOCATED_SIZE
8247  record->allocated_size = malloc_allocated_size;
8248 #endif
8249 #if GC_PROFILE_DETAIL_MEMORY
8250 #ifdef RUSAGE_SELF
8251  {
8252  struct rusage usage;
8253  if (getrusage(RUSAGE_SELF, &usage) == 0) {
8254  record->maxrss = usage.ru_maxrss;
8255  record->minflt = usage.ru_minflt;
8256  record->majflt = usage.ru_majflt;
8257  }
8258  }
8259 #endif
8260 #endif
8261  }
8262 }
8263 
8264 static inline void
8265 gc_prof_timer_start(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
8266 {
8267  if (gc_prof_enabled(objspace)) {
8268  gc_profile_record *record = gc_prof_record(objspace);
8269 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
8270  record->prepare_time = objspace->profile.prepare_time;
8271 #endif
8272  record->gc_time = 0;
8273  record->gc_invoke_time = getrusage_time();
8274  }
8275 }
8276 
8277 static double
8278 elapsed_time_from(double time)
8279 {
8280  double now = getrusage_time();
8281  if (now > time) {
8282  return now - time;
8283  }
8284  else {
8285  return 0;
8286  }
8287 }
8288 
8289 static inline void
8290 gc_prof_timer_stop(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
8291 {
8292  if (gc_prof_enabled(objspace)) {
8293  gc_profile_record *record = gc_prof_record(objspace);
8294  record->gc_time = elapsed_time_from(record->gc_invoke_time);
8295  record->gc_invoke_time -= objspace->profile.invoke_time;
8296  }
8297 }

8301 {
8302  if (RUBY_DTRACE_GC_MARK_BEGIN_ENABLED()) {
8303  RUBY_DTRACE_GC_MARK_BEGIN();
8304  }
8305 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
8306  if (gc_prof_enabled(objspace)) {
8307  gc_prof_record(objspace)->gc_mark_time = getrusage_time();
8308  }
8309 #endif
8310 }

8312 static inline void
8313 gc_prof_mark_timer_stop(rb_objspace_t *objspace)

8315  if (RUBY_DTRACE_GC_MARK_END_ENABLED()) {
8316  RUBY_DTRACE_GC_MARK_END();
8317  }
8318 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
8319  if (gc_prof_enabled(objspace)) {
8320  gc_profile_record *record = gc_prof_record(objspace);
8321  record->gc_mark_time = elapsed_time_from(record->gc_mark_time);
8322  }
8323 #endif
8324 }

8326 static inline void
8327 gc_prof_sweep_timer_start(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
8328 {
8329  if (RUBY_DTRACE_GC_SWEEP_BEGIN_ENABLED()) {
8330  RUBY_DTRACE_GC_SWEEP_BEGIN();
8331  }
8332  if (gc_prof_enabled(objspace)) {
8333  gc_profile_record *record = gc_prof_record(objspace);
8334 
8335  if (record->gc_time > 0 || GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL) {
8336  objspace->profile.gc_sweep_start_time = getrusage_time();
8337  }
8338  }
8339 }
8340 
8341 static inline void
8342 gc_prof_sweep_timer_stop(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
8343 {
8344  if (RUBY_DTRACE_GC_SWEEP_END_ENABLED()) {
8345  RUBY_DTRACE_GC_SWEEP_END();
8346  }
8347 
8348  if (gc_prof_enabled(objspace)) {
8349  double sweep_time;
8350  gc_profile_record *record = gc_prof_record(objspace);
8351 
8352  if (record->gc_time > 0) {
8353  sweep_time = elapsed_time_from(objspace->profile.gc_sweep_start_time);
8354  /* need to accumulate GC time for lazy sweep after gc() */
8355  record->gc_time += sweep_time;
8356  }
8357  else if (GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL) {
8358  sweep_time = elapsed_time_from(objspace->profile.gc_sweep_start_time);
8359  }
8360 
8361 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
8362  record->gc_sweep_time += sweep_time;
8363  if (heap_pages_deferred_final) record->flags |= GPR_FLAG_HAVE_FINALIZE;
8364 #endif
8365  if (heap_pages_deferred_final) objspace->profile.latest_gc_info |= GPR_FLAG_HAVE_FINALIZE;
8366  }
8367 }

8369 static inline void
8370 gc_prof_set_malloc_info(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
8371 {
8372 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
8373  if (gc_prof_enabled(objspace)) {
8374  gc_profile_record *record = gc_prof_record(objspace);
8375  record->allocate_increase = malloc_increase;
8376  record->allocate_limit = malloc_limit;
8377  }
8378 #endif
8379 }
8380 
8381 static inline void
8382 gc_prof_set_heap_info(rb_objspace_t *objspace)
8383 {
8384  if (gc_prof_enabled(objspace)) {
8385  gc_profile_record *record = gc_prof_record(objspace);
8386  size_t live = objspace->profile.total_allocated_objects_at_gc_start - objspace->profile.total_freed_objects;
8387  size_t total = objspace->profile.heap_used_at_gc_start * HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT;
8388 
8389 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
8390  record->heap_use_pages = objspace->profile.heap_used_at_gc_start;
8391  record->heap_live_objects = live;
8392  record->heap_free_objects = total - live;
8393 #endif
8394 
8395  record->heap_total_objects = total;
8396  record->heap_use_size = live * sizeof(RVALUE);
8397  record->heap_total_size = total * sizeof(RVALUE);
8398  }
8399 }
8400 
8401 /*
8402  * call-seq:
8403  * GC::Profiler.clear -> nil
8404  *
8405  * Clears the GC profiler data.
8406  *
8407  */
8408 
8409 static VALUE
8410 gc_profile_clear(void)
8411 {
8412  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
8413  if (GC_PROFILE_RECORD_DEFAULT_SIZE * 2 < objspace->profile.size) {
8414  objspace->profile.size = GC_PROFILE_RECORD_DEFAULT_SIZE * 2;
8415  objspace->profile.records = realloc(objspace->profile.records, sizeof(gc_profile_record) * objspace->profile.size);
8416  if (!objspace->profile.records) {
8417  rb_memerror();
8418  }
8419  }
8420  MEMZERO(objspace->profile.records, gc_profile_record, objspace->profile.size);
8421  objspace->profile.next_index = 0;
8422  objspace->profile.current_record = 0;
8423  return Qnil;
8424 }
8425 
8426 /*
8427  * call-seq:
8428  * GC::Profiler.raw_data -> [Hash, ...]
8429  *
8430  * Returns an Array of individual raw profile data Hashes ordered
8431  * from earliest to latest by +:GC_INVOKE_TIME+.
8432  *
8433  * For example:
8434  *
8435  * [
8436  * {
8437  * :GC_TIME=>1.3000000000000858e-05,
8438  * :GC_INVOKE_TIME=>0.010634999999999999,
8439  * :HEAP_USE_SIZE=>289640,
8440  * :HEAP_TOTAL_SIZE=>588960,
8441  * :HEAP_TOTAL_OBJECTS=>14724,
8442  * :GC_IS_MARKED=>false
8443  * },
8444  * # ...
8445  * ]
8446  *
8447  * The keys mean:
8448  *
8449  * +:GC_TIME+::
8450  * Time elapsed in seconds for this GC run
8451  * +:GC_INVOKE_TIME+::
8452  * Time elapsed in seconds from startup to when the GC was invoked
8453  * +:HEAP_USE_SIZE+::
8454  * Total bytes of heap used
8455  * +:HEAP_TOTAL_SIZE+::
8456  * Total size of heap in bytes
8457  * +:HEAP_TOTAL_OBJECTS+::
8458  * Total number of objects
8459  * +:GC_IS_MARKED+::
8460  * Returns +true+ if the GC is in mark phase
8461  *
8462  * If ruby was built with +GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL+, you will also have access
8463  * to the following hash keys:
8464  *
8465  * +:GC_MARK_TIME+::
8466  * +:GC_SWEEP_TIME+::
8467  * +:ALLOCATE_INCREASE+::
8468  * +:ALLOCATE_LIMIT+::
8469  * +:HEAP_USE_PAGES+::
8470  * +:HEAP_LIVE_OBJECTS+::
8471  * +:HEAP_FREE_OBJECTS+::
8472  * +:HAVE_FINALIZE+::
8473  *
8474  */
8475 
8476 static VALUE
8477 gc_profile_record_get(void)
8478 {
8479  VALUE prof;
8480  VALUE gc_profile = rb_ary_new();
8481  size_t i;
8482  rb_objspace_t *objspace = (&rb_objspace);
8483 
8484  if (!objspace->profile.run) {
8485  return Qnil;
8486  }
8487 
8488  for (i =0; i < objspace->profile.next_index; i++) {
8489  gc_profile_record *record = &objspace->profile.records[i];
8490 
8491  prof = rb_hash_new();
8492  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("GC_FLAGS")), gc_info_decode(0, rb_hash_new(), record->flags));
8493  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("GC_TIME")), DBL2NUM(record->gc_time));
8494  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("GC_INVOKE_TIME")), DBL2NUM(record->gc_invoke_time));
8495  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("HEAP_USE_SIZE")), SIZET2NUM(record->heap_use_size));
8496  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("HEAP_TOTAL_SIZE")), SIZET2NUM(record->heap_total_size));
8497  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("HEAP_TOTAL_OBJECTS")), SIZET2NUM(record->heap_total_objects));
8498  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("GC_IS_MARKED")), Qtrue);
8499 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
8500  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("GC_MARK_TIME")), DBL2NUM(record->gc_mark_time));
8501  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("GC_SWEEP_TIME")), DBL2NUM(record->gc_sweep_time));
8502  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("ALLOCATE_INCREASE")), SIZET2NUM(record->allocate_increase));
8503  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("ALLOCATE_LIMIT")), SIZET2NUM(record->allocate_limit));
8504  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("HEAP_USE_PAGES")), SIZET2NUM(record->heap_use_pages));
8505  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("HEAP_LIVE_OBJECTS")), SIZET2NUM(record->heap_live_objects));
8506  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("HEAP_FREE_OBJECTS")), SIZET2NUM(record->heap_free_objects));
8507 
8508  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("REMOVING_OBJECTS")), SIZET2NUM(record->removing_objects));
8509  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("EMPTY_OBJECTS")), SIZET2NUM(record->empty_objects));
8510 
8511  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("HAVE_FINALIZE")), (record->flags & GPR_FLAG_HAVE_FINALIZE) ? Qtrue : Qfalse);
8512 #endif
8513 
8514 #if RGENGC_PROFILE > 0
8515  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("OLD_OBJECTS")), SIZET2NUM(record->old_objects));
8516  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("REMEMBED_NORMAL_OBJECTS")), SIZET2NUM(record->remembered_normal_objects));
8517  rb_hash_aset(prof, ID2SYM(rb_intern("REMEMBED_SHADY_OBJECTS")), SIZET2NUM(record->remembered_shady_objects));
8518 #endif
8519  rb_ary_push(gc_profile, prof);
8520  }
8521 
8522  return gc_profile;
8523 }
8524 
8525 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
8526 #define MAJOR_REASON_MAX 0x10
8527 
8528 static char *
8529 gc_profile_dump_major_reason(int flags, char *buff)
8530 {
8531  int reason = flags & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_MASK;
8532  int i = 0;
8533 
8534  if (reason == GPR_FLAG_NONE) {
8535  buff[0] = '-';
8536  buff[1] = 0;
8537  }
8538  else {
8539 #define C(x, s) \
8540  if (reason & GPR_FLAG_MAJOR_BY_##x) { \
8541  buff[i++] = #x[0]; \
8542  if (i >= MAJOR_REASON_MAX) rb_bug("gc_profile_dump_major_reason: overflow"); \
8543  buff[i] = 0; \
8544  }
8545  C(NOFREE, N);
8546  C(OLDGEN, O);
8547  C(SHADY, S);
8548  C(RESCAN, R);
8549  C(STRESS, T);
8550 #if RGENGC_ESTIMATE_OLDMALLOC
8551  C(OLDMALLOC, M);
8552 #endif
8553 #undef C
8554  }
8555  return buff;
8556 }
8557 #endif
8558 
8559 static void
8560 gc_profile_dump_on(VALUE out, VALUE (*append)(VALUE, VALUE))
8561 {
8562  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
8563  size_t count = objspace->profile.next_index;
8564 #ifdef MAJOR_REASON_MAX
8565  char reason_str[MAJOR_REASON_MAX];
8566 #endif
8567 
8568  if (objspace->profile.run && count /* > 1 */) {
8569  size_t i;
8570  const gc_profile_record *record;
8571 
8572  append(out, rb_sprintf("GC %"PRIuSIZE" invokes.\n", objspace->profile.count));
8573  append(out, rb_str_new_cstr("Index Invoke Time(sec) Use Size(byte) Total Size(byte) Total Object GC Time(ms)\n"));
8574 
8575  for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
8576  record = &objspace->profile.records[i];
8577  append(out, rb_sprintf("%5"PRIdSIZE" %19.3f %20"PRIuSIZE" %20"PRIuSIZE" %20"PRIuSIZE" %30.20f\n",
8578  i+1, record->gc_invoke_time, record->heap_use_size,
8579  record->heap_total_size, record->heap_total_objects, record->gc_time*1000));
8580  }
8581 
8582 #if GC_PROFILE_MORE_DETAIL
8583  append(out, rb_str_new_cstr("\n\n" \
8584  "More detail.\n" \
8585  "Prepare Time = Previously GC's rest sweep time\n"
8586  "Index Flags Allocate Inc. Allocate Limit"
8587 #if CALC_EXACT_MALLOC_SIZE
8588  " Allocated Size"
8589 #endif
8590  " Use Page Mark Time(ms) Sweep Time(ms) Prepare Time(ms) LivingObj FreeObj RemovedObj EmptyObj"
8591 #if RGENGC_PROFILE
8592  " OldgenObj RemNormObj RemShadObj"
8593 #endif
8594 #if GC_PROFILE_DETAIL_MEMORY
8595  " MaxRSS(KB) MinorFLT MajorFLT"
8596 #endif
8597  "\n"));
8598 
8599  for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
8600  record = &objspace->profile.records[i];
8601  append(out, rb_sprintf("%5"PRIdSIZE" %4s/%c/%6s%c %13"PRIuSIZE" %15"PRIuSIZE
8602 #if CALC_EXACT_MALLOC_SIZE
8603  " %15"PRIuSIZE
8604 #endif
8605  " %9"PRIuSIZE" %17.12f %17.12f %17.12f %10"PRIuSIZE" %10"PRIuSIZE" %10"PRIuSIZE" %10"PRIuSIZE
8606 #if RGENGC_PROFILE
8607  "%10"PRIuSIZE" %10"PRIuSIZE" %10"PRIuSIZE
8608 #endif
8609 #if GC_PROFILE_DETAIL_MEMORY
8610  "%11ld %8ld %8ld"
8611 #endif
8612 
8613  "\n",
8614  i+1,
8615  gc_profile_dump_major_reason(record->flags, reason_str),
8616  (record->flags & GPR_FLAG_HAVE_FINALIZE) ? 'F' : '.',
8617  (record->flags & GPR_FLAG_NEWOBJ) ? "NEWOBJ" :
8618  (record->flags & GPR_FLAG_MALLOC) ? "MALLOC" :
8619  (record->flags & GPR_FLAG_METHOD) ? "METHOD" :
8620  (record->flags & GPR_FLAG_CAPI) ? "CAPI__" : "??????",
8621  (record->flags & GPR_FLAG_STRESS) ? '!' : ' ',
8622  record->allocate_increase, record->allocate_limit,
8623 #if CALC_EXACT_MALLOC_SIZE
8624  record->allocated_size,
8625 #endif
8626  record->heap_use_pages,
8627  record->gc_mark_time*1000,
8628  record->gc_sweep_time*1000,
8629  record->prepare_time*1000,
8630 
8631  record->heap_live_objects,
8632  record->heap_free_objects,
8633  record->removing_objects,
8634  record->empty_objects
8635 #if RGENGC_PROFILE
8636  ,
8637  record->old_objects,
8638  record->remembered_normal_objects,
8639  record->remembered_shady_objects
8640 #endif
8641 #if GC_PROFILE_DETAIL_MEMORY
8642  ,
8643  record->maxrss / 1024,
8644  record->minflt,
8645  record->majflt
8646 #endif
8647 
8648  ));
8649  }
8650 #endif
8651  }
8652 }
8653 
8654 /*
8655  * call-seq:
8656  * GC::Profiler.result -> String
8657  *
8658  * Returns a profile data report such as:
8659  *
8660  * GC 1 invokes.
8661  * Index Invoke Time(sec) Use Size(byte) Total Size(byte) Total Object GC time(ms)
8662  * 1 0.012 159240 212940 10647 0.00000000000001530000
8663  */
8664 
8665 static VALUE
8666 gc_profile_result(void)
8667 {
8668  VALUE str = rb_str_buf_new(0);
8669  gc_profile_dump_on(str, rb_str_buf_append);
8670  return str;
8671 }
8672 
8673 /*
8674  * call-seq:
8675  * GC::Profiler.report
8676  * GC::Profiler.report(io)
8677  *
8678  * Writes the GC::Profiler.result to <tt>$stdout</tt> or the given IO object.
8679  *
8680  */
8681 
8682 static VALUE
8683 gc_profile_report(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE self)
8684 {
8685  VALUE out;
8686 
8687  if (argc == 0) {
8688  out = rb_stdout;
8689  }
8690  else {
8691  rb_scan_args(argc, argv, "01", &out);
8692  }
8693  gc_profile_dump_on(out, rb_io_write);
8694 
8695  return Qnil;
8696 }
8697 
8698 /*
8699  * call-seq:
8700  * GC::Profiler.total_time -> float
8701  *
8702  * The total time used for garbage collection in seconds
8703  */
8704 
8705 static VALUE
8706 gc_profile_total_time(VALUE self)
8707 {
8708  double time = 0;
8709  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
8710 
8711  if (objspace->profile.run && objspace->profile.next_index > 0) {
8712  size_t i;
8713  size_t count = objspace->profile.next_index;
8714 
8715  for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
8716  time += objspace->profile.records[i].gc_time;
8717  }
8718  }
8719  return DBL2NUM(time);
8720 }
8721 
8722 /*
8723  * call-seq:
8724  * GC::Profiler.enabled? -> true or false
8725  *
8726  * The current status of GC profile mode.
8727  */
8728 
8729 static VALUE
8730 gc_profile_enable_get(VALUE self)
8731 {
8732  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
8733  return objspace->profile.run ? Qtrue : Qfalse;
8734 }
8735 
8736 /*
8737  * call-seq:
8738  * GC::Profiler.enable -> nil
8739  *
8740  * Starts the GC profiler.
8741  *
8742  */
8743 
8744 static VALUE
8745 gc_profile_enable(void)
8746 {
8747  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
8748  objspace->profile.run = TRUE;
8749  objspace->profile.current_record = 0;
8750  return Qnil;
8751 }
8752 
8753 /*
8754  * call-seq:
8755  * GC::Profiler.disable -> nil
8756  *
8757  * Stops the GC profiler.
8758  *
8759  */
8760 
8761 static VALUE
8762 gc_profile_disable(void)
8763 {
8764  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
8765 
8766  objspace->profile.run = FALSE;
8767  objspace->profile.current_record = 0;
8768  return Qnil;
8769 }

8774 
8775 static const char *
8776 type_name(int type, VALUE obj)
8777 {
8778  switch (type) {
8779 #define TYPE_NAME(t) case (t): return #t;
8780  TYPE_NAME(T_NONE);
8781  TYPE_NAME(T_OBJECT);
8782  TYPE_NAME(T_CLASS);
8783  TYPE_NAME(T_MODULE);
8784  TYPE_NAME(T_FLOAT);
8785  TYPE_NAME(T_STRING);
8786  TYPE_NAME(T_REGEXP);
8787  TYPE_NAME(T_ARRAY);
8788  TYPE_NAME(T_HASH);
8789  TYPE_NAME(T_STRUCT);
8790  TYPE_NAME(T_BIGNUM);
8791  TYPE_NAME(T_FILE);
8792  TYPE_NAME(T_MATCH);
8793  TYPE_NAME(T_COMPLEX);
8794  TYPE_NAME(T_RATIONAL);
8795  TYPE_NAME(T_NIL);
8796  TYPE_NAME(T_TRUE);
8797  TYPE_NAME(T_FALSE);
8798  TYPE_NAME(T_SYMBOL);
8799  TYPE_NAME(T_FIXNUM);
8800  TYPE_NAME(T_UNDEF);
8801  TYPE_NAME(T_IMEMO);
8802  TYPE_NAME(T_NODE);
8803  TYPE_NAME(T_ICLASS);
8804  TYPE_NAME(T_ZOMBIE);
8805  case T_DATA:
8806  if (obj && rb_objspace_data_type_name(obj)) {
8807  return rb_objspace_data_type_name(obj);
8808  }
8809  return "T_DATA";
8810 #undef TYPE_NAME
8811  }
8812  return "unknown";
8813 }
8814 
8815 static const char *
8816 obj_type_name(VALUE obj)
8817 {
8818  return type_name(TYPE(obj), obj);
8819 }
8820 
8821 #if RGENGC_DEBUG || RGENGC_CHECK_MODE
8822 #define OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_NUM 10
8823 #define OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE 0x100
8824 static int obj_info_buffers_index = 0;
8825 static char obj_info_buffers[OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_NUM][OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE];
8826 
8827 /* from array.c */
8828 # define ARY_SHARED_P(ary) \
8829  (assert(!FL_TEST((ary), ELTS_SHARED) || !FL_TEST((ary), RARRAY_EMBED_FLAG)), \
8830  FL_TEST((ary),ELTS_SHARED)!=0)
8831 # define ARY_EMBED_P(ary) \
8832  (assert(!FL_TEST((ary), ELTS_SHARED) || !FL_TEST((ary), RARRAY_EMBED_FLAG)), \
8833  FL_TEST((ary), RARRAY_EMBED_FLAG)!=0)
8834 
8835 static const char *
8836 obj_info(VALUE obj)
8837 {
8838  const int index = obj_info_buffers_index++;
8839  char *const buff = &obj_info_buffers[index][0];
8840  const int age = RVALUE_FLAGS_AGE(RBASIC(obj)->flags);
8841  const int type = BUILTIN_TYPE(obj);
8842 
8843  if (obj_info_buffers_index >= OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_NUM) {
8844  obj_info_buffers_index = 0;
8845  }
8846 
8847 #define TF(c) ((c) != 0 ? "true" : "false")
8848 #define C(c, s) ((c) != 0 ? (s) : " ")
8849  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%p [%d%s%s%s%s] %s",
8850  (void *)obj, age,
8851  C(RVALUE_UNCOLLECTIBLE_BITMAP(obj), "L"),
8852  C(RVALUE_MARK_BITMAP(obj), "M"),
8853  C(RVALUE_MARKING_BITMAP(obj), "R"),
8854  C(RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED_BITMAP(obj), "U"),
8855  obj_type_name(obj));
8856 
8857  if (internal_object_p(obj)) {
8858  /* ignore */
8859  }
8860  else if (RBASIC(obj)->klass == 0) {
8861  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s (temporary internal)", buff);
8862  }
8863  else {
8864  VALUE class_path = rb_class_path_cached(RBASIC(obj)->klass);
8865  if (!NIL_P(class_path)) {
8866  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s (%s)", buff, RSTRING_PTR(class_path));
8867  }
8868  }
8869 
8870 #if GC_DEBUG
8871  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s @%s:%d", buff, RANY(obj)->file, RANY(obj)->line);
8872 #endif
8873 
8874  switch (type) {
8875  case T_NODE:
8876  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s (%s)", buff,
8877  ruby_node_name(nd_type(obj)));
8878  break;
8879  case T_ARRAY:
8880  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s [%s%s] len: %d", buff,
8881  C(ARY_EMBED_P(obj), "E"),
8882  C(ARY_SHARED_P(obj), "S"),
8883  (int)RARRAY_LEN(obj));
8884  break;
8885  case T_STRING: {
8886  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s %s", buff, RSTRING_PTR(obj));
8887  break;
8888  }
8889  case T_CLASS: {
8890  VALUE class_path = rb_class_path_cached(obj);
8891  if (!NIL_P(class_path)) {
8892  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s %s", buff, RSTRING_PTR(class_path));
8893  }
8894  break;
8895  }
8896  case T_DATA: {
8897  const char * const type_name = rb_objspace_data_type_name(obj);
8898  if (type_name && strcmp(type_name, "iseq") == 0) {
8899  rb_iseq_t *iseq;
8900  GetISeqPtr(obj, iseq);
8901  if (iseq->location.label) {
8902  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s %s@%s:%d", buff,
8903  RSTRING_PTR(iseq->location.label), RSTRING_PTR(iseq->location.path), (int)iseq->location.first_lineno);
8904  }
8905  }
8906  else if (type_name) {
8907  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s %s", buff, type_name);
8908  }
8909  break;
8910  }
8911  case T_IMEMO: {
8912  const char *imemo_name;
8913  switch (imemo_type(obj)) {
8914 #define IMEMO_NAME(x) case imemo_##x: imemo_name = #x; break;
8915  IMEMO_NAME(none);
8916  IMEMO_NAME(cref);
8917  IMEMO_NAME(svar);
8918  IMEMO_NAME(throw_data);
8919  IMEMO_NAME(ifunc);
8920  IMEMO_NAME(memo);
8921  IMEMO_NAME(ment);
8922  default: rb_bug("unknown IMEMO");
8923 #undef IMEMO_NAME
8924  }
8925  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s %s", buff, imemo_name);
8926  if (imemo_type(obj) == imemo_ment) {
8927  const rb_method_entry_t *me = &RANY(obj)->as.imemo.ment;
8928  snprintf(buff, OBJ_INFO_BUFFERS_SIZE, "%s (called_id: %s, type: %d)", buff, rb_id2name(me->called_id), me->def->type);
8929  }
8930  }
8931  default:
8932  break;
8933  }
8934 #undef TF
8935 #undef C
8936 
8937  return buff;
8938 }
8939 
8940 #else
8941 static const char *
8942 obj_info(VALUE obj)
8943 {
8944  return obj_type_name(obj);
8945 }
8946 #endif
8947 
8948 const char *
8949 rb_obj_info(VALUE obj)
8950 {
8951  if (!rb_special_const_p(obj)) {
8952  return obj_info(obj);
8953  }
8954  else {
8955  return obj_type_name(obj);
8956  }
8957 }
8958 
8959 #if GC_DEBUG
8960 
8961 void
8962 rb_gcdebug_print_obj_condition(VALUE obj)
8963 {
8964  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
8965 
8966  fprintf(stderr, "created at: %s:%d\n", RANY(obj)->file, RANY(obj)->line);
8967 
8968  if (is_pointer_to_heap(objspace, (void *)obj)) {
8969  fprintf(stderr, "pointer to heap?: true\n");
8970  }
8971  else {
8972  fprintf(stderr, "pointer to heap?: false\n");
8973  return;
8974  }
8975 
8976  fprintf(stderr, "marked? : %s\n", MARKED_IN_BITMAP(GET_HEAP_MARK_BITS(obj), obj) ? "true" : "false");
8977 #if USE_RGENGC
8978  fprintf(stderr, "age? : %d\n", RVALUE_AGE(obj));
8979  fprintf(stderr, "old? : %s\n", RVALUE_OLD_P(obj) ? "true" : "false");
8980  fprintf(stderr, "WB-protected?: %s\n", RVALUE_WB_UNPROTECTED(obj) ? "false" : "true");
8981  fprintf(stderr, "remembered? : %s\n", RVALUE_REMEMBERED(obj) ? "true" : "false");
8982 #endif
8983 
8984  if (is_lazy_sweeping(heap_eden)) {
8985  fprintf(stderr, "lazy sweeping?: true\n");
8986  fprintf(stderr, "swept?: %s\n", is_swept_object(objspace, obj) ? "done" : "not yet");
8987  }
8988  else {
8989  fprintf(stderr, "lazy sweeping?: false\n");
8990  }
8991 }

8994 gcdebug_sentinel(VALUE obj, VALUE name)
8995 {
8996  fprintf(stderr, "WARNING: object %s(%p) is inadvertently collected\n", (char *)name, (void *)obj);
8997  return Qnil;
8998 }

9001 rb_gcdebug_sentinel(VALUE obj, const char *name)
9002 {
9003  rb_define_finalizer(obj, rb_proc_new(gcdebug_sentinel, (VALUE)name));
9004 }

9010 rb_gcdebug_add_stress_to_class(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE self)

9020 
9021 static VALUE
9022 rb_gcdebug_remove_stress_to_class(int argc, VALUE *argv, VALUE self)
9023 {
9024  rb_objspace_t *objspace = &rb_objspace;
9025  int i;
9026 
9027  if (stress_to_class) {
9028  for (i = 0; i < argc; ++i) {
9029  rb_ary_delete_same(stress_to_class, argv[i]);
9030  }
9031  if (RARRAY_LEN(stress_to_class) == 0) {
9032  stress_to_class = 0;
9033  }
9034  }
9035  return Qnil;
9036 }
9037 #endif
9038 
9039 /*
9040  * Document-module: ObjectSpace
9041  *
9042  * The ObjectSpace module contains a number of routines
9043  * that interact with the garbage collection facility and allow you to
9044  * traverse all living objects with an iterator.
9045  *
9046  * ObjectSpace also provides support for object finalizers, procs that will be
9047  * called when a specific object is about to be destroyed by garbage
9048  * collection.
9049  *
9050  * require 'objspace'
9051  *
9052  * a = "A"
9053  * b = "B"
9054  *
9055  * ObjectSpace.define_finalizer(a, proc {|id| puts "Finalizer one on #{id}" })
9056  * ObjectSpace.define_finalizer(b, proc {|id| puts "Finalizer two on #{id}" })
9057  *
9058  * _produces:_
9059  *
9060  * Finalizer two on 537763470
9061  * Finalizer one on 537763480
9062  */
9063 
9064 /*
9065  * Document-class: ObjectSpace::WeakMap
9066  *
9067  * An ObjectSpace::WeakMap object holds references to
9068  * any objects, but those objects can get garbage collected.
9069  *
9070  * This class is mostly used internally by WeakRef, please use
9071  * +lib/weakref.rb+ for the public interface.
9072  */
9073 
9074 /* Document-class: GC::Profiler
9075  *
9076  * The GC profiler provides access to information on GC runs including time,
9077  * length and object space size.
9078  *
9079  * Example:
9080  *
9081  * GC::Profiler.enable
9082  *
9083  * require 'rdoc/rdoc'
9084  *
9085  * GC::Profiler.report
9086  *
9087  * GC::Profiler.disable
9088  *
9089  * See also GC.count, GC.malloc_allocated_size and GC.malloc_allocations
9090  */
9091 
9092 /*
9093  * The GC module provides an interface to Ruby's mark and
9094  * sweep garbage collection mechanism.
9095  *
9096  * Some of the underlying methods are also available via the ObjectSpace
9097  * module.
9098  *
9099  * You may obtain information about the operation of the GC through
9100  * GC::Profiler.
9101  */
9102 
9103 void
9104 Init_GC(void)
9105 {
9106 #undef rb_intern
9107  VALUE rb_mObjSpace;
9108  VALUE rb_mProfiler;
9109  VALUE gc_constants;
9110 
9111  rb_mGC = rb_define_module("GC");
9112  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mGC, "start", gc_start_internal, -1);
9113  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mGC, "enable", rb_gc_enable, 0);
9114  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mGC, "disable", rb_gc_disable, 0);
9115  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mGC, "stress", gc_stress_get, 0);
9116  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mGC, "stress=", gc_stress_set_m, 1);
9117  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mGC, "count", gc_count, 0);
9118  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mGC, "stat", gc_stat, -1);
9119  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mGC, "latest_gc_info", gc_latest_gc_info, -1);
9120  rb_define_method(rb_mGC, "garbage_collect", gc_start_internal, -1);
9121 
9122  gc_constants = rb_hash_new();
9123  rb_hash_aset(gc_constants, ID2SYM(rb_intern("RVALUE_SIZE")), SIZET2NUM(sizeof(RVALUE)));
9124  rb_hash_aset(gc_constants, ID2SYM(rb_intern("HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT")), SIZET2NUM(HEAP_OBJ_LIMIT));
9125  rb_hash_aset(gc_constants, ID2SYM(rb_intern("HEAP_BITMAP_SIZE")), SIZET2NUM(HEAP_BITMAP_SIZE));
9126  rb_hash_aset(gc_constants, ID2SYM(rb_intern("HEAP_BITMAP_PLANES")), SIZET2NUM(HEAP_BITMAP_PLANES));
9127  OBJ_FREEZE(gc_constants);
9128  rb_define_const(rb_mGC, "INTERNAL_CONSTANTS", gc_constants);
9129 
9130  rb_mProfiler = rb_define_module_under(rb_mGC, "Profiler");
9131  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mProfiler, "enabled?", gc_profile_enable_get, 0);
9132  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mProfiler, "enable", gc_profile_enable, 0);
9133  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mProfiler, "raw_data", gc_profile_record_get, 0);
9134  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mProfiler, "disable", gc_profile_disable, 0);
9135  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mProfiler, "clear", gc_profile_clear, 0);
9136  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mProfiler, "result", gc_profile_result, 0);
9137  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mProfiler, "report", gc_profile_report, -1);
9138  rb_define_singleton_method(rb_mProfiler, "total_time", gc_profile_total_time, 0);
9139 
9140  rb_mObjSpace = rb_define_module("ObjectSpace");
9141  rb_define_module_function(rb_mObjSpace, "each_object", os_each_obj, -1);
9142  rb_define_module_function(rb_mObjSpace, "garbage_collect", gc_start_internal, -1);
9143 
9144  rb_define_module_function(rb_mObjSpace, "define_finalizer", define_final, -1);
9145  rb_define_module_function(rb_mObjSpace, "undefine_finalizer", undefine_final, 1);
9146 
9147  rb_define_module_function(rb_mObjSpace, "_id2ref", id2ref, 1);
9148 
9149  rb_vm_register_special_exception(ruby_error_nomemory, rb_eNoMemError, "failed to allocate memory");
9150 
9151  rb_define_method(rb_cBasicObject, "__id__", rb_obj_id, 0);
9152  rb_define_method(rb_mKernel, "object_id", rb_obj_id, 0);
9153 
9154  rb_define_module_function(rb_mObjSpace, "count_objects", count_objects, -1);
9155 
9156  {
9157  VALUE rb_cWeakMap = rb_define_class_under(rb_mObjSpace, "WeakMap", rb_cObject);
9158  rb_define_alloc_func(rb_cWeakMap, wmap_allocate);
9159  rb_define_method(rb_cWeakMap, "[]=", wmap_aset, 2);
9160  rb_define_method(rb_cWeakMap, "[]", wmap_aref, 1);

9179 #if MALLOC_ALLOCATED_SIZE
